title: mexican cornbread with beef
directions: Cook meat in skillet until red is gone.
Do not brown. Before done, add onion, bell pepper and garlic.
In large mixing bowl, mix cornmeal with salt and soda.
Add milk, eggs, cream corn and oil.
Mix well then add cheese and jalapenos.
Pour 1/2 of cornbread mixture into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Spread meat mixture on top.
Add remaining cornbread mixture.
Bake 1 hour or until golden brown in 400° oven.

title: shrimp macaroni salad
directions: Thaw and thoroughly rinse baby shrimp.
Squeeze in a paper towel and set aside.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Rinse and drain.
Toss macaroni with clear Italian salad dressing, just enough to keep it from sticking together. Steam carrots and broccoli until slightly tender.
Toss macaroni, egg, carrots, broccoli and onion together.
Add baby shrimp.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in punch bowl except sliced fruit and sugar.
Add sugar to taste.
Arrange sliced fruit on top.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix soup, pimentos, chopped onion, mayonnaise and cheese.
Add macaroni and mix real good.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish.
Melt margarine and add crushed Ritz crackers.
Stir until crackers are coated with margarine. Spread on top of macaroni mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: jan hagel cookies
directions: *Or 2 sticks I Can't Believe It's Not Butter.

title: orange spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
To serve, stir 2 heaping teaspoons of the mix into an 8 ounce mug of hot water or 10 ounce glass of cold water.
Great hot or cold.

title: italian pasta summer salad
directions: Twenty-four hours before serving, cook macaroni twists according to box directions.
Drain, rinse and cool.
Put in large bowl and marinate overnight in Italian dressing.
The following day, combine all other ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Chill until ready to serve.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top just before serving.
Serves 16 people, must do ahead.
Prepared in one half hour; cooking time 10 minutes.
This salad could be served with anything.
It is actually good without shrimp, too.

title: creamy fudge for beginners
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients 2 minutes after it boils.
Add vanilla and butter.
Beat until creamy.
This fudge never gets too hard and always sets.

title: mixed roast vegetables
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°.
Spread the olive oil over a baking sheet that measures about 12 x 18-inches.
Put each vegetable into a specific area on the baking sheet, spreading them out as much as possible.
Sprinkle on the garlic and herbs.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cover reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in soup and milk - heat through. Garnish if desired with shredded cheddar cheese, diced cooked ham or bacon.
Add pepper to taste.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Combine first four ingredients. Gradually add milk.
Mix well.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Cook spinach according to package; drain with strainer and spoon and press out all water.
Mix eggs, cream and seasonings. Stir in spinach.
Pour into frozen pie shell.
Place in preheated 350° oven and cook for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cook bacon, drain on paper towel, roll and place on top of quiche before serving.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast with milk, sugar and salt.
Stir
until yeast is dissolved.
Add eggs and shortening. Stir in flour with a spoon as long as you can, then finish mixing it with your hands until all the flour is mixed well.
Wet a towel in hot water and put over top of the bowl.
You can let rise a little while, then pour it out, roll them and cut them out.
Let them finish rising before you bake them.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Stir in taco mix and 1 cup water and simmer 10 minutes.
Pour half of the bottle of taco sauce into casserole.
Turn 5 tortillas in sauce coating each and spread overlapping in bottom of dish.
Press most of water out of cooked spinach and stir half into beef.
Spoon beef mixture into tortilla and sprinkle with half of Jack cheese.
Cover with remaining tortillas, overlapping and spread remaining taco sauce over. Sprinkle diced ham on top and spread with sour cream.
Scatter remaining spinach over sour cream.
Top evenly with remaining 1/2 of cheese.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes, covering for the first 25 minutes.

title: favorite pie crust
directions: With pastry cutter, mix flour, shortening, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Slowly add cold water and mix well, until mixture forms into a ball.
Refrigerate at least one hour before rolling. Roll out onto well floured surface.
Makes four 9-inch shells. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: easy fruit tray
directions: Prepare fruits and chill. Serve with cheese slices and strawberry yogurt as a dip.

title: sinful salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add all other ingredients, except sour cream.
Put half of mixture into mold and congeal. Spread sour cream on top.
Pour the rest of jello mixture into mold and chill until set.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Fry meat, drain and rinse real good.
Add onion and pepper. Fry until meat is brown and pepper is soft.
Put in a large baking dish.
Add catsup, brown sugar, red pepper, chili powder and beans.
Also hot sauce.
Mix together.
Bake in oven for about 30 to 45 minutes.
May be microwaved.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt, cocoa and beaten egg yolks with a small amount of milk to mix.
Heat milk to boiling stage. Immediately add first mixture and cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into baked shell and add meringue.
Brown.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Mix jello with boiling water thoroughly.
Add the ice cubes and stir until all is dissolved and refrigerate for 20 minutes.

title: rice with zucchini
directions: Cook onion for 8 to 10 minutes, or until they are soft.
Add rice, 4 cups of water and thyme.
When the rice has absorbed most of the water, add sliced zucchini.
Cook over low heat until the vegetables are done.

title: tailgate salad
directions: Drain all cans and empty into a large bowl.
Add celery, onion, green pepper and pimentos.
Bring to a boil sugar, vinegar and oil.
Pour over salad while still hot.	Chill overnight.

title: molasses cake or cookies
directions: Mix with enough flour to roll out and cut into cookies.
Bake at 375° until brown.
You can make gingerbread; you can make a loaf cake and add other spices.

title: turkey chili(serves 8)
directions: Spray pan with vegetable spray.
Saute onion, celery and peppers.
Add turkey and brown.
Add tomato juice and entire can of tomatoes, juice and all.
(I cut up tomatoes in hunks.)
Season with rest of ingredients to taste.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes and onion thin.
Put in boiling water, cover and cook 5 minutes.
Drain.
Melt margarine.
Stir in flour, pepper and paprika.
Cook about 1 minute.
Gradually add milk, stirring until it begins to thicken.
Grease casserole and layer potatoes, onion and ham.
Sprinkle with parsley and cover with half of the sauce.
Put American cheese on this.
Repeat layer ending with sauce.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, with fork, stir first 5 ingredients together. Add chicken, pear, apple and celery.
Toss gently until well mixed.
Heap on lettuce leaves, or individual salad plates. Serves 4.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dredge steak in flour; brown with onions in butter.
Add seasonings and water.
Cover and simmer 45 to 60 minutes or until meat is almost tender, stirring occasionally.
Add soup; stir to mix.
Simmer 30 minutes or until beef is tender.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: cranberry gelatin
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add fruit with juice, mix and pour into 9x13 in. pan.
Chill overnight.
Mix sour cream and cream cheese until smooth.
Spread on top of set jello.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts if desired.
Whipped topping can be used instead of topping.

title: sausage and brown rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet. Remove and drain.
Pour off drippings, reserving 1/4 cup.
Add mushroom pieces and onion to drippings.
Saute until lightly browned. Remove and drain.
In a large bowl, blend cream or evaporated milk into flour to form a paste.
Stir in broth, pepper and thyme. Add sausage and onion mixture and rice.
Mix lightly.
Put into 2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pearl scott 7-up cake
directions: Beat eggs one at a time.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crispy fried catfish
directions: Sprinkle catfish with salt and pepper; place in shallow dish. Add hot sauce; marinate 1 to 2 hours in fridge.
Place corn meal in plastic bag.
Drop in fish, one at a time; shake until fish are completely coated.
Fry in deep, hot oil (375°) until fish float on top and are golden brown.
Drain well.
Garnish with lemon slices. Serves 6.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Combine spinach, mayonnaise, sour cream, onion, water chestnuts and soup mix.
Stir well.
Chill 2 hours before serving. Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: make ahead potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes; mash.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and margarine.
Mix well.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Yields 2 gallons.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugars, margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and egg in medium bowl with wooden spoon (plastic is okay, too!) until creamy and well blended.
Mix in flour and oats.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 1 1/2 inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake exactly 10 minutes.
Allow to cool 1 to 2 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: cube steak
directions: Place cube stake in crock-pot with both cans of soup.
Add 1/2 can of water to crock-pot.
Mix soup and water together.
Pour over cubed steak.
Cook 4
hours on high, 6 hours on low.

title: chocolate cake dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients except powdered sugar until well blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Layer nuts and rolls.
Sprinkle with dry pudding, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with waxed paper and let rise
overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.

title: spiced apple cider
directions: Combine cider and sugar.
Tie cloves and nutmeg in cloth.
Add to cider and bring to boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Remove bag and add juices.
Simmer again until heated.
Serve with cinnamon sticks.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: polynesian pork chops
directions: Season chops with garlic.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add chops and cook until browned.
Add onion.
Add soup, pineapple with juice, water, soy sauce and honey. Heat to a boil.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes or until done.

title: alabama dip
directions: Brown and drain meat, set aside.
Add Velveeta, Ro-Tel, picante sauce and soup together and heat.
Add meat after cheese has melted. You can make mild or hot by varying the spiciness of the sausage and picante sauce.

title: never fail drop biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cut in shortening; stir in milk to make soft dough.
Drop from spoon onto greased pan or into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 300° until lightly browned.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook all together until a little dropped in cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from fire.
Cool and beat well.
Pour in buttered pan and cut into squares.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Cook all ingredients and add seasonings: salt, pepper, dash of chili powder, parsley and garlic powder.
Cook until done.
Serves 20 people or enough for 2 weeks.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill before serving.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoons on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Chop all ingredients very fine or put in food processor.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour juice from 1 jar of jalapeno peppers into salsa.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Steam broccoli and place in casserole.
Mix mayonnaise, soup and lemon juice.
Pour over broccoli and bake until bubbly.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans, thoroughly.
Roll ball into shape and roll in pecans until covered.
Chill.

title: taco pie
directions: Spread crescent rolls in pie pan.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Pour into pie shell and top with corn chips and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Chop lettuce and tomato and place over slices of taco pie.
Top with taco sauce.

title: old fashion oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water on medium heat until raisins are plump (15 minutes).
Drain but reserve liquid.
Add or subtract to make 1/2 cup liquid.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Cook shrimp until done, then chop.
Heat soup and cream cheese in a double boiler until cream cheese melts.
Cool slightly; stir in gelatin and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into a gelatin mold and let gel at least 8 hours.
Unmold onto a platter lined with lettuce leaves, if desired.
Serve with crackers.
Lobster may be substituted instead of shrimp.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil and melted chocolate.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Add other ingredients (except powdered sugar).
Chill overnight.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve jello.
Beat in frozen strawberries.
Let it set some.
Pour over torn up angel food cake pieces.
Can use regular or diet jello.

title: pie pastry
directions: Mix
Crisco
into
flour,
mix water, salt and vinegar; add to flour mixture.
Stir with fork until dough forms ball. Roll out on floured surface.
Makes 2 (2-crust) pies.

title: old fashioned fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Combine reserved juice and sugar; stir well and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour pineapple juice mixture over salad; toss gently.
Chill 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add flour and milk, alternating.
Add salt, baking powder and flavoring.
Start in cold oven, cook cake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp parmesan
directions: Shell and devein shrimp; pat dry.
Mix bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese together.
Dip shrimp in milk, then roll in bread crumb and cheese mixture.
Lightly coat pan with Pam or butter.
Arrange shrimp all in one layer.
Take melted butter and coat shrimp. Bake in oven at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: heavenly beans
directions: Brown ground
beef
in a large pan.
Drain and set meat aside. Brown
bacon
in
the
same
pan.	Drain and set bacon aside. Saute
onion
in the same pan and then return meats to the pan. Add
the 3 cans of undrained beans to the onion-meat mixture. Stir
in brown sugar, catsup and liquid smoke.
Pour into a
large casserole	and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: zebra brownies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients and then add eggs, 1/2 milk, flour, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, nuts and chips.
Pour 1/2 of brownie mix into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour mixture of cream cheese, 1 egg, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla, then spoon on remaining brownie batter.
Marble by pulling knife through butter in wide curves; turn pan and repeat.
Bake in preheated oven at 350°.
Do not overbake!

title: hopping john with mexican tomatoes and rice
directions: Place ham hocks in large saucepan; cover with water.
Cook until almost done.
Add peas, onion, salt (if needed), pepper and enough water to cover.
Cook, covered, for 45 minutes or until peas are tender, adding water as needed.
Stir in rice and Mexican tomatoes; cover.
Cook until rice and peas are tender (30 minutes or longer).
Yields 6 servings.
Freezes well.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Mix flour and 6 tablespoons of juice (may add 12 tablespoons) in a small bowl.
In a separate bowl, combine pineapple, cheese and sugar.
Pour juice mixture over pineapple and cheese.
Mix well.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish and top with crushed crumbs.
Pour butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Pour the first 3 ingredients into a blender; blend.
Pour into a small saucepan and heat on medium just until it begins to boil. Pour into a mug and top with the marshmallows.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream together shortening and sugar until light.
Add eggs and vanilla. Cream until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add coconut and corn flakes.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until browned. Makes 90 cookies.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; set aside to cool.
Cream the cheese with sugar.
Stir cooled jello into cream cheese and sugar. Add whipped milk.
Pour into crust.
Top with pie filling or cracker crumbs.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture. Stir in oats and nuts; mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: drop sand tarts
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Drop by 1/2 tablespoon	on cookie sheet and press down with floured glass. Sprinkle
with sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° until light brown, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: angel pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Add vanilla.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Put layers of beef and vegetables in greased casserole in order.
Sprinkle mix on the potatoes and carrots.
Spread chicken soup on.
Cover and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Top with the onion rings the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust and chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: chocolate truffle bombe with hazelnuts
directions: Line bottom of 5-cup ring mold with 3/4 of the ice cream.
With small spoon, push ice cream up sides of mold, leaving deep groove in center.
Freeze until firm.
Bring cream to boil; remove from heat.
Add chocolate and stir until melted.
Blend in liqueur, hazelnuts and Grand Marnier.
Cool truffle mixture to room temperature.
Pour truffle mixture into groove of mold.
Spread remaining ice cream on top; cover with foil and freeze at least 4 hours.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Layer the bottom of a glass Pyrex dish with sour cream.
Cover the sour cream with hot salsa or picante medium sauce (we mix the two together so it's not so hot).
Sprinkle the top in layers as follows:
taco seasoning, followed by the green chilies and top with cheese.
Put in a microwave oven until the cheese melts; serve with corn chips.

title: ma elsie gue's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan; simmer 5 minutes.
Brown chicken, pork or beef.
Arrange in Pyrex dish and pour sauce over all.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour, covered.
May be used to baste meat when cooking on outdoor grill.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Grease and flour one loaf pan.
In mixing bowl, stir berries, eggs and oil.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring between each addition until well blended.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chocolate crinkle-top cookies
directions: In small bowl combine flour, baking powder and salt.
In small heavy saucepan over low heat, melt 1 cup morsels; stir until smooth.
In large mixer bowl beat granulated sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Beat in melted chocolate; beat in egg whites.
Gradually beat in dry ingredients alternately with water.
Stir in remaining morsels.
Cover; chill until firm.

title: turkey marinade
directions: Mix and pour over turkey pieces for grilling. Marinate 4 hours or overnight. Grill and baste.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: pineapple supreme
directions: Add crushed pineapple (with the juice) to marshmallows.
Stir 2 or 3 times and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
When serving, add whipped cream, if desired.
Decorate with cherries or nuts.

title: eclair pie
directions: Spread crackers over bottom of pan or baking dish (1 layer). Mix pudding and milk until thickened; fold in whipped topping. Layer 1/2 pudding on top of crackers, then layer graham crackers and other 1/2 pudding.
Top with 3rd layer of graham crackers. Spread crackers with chocolate frosting.
Chill and serve.

title: jane's cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Form into one large ball or two smaller balls.
Coat with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pear pickle
directions: Wash, peel and core pears.
Cut into quarters. Place at once in 1-quart water and 1 tablespoon vinegar added.
Combine sugar, 1 1/4 cup vinegar and 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil.
Add spices tied in clean, thin white cloth.
Cover and boil 5 minutes. Remove spices.
Add pears and simmer 2 minutes.
Pack pears in hot pint jars.
Add syrup to within 1/2-inch from top of jar.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath 20 minutes. Makes 3 to 4 pints.

title: meaty barbecue beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onions, drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes or until thickened.
Makes 6 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: country chicken or turkey stew
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Place on paper towel.
In drippings, cook onion.
Add soup, water, potatoes and carrots; heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Cover; cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in beans, chicken and bacon.
Cover another 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 cups.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Saute margarine; cut up onion and cut up celery, then add 4 to 6 tablespoons flour.
Add chicken broth and 1 package of cut up, cooked broccoli.
Heat and add 1/4 to 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese (cut up) and 1 to 1 1/2 cups of cut up sharp Cheddar cheese.
Heat 1 cup milk and 1 cup light cream together, then add it to mixture. Add 2 chicken bouillon cubes.
Add water or milk if a thinner consistency is needed.

title: hot cheese and crab dip
directions: Combine the crab meat and cheeses with skim milk; stir over low heat until cheeses melt.
Add Sauterne and crab meat; heat through.
Makes 3 cups.

title: raisin nut chunks*
directions: In medium saucepan, melt chips over medium heat.
Stir frequently.
When melted, add nuts and raisins.
Stir well.
Drop teaspoons onto wax paper covered cookie sheets.
Chill until hard.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix cream of mushroom soup, onion, egg and mayonnaise.
Pour over broccoli.
Lay cheese slices on top.
Melt margarine. Crumble Ritz crackers over cheese.
Pour melted margarine over crumbs.
Bake on 350° about 30 minutes until bubbly and brown.

title: homemade prewash
directions: Combine in squeeze bottle.
Shake before using.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add dates and nuts.
Add alternately with applesauce to the butter and sugar mixture.
Mix thoroughly and turn into a well-buttered and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: tamale pie
directions: Place the onion in a large pot with 1/4 cup water.
Saute about 10 minutes.
Add the green pepper, corn, green chiles, tomato sauce and 1 1/2 teaspoon chili powder.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add mashed beans and cook about 10 minutes over low heat.
Remove from heat.

title: green and white vegetable salad
directions: Remove large leaves of broccoli and cut off tough ends of lower stalks; discard.
Wash broccoli thoroughly and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Combine broccoli, cauliflower, celery and green onions in a large bowl.

title: hardtack candy
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine all ingredients, except powdered sugar.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook until "hard crack" stage is reached.
Remove from heat.
Add flavoring and food coloring; stir until well mixed.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on countertop or table.
Pour hot mixture over powdered sugar, making a thin layer.
Sprinkle more powdered sugar on top.
Cool and cut into small pieces with scissors.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar well.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add flour and milk a little at a time. Beat egg whites and fold into batter.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, then turn to 350° and bake another 30 minutes. Makes a large cake.

title: chicken succotash
directions: Steam chicken in chicken broth.
Add a few celery leaves. When tender, remove and cool.
Cover stock and chill.
Take chicken meat from skin and bones in generous pieces.
Wrap well and chill.
Measure 3 cups fat free broth and place in a large kettle.
Bring to a boil and add lima beans.
Cover and cook until almost tender.
Add corn, chicken, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Thicken broth.

title: wedding punch
directions: Boil 3 cups water and sugar.
Add package Jell-O; cool.
Add lemonade and water according to instructions on can.
Add pineapple juice and sherbet.
Mix Kool-Aid in 3 quarts water.
Add to fruit mixture; chill.
Add ginger ale.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together until very tender.
Drain off water.
Mash fine.
Add salt and pepper, cheese, butter, egg yolks and crackers, that have been crumbled very fine.
Beat egg whites very stiff and fold into mixture.
Cook in greased casserole dish until brown.

title: crumb cake
directions: Put all ingredients into a medium size mixing bowl; mix well. Pour into greased and lightly floured cake pan.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Blend pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Place one layer of crackers in bottom of pan.
Add 1/2 pudding mixture, another layer of crackers and rest of the pudding, then another layer of crackers.
Heat frosting, pour and spread on top of cake. Refrigerate for 2 or more hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans and soup; stir in 1/2 can onion rings.
Pour into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining onion rings and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: wedding punch
directions: Boil sugar and water.
Cool.
Put bananas in blender.
Add 1 cup pineapple juice.
Blend until smooth.
Mix bananas with remaining juices.
Freeze overnight in 3 equal containers. When serving, partly thaw juice and add 1 bottle ginger ale per container.
Serves 50.

title: grandma brown's mincemeat cake
directions: Add spices to flour and sift 4 to 5 times.
Cream sugar and butter and add beaten eggs.
Add a little milk and then flour until all is mixed.
Put mincemeat on stove and add a little water.
Cook until dissolved good.
Then add pecans and stir. Have the raisins washed and drained; flour them and stir mincemeat, pecans and raisins into the cake mixture.
Put in a big cake pan with tube and cook at 250° until done, usually about 3 hours or 3 hours and 15 minutes.

title: rainbow jello
directions: Dissolve blackberry jello with 1 cup boiling water and divide in half.
Add 2 tablespoons sour cream to one half.
Pour sour cream layer into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until this layer is set.
Set second half aside.
When first half is set, pour in remaining half of blackberry jello and allow it to set.
Repeat each flavor in the same manner.
(This takes several hours to prepare.)

title: homemade condensed sweetened milk
directions: Blend all together.
This equals 1 can condensed sweetened milk (like Eagle Brand).

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Mix cake mix as directed and bake.
Mix cream cheese and drained pineapple.
Pour onto crust.
Mix instant coconut pudding and milk.
Pour over last mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts and cherries.

title: quick mexican spread
directions: Combine Neufchatel cheese and chilies, mixing until well blended.
Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips or spread over warm tortillas or corn bread. Makes 1 cup.

title: amish dressing
directions: Bake at 300°, stirring often until vegetables are cooked and bread is not soggy.

title: old fashioned cocoa fudge
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in a large saucepan.
Add milk and mix.
Bring to a boil on medium heat, stirring continuously. Continue boiling until 325° is reached or the mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.

title: pineapple turnovers
directions: Mix flour, salt and margarine as for pie dough.
Combine sour cream, egg yolks and yeast and add to flour mixture.
Chill dough several hours or overnight.
Work with about 1/3 of dough at a time.
Roll out slightly thinner than for pie dough.
Cut into 4-inch rounds or squares and fill each with 1/2 teaspoon jam. Fold over and seal edges well with fork.
Make a couple of slits on top for steam to escape.
Brush with egg wash and bake at 375° until nicely browned.

title: baked beans and bacon
directions: Combine all ingredients in large microwave bowl.
Heat, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Liquid will thicken almost to a caramel state.
Let stand 10 minutes and serve.
Enjoy!

title: grandma's peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir milk and sugar over heat until starts to boil.
Turn heat to medium and boil until soft ball stage.
Let cool; don't stir. Beat with spoon until creamy.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Put in buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: two-tone rice
directions: Cook wild rice in 1 1/4 cups of the consomme for 10 minutes. Meanwhile, place white rice in a 1-quart baking dish in a slow oven (300°) to toast until golden brown.
Stir in the remaining 1 1/4 cups consomme, soy, minced onion and partially cooked wild rice. Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cousin gary smith's curry chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°, uncovered.
Turn off oven and let stand 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Split bagels.
Mix approximately 2 tablespoons Italian dressing with the cream cheese.
Add more if necessary to taste. Spread cheese mixture on bagel halves.
Top with thin slices of cucumber and sprinkle with dry dill.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cook beef in skillet over medium heat in hot oil until brown. Remove beef.
Add onion, celery, garlic, peppers and broth. Simmer for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Mix cornstarch and soy sauce.
Stir into vegetables.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add beef and heat through.
Serve over hot rice.

title: fresh fruit compote
directions: Pour milk and juice into bowl.
Add pudding; beat for 1 minute.
Add Cool Whip; beat 1 minute more.
Arrange 1/2 fruit in the bowl.
Add pudding mixture.
Top with remaining fruit. Refrigerate.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix taco seasoning and dip mix in with ground beef. Combine all ingredients. Cover and cook. The soup can be spicy, so diced tomatoes can be substituted for part of the Rotel tomatoes.

title: play clay
directions: Stir together baking soda and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Add water and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches consistency of moist mashed potatoes (approximately 10 to 15 minutes).
If cooked too long, finished ornaments may crack.
Remove and put on a plate.
Cover with a damp cloth.
When cool, pat until smooth.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: In a medium saucepan, pour Ro-Tel tomato juice (not tomatoes) and heat over low heat on stove.
Cut up cheese into squares and add to Ro-Tel juice.
(May need to add a tad bit of milk.)
Add remaining cheese and continue to heat until all of cheese is melted, adding Ro-Tel tomatoes and green chilies, stirring constantly.
Serve hot over your favorite tortilla chips.

title: sirloin tips
directions: Cut sirloin tips into strips.
Add the remaining ingredients. Cook in 300° oven for 3 to 4 hours, covered.
No salt needed.

title: mock cavatinni
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and add to Ragu.
Season sauce with spices to taste.
Pour cooked macaroni into large baking dish and cover with sauce.
Mix well.
Top with pepperoni and cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: cherry fajitas
directions: Place a small amount of butter or margarine in a skillet to melt.
Place tortilla in the skillet to soften, just a few seconds.
Place on a plate.
Spoon cherry pie filling onto the tortilla.
Roll.
Place several in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
(Can be warmed in the microwave.)

title: camper's cocoa
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, mix 1/4 cup mix with 1 cup hot water.
Makes about 70 cups.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Melt butter in large soup pot.
Add celery, onions and carrots.
Saute for 5 minutes, then add 2 tablespoons of flour into butter mixture until smooth.
Add water.
Then add bacon or ham for flavor.
Add cabbage and potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer until well done.
Enjoy!!

title: graham pralines
directions: Combine sugar and margarine.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool and break apart.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Cook
sausage
in a skillet until brown.
Stir to crumble; drain well and set aside.
Combine shortening and flour; mix well. Dissolve yeast in warm water; add sugar.
Let stand 5 minutes. Add buttermilk while stirring well.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Stir	just until ingredients are moistened. Knead in sausage.

title: texas hash
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and cook 15 more minutes.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Saute
onion
in
butter.
Stir
in
flour and cook one minute over low heat, stirring.
Gradually stir in sour cream, corn
and salt.
Cook over medium-low heat.
Stir until heated (do not boil).
Stir
in half bacon; pour corn mixture into a greased shallow
2	quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown 1 pound of hamburger; drain.
Return to skillet and stir in 15 ounce can of whole tomatoes, 3 ounce can tomato sauce, 1 envelope dry spaghetti sauce mix and 1 (12 ounce) can V-8 juice. Simmer 10 minutes.
(If it's a little soupy, sprinkle 1 or 2 tablespoons of flour into mixture to thicken.)

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Prepare pumpkin pie filling.
Place in
9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Sprinkle with yellow cake mix.
Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut steak diagonally across the grain into thin slices, then cut into strips about 2-inches long.
Heat salad oil in skillet over medium heat.
Place garlic clove and meat in oil and cook over medium heat, turning as needed until browned.
Add onion, green pepper, salt, pepper and ginger.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until tender.
Combine cornstarch with stock and soy sauce.
Stir into mixture in skillet.
Bring to a boil and cook, stirring until mixture becomes thick and clear.
Serve immediately over hot cooked rice.

title: blue ribbon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and nutmeg.
Set aside.
Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Add sugar gradually, creaming all the while.
Be sure to add sugar very slowly and beat hard.
Add eggs gradually.
Add all these ingredients to the flour, salt, baking powder and nutmeg. Beat thoroughly.

title: rice krispies cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together all ingredients.
Roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Chill 4 hours.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir contents of vegetable seasoning packet, margarine and water in bowl.
Add stuffing crumbs.
Stir until water is absorbed.
Mix gravy, chicken and vegetables in 2-quart casserole. Spoon stuffing over chicken mixture. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly (about 45 minutes).
Preparation time: 20 minutes.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: chinese chicken noodle soup
directions: Heat broth to boiling in large soup pot; add all ingredients. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Uncover and bring to boil; add vermicelli and cook over medium-high heat for 15 minutes.
Skim off any foamy particles.
Serves 8.

title: jalapeno and cheese french bread
directions: Split loaf of bread lengthwise.
Mix melted butter, mayonnaise and onions.
Spread mixture on bread.
Scatter sliced olives and jalapenos on top of mixture, then cover with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Cook for 5 hours at 250°.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant; slice in rounds.
Soak in salted water for 1/2 hour; drain.
Beat egg.
Combine with milk.
Dip eggplant in mixture; remove and roll in seasoned bread crumbs, flour or cornmeal.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: creme fraiche
directions: In saucepan, heat whipping cream to 90°.
Pour into bowl; stir buttermilk.
Cover, let stand at room temperature, for 18 hours. Do not stir.
Store in covered container in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: caramel layer choco squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine in heavy saucepan, first 2 ingredients.
I use the microwave, stirring some until caramels are melted.
Keep warm. Combine in large bowl, remaining ingredients except for chocolate pieces.
Stir with fork until dough is crumbly, but holds together.
Press 1/2 of dough into prepared pan; reserve remaining dough for topping.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes (do not overbake). Sprinkle chocolate pieces over baked crust.
Spread caramel mixture over all.
Combine reserved dough over caramel mixture. Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: snow peak frosting
directions: Bring corn syrup to a boil.
Combine egg whites and salt in a large bowl.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; continue to beat.
Slowly add hot syrup; add vanilla.
Continue beating until thick enough to spread.

title: stupid pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Fold in crackers and nuts. Bake in foil disposable pans for 30 minutes at 350°.
Chill and top with whipped cream.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix in bowl the flour, sugar, soda, salt and mashed bananas. Mix well, then add eggs one at a time.
Mix after adding each egg. Add oil last and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Be sure to grease and flour pan before adding cake mixture.

title: cheese and vegetable bread
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
To soften vegetable flakes, in small bowl, combine 1/2 cup boiling water and dried mixed vegetable flakes; mix well.
Let stand 3 minutes; drain well.

title: mint slush
directions: Wash mint very well and steep in 3 cups boiling water overnight.
Boil remaining water with sugar, then add lemon juice. Cool and freeze.

title: blondie's vegetable soup
directions: Place ingredients in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat to simmer about 1 hour.
Add shell macaroni during last 15 minutes, if desired.

title: salmon stew
directions: Heat salmon; add margarine, milk and pepper.
Bring to boil. Remove from heat and serve in bowls and add crackers as desired. Very tasty.

title: cookies and cream cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Line 24 regular size (2-1/2 inch) muffin pan with muffin cup liners.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Place cut up chicken in oven dish.
Layer broccoli on top. Stir together sour cream and undiluted soup.
Pour over broccoli. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: angel food cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Have ready a tube pan (10 x 4-inch), but do not grease.
Measure flour.
Stir flour and first amount of sugar together to blend.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Add next 6 ingredients; cook 15 to 20 minutes until onions are cooked and sugar dissolved. Add to large Dutch oven the beans; drain slightly. Combine with onions and sugar mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Can be done in crock-pot after onion mixture is cooked.

title: country ham
directions: In a large 12 inch skillet mix all ingredients, except ham. Cook and stir over medium high heat, until sugar and mustard are dissolved.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in melted butter. Add all ingredients together; if too stiff, add a little more canned milk. Cover top with grated cheese and bake in baking dish for 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.

title: county fair casserole(southern living)
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; drain well.
Combine ground beef, onion and seasonings in a skillet; saute until meat is lightly browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain grease.
Stir in cream of celery soup; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in macaroni and remaining ingredients.
Bake in a lightly greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish for 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 people.

title: pork and white beans
directions: Cut pork to bite size pieces.
Brown in a large frypan. Remove.
Add
margarine, apple, cabbage and onion to pan. Cook until
soft, stirring often.
Re-add pork and rest of ingredients. Cook
over low heat, simmering off most of liquid. Real good with corn bread!

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Can use Pam.)
Sprinkle nuts in pan. Cut each thawed loaf into 12 or 14 pieces.
Fill pan with single layer.
Heat together all other ingredients (don't boil); pour over dough.
Let rise in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in preheated oven at 350°, for 30 minutes.
Cool, then invert to serve.

title: rhubarb jello jam
directions: Mix rhubarb with sugar; let stand overnight.
Cook rhubarb until soft.
Add dry jello and Kool-Aid.
Seal in jelly jars and process or freeze.

title: sally's jello salad
directions: Make lime Jell-O with 1 cup of hot water.
Use the pineapple juice for the cold water.
If not 1 full cup, fill with water to get 1 cup.
Mix pineapple into Jell-O and let set in refrigerator. When set, mix cream cheese together.
If too thick, add a little mayo or milk.
Beat together cream cheese, nuts and Cool Whip. Spread over set Jell-O.
Cool.
Next, make strawberry Jell-O using 1 cup of hot water and 1 cup of cold water.
Pour over other 2 layers and cool.
You can also add strawberries or pears to strawberry Jell-O.
Top with mini marshmallows.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Do not grease cookie sheets. Roll in balls and flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lorna doone torte
directions: Whip together butter, margarine and 8 tablespoons sugar.
Beat in 2 eggs.
Gradually add 4 additional tablespoons sugar until fluffy.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Crumble cheese that is room temperature into a large bowl. Add pimento and juice to cheese.
Add mayonnaise gradually.
Mix at very low speed.
Add mayonnaise until you reach consistency you like.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Simmer celery and onion together.
Combine all ingredients and simmer for 8 minutes.
Add a little more milk, if reheating.

title: tuna-mac salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix lemon juice with milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Add fruits, coconut and nuts.
Put in graham cracker crust and chill overnight.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Mix remainder and add to creamed ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Batter can be frozen.

title: blt pasta salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, chili sauce, lemon, bouillon and sugar. Add pasta, tomato and onions. Cover and chill. Just before serving, stir in bacon and lettuce. Makes approximately 8 cups.

title: cranberry meatballs
directions: Use a crock-pot or large pan on stove.
Mix all ingredients except hamburger into crock-pot.
Roll hamburger into 1 to 1 1/2-inch size meatballs.
Add meatballs to mixture in crock-pot. Cook on medium to low heat until meatballs are cooked.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Chop water chestnuts.
Mix all together well.
Put into a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet memories sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° or 375°.
Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut and put on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake for 12 minutes or until brown; watch them very closely. Makes approximately 40 cookies.

title: easy time party squares
directions: Grease jelly roll pan, 15 x 10 x 1-inch. Cream oleo until soft. Gradually add sugar and beat well. Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour gradually. Add lemon juice or extract. Spread batter in pan. Lightly score into 20 pieces. Place 1 heaping tablespoonful of pie filling on each square. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. While warm, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drain spinach and add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: Toss together cereals and pretzels in a large bowl.
Melt almond bark over medium heat in a medium saucepan or in microwave after breaking into small pieces.
Pour over cereal mix and gently but quickly stir until covered.
Add M&M's and gently stir until covered.
Spread onto wax paper and let cool.
Break into smaller pieces for serving.

title: nutty noodles
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until brown.
Cook noodles in salted water until done; drain.
Add meat mixture, olives and cheese. Dilute soup with milk and water and add to meat mixture.
Mix well. Pour into casserole and bake 30 minutes covered at 350°.
Then sprinkle top with 1 can chow mein noodles and 1/4 pound nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes uncovered.

title: holiday cider
directions: Mix apple cider and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Let simmer 5 minutes; add orange juice.
Bring to full boil.
Serve hot.

title: enchilada stack
directions: Cook beef and onion in oil until meat loses its red color, breaking meat up so it's crumbly.
Stir in salt and chili salsa. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Arrange alternate layers of tortillas, meat mixture, sour cream and cheese in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts. Cut into squares to serve.
Top with salsa and sour cream.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: curry chicken salad
directions: Cook rice; dice chicken.
Mix curry with mayonnaise.
Toss all ingredients together.
Chill.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Butter bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line pan with whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding with milk.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour half of pudding mixture over crackers.
Put on second layer of crackers.
Pour on remaining pudding.
Add last layer of crackers.
Refrigerate for two hours.

title: oven-barbecued chicken
directions: Arrange chicken
pieces
in
ungreased	13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. In	medium	bowl,
combine	remaining ingredients.	Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake until
chicken
is
tender, about 30 minutes longer. Makes 5 servings.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and chill until syrupy.
Beat milk, which has been chilled several hours, until it forms stiff peaks.
Beat syrupy Jell-O until foamy, then beat it into the milk.
Cream cheese with sugar and vanilla; fold into beaten milk. Fold in crushed pineapple.
Crush crackers fine; add powdered sugar, then melted margarine.
Sprinkle 1/2 crumbs in a large rectangle pan.
Pour in cake mixture and top with remaining crumbs.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Makes 12 servings.

title: jen's strawberry surprise
directions: Prepare Jell-O as indicated on package.
Pour into a large bowl.
Let set in refrigerator until it begins to thicken.
When 1/2 way thickened, combine with thawed strawberries and 6 ounces of whipped topping.
Pour mixture over angel food cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.
Spread remaining whipped topping over dessert and garnish with strawberries.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Chop and drain artichoke hearts and mix with remaining ingredients. Spread in a glass baking dish and bake on 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Garnish and serve with chopped tomatoes and green onions. Serve with tortilla chips or favorite crackers.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Put 1 egg in measuring cup.
Fill to 1/2 cup with milk and mix into flour mixture.
Bake at 400° until brown or use for 2 crust pie.

title: miracle stew
directions: Season vegetables with salt and pepper. Place beef in Dutch oven. Add vegetables. Pour tomato soup over top; sprinkle with tapioca. Pour peas plus liquid over all.
Cover tightly and cook at 250° for 5 to 6 hours in the oven.

title: easy rice casserole
directions: Put all together in a baking dish that can be covered.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: smokey split pea vegetable soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy large pot over low heat.
Add carrots, parsnips, leeks, onion, thyme, marjoram and bay leaves.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes.
Add stock, peas and ham hocks.
Bring to simmer. Cover partially and cook until peas are tender and soup thickens slightly, stirring occasionally, about 45 minutes.
Remove ham hocks and cut into pieces.
Add to soup.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: cookies and cream pudding pie
directions: Place cookies on bottom and sides of pie plate.
Cookies should cover plate evenly.

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Add additional chips or walnuts, if desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash whole.
Drain and cut into quarters.
Set aside. In casserole pan mix margarine, eggs, pepper, salt, cheese, evaporated milk and onion.
Add cooked squash to mixture and mix together thoroughly.
Mix in cracker crumbs and stir together.
Top with sprinkles of cheese.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until light brown.

title: "one" easy rice
directions: Mix rice, both soups (without adding water) and butter in a casserole dish.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: beef and wine
directions: Brown meat in 2 tablespoons butter, no flour or salt.
Take meat out and pour in wine.
Let wine boil to let alcohol escape. Add meat and mushrooms and enough beef bouillon to cover meat. Add thyme, bay leaf, pinch of salt and the tomato paste.
Cover and put in 300° oven for two hours, stirring occasionally and adding beef bouillon if needed.
Heat onions in own juice and add to meat.
(If you should want to thicken juice at finish, make a paste of flour and butter and stir into meat.)
Serve on rice or noodles.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Mix jello in boiling water; add sherbet.
Let partially jell. Drain pineapple and fold in.
Add ready mixed Dream Whip.
Let chill and serve.

title: meaty nacho dip
directions: Cook chuck and sausage scrambled.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot and allow cheeses to melt; stir often.
Serve with nacho chips and hot peppers, if you like.

title: shoney boy pie
directions: Mix and boil until thick.
Add a pint of sliced strawberries. Put in precooked pie shell.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Roll out pie crust for a 9-inch pie.
Break Ritz crackers coarsely into pie shell. Combine water, sugar and cream of tartar in saucepan. Boil gently for 15 minutes. Add lemon juice and rind. Cool.

Pour syrup over crackers. Dot generously with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon. Cover with top crust. Trim and flute edges. Cut in slits to let steam escape. Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes until crust is golden. Serve warm.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Blend flour, butter and confectioners sugar thoroughly.
Press evenly in square (8 x 8 x 2-inch) pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Beat rest of ingredients together. Pour over crust and bake 20 to 25 minutes more.
Do not overbake! (The filling puffs during baking, but flattens when cooled.)
Makes 16 squares.

title: chili by dawn
directions: Scramble hamburger in skillet over medium heat until half done.
Add chopped onions and bell pepper.
Continue cooking until hamburger and onions are done.
Put hamburger, peppers and onions with other ingredients and simmer in boiler pan for 30 minutes.

title: hot peanuts
directions: Spread nuts in pan and roast 45 minutes at 300°.
Melt margarine; add other ingredients and simmer a couple of minutes. Pour on nuts and roast another 35 to 40 minutes, stirring frequently.
Spread on paper towels and sprinkle with salt.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix together the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Gradually add flour and walnuts.
Chill and shape into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet about 15 minutes at 350°.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and slice tomatoes 1/4 inch thick.
Mix salt and pepper to flour mixture, coat each slice well.
Fry in hot oil until each side is nicely brown.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a large skillet, saute the onion.
Stir in the remaining ingredients except the rice; bring to a boil.
Stir in the rice. Reduce the heat to low; cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes or until liquid is absorbed; stir occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Fluff mixture with a fork.
Garnish with cilantro and cherry tomatoes, if desired.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients together.
Thoroughly mix together and pour into hot cake pan with butter.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: sour cream baked beans
directions: Soak the navy beans overnight in water enough to cover them. Drain off water and add onion with 1 quart water.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 hour.
Add more water if necessary until tender, drain.
In deep casserole dish, add beans, salt, molasses, mustard and sour cream.
Mix well.
Add salt pork with rind exposed.
Pour enough boiling water to cover the beans.
Cover and bake at 300° about 3 hours, adding water if it evaporates.
Uncover the last hour to brown.

title: rice pudding
directions: Pour rice into rapidly boiling, lightly salted water. Cover and cook for 7 minutes. All water should be absorbed, and rice will be al dent. Add milk and butter. Stir gently until butter melts. Bring to a boil. Cover and cook slowly over low heat for 1 hour.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs well.
Add flour gradually, beating well.
Add vanilla, nuts, apples and cinnamon, mixing ingredients well.
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Let cool about 30 minutes, then turn onto cake plate.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Follow instruction on the cake mix box, using the ingredients called for by Betty Crocker.

Add the can of pecan-coconut icing to the batter, mixing well. Pour batter into a greased and floured bundt cake pan (or any kind of pan you wish to use) - again following the time suggested on the box of cake mix by Betty Crocker, according to the size pan you choose.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In medium bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, mix remaining ingredients until well blended.
Lightly coat muffin tins with butter or margarine.
Fill about 3/4 full with batter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until browned.

title: cheese cake
directions: Form crust in spring-form pan (9 1/2-inch).
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.
Chill.

title: momma's chili and cheese
directions: Grate cheese and toss with flour, salt and chiles.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Mix.
Pour into a 7 x 11-inch greased baking dish. Bake, uncovered, 45 to 50 minutes at 350°, until brown on top. Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: seafood salad
directions: Remove crusts from bread and butter both sides. Cut into small pieces, 16 cubes per each slice.
Combine buttered bread cubes with chopped onion and eggs and refrigerate overnight.
The next morning, add the remaining ingredients.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot fat until golden brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together; pour in pan.
Dot top with butter. Bake for 30 minutes or longer at 325°.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients into a separate bowl.
Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs and bananas.
Stir good.
Add dry ingredients. Stir good.
Add nuts, if desired, and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves (regular size).

title: excellent chocolate cake
directions: In medium size pot, put butter, water and cocoa.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Turn off heat. Add flour and sugar, stir until well mixed.
Pour into greased pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 33 to 35 minutes.
After removing cake from oven, frost immediately with Excellent Chocolate Frosting.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken; cut in chunks.
Cook broccoli per package instructions and drain.
Cover bottom of large casserole dish with broccoli.
Add chicken chunks.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour mixture over chicken and broccoli.
Top with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt oleo with oil.
Add marshmallows; melt and beat well. In a large bowl, put in popcorn, candied gumdrops and nuts.
Pour first ingredients over this mixture and stir well.
Pour in greased angel food pan and press well.
Let stand a few seconds. Turn pan over onto plate.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Combine the Ricotta and egg substitute in a small bowl and stir to mix well. Set aside. Put the ground beef in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Cook, stirring to crumble, until meat is no longer pink. Add the tomatoes, tomato paste, beans, chilies and chili powder and stir to mix well. Cook, uncovered, stirring frequently, for about 10 minutes or until the mixture is thick. Remove the skillet from the heat and set aside. Coat a 9 x 13 pan with nonstick cooking spray and line the bottom of the pan with 5 tortillas, slightly overlapping them. (You will need to cut one of the tortillas in half.) Spread half of the meat mixture over the tortillas, dot with half of the Ricotta mixture and top with half of the cheese. Repeat the layers using the remaining ingredients. Cover the dish with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Remove the foil and bake for 5 minutes more or until the dish is heated through and the cheese is melted. Remove the dish from the oven and let sit for 10 minutes before cutting into squares and serving.

title: dilly bars
directions: Beat above ingredients until fluffy.
Spread mixture on trimmed bread and stack 3 high.
Slice in thirds or quarters. Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken broccoli quiche
directions: Sprinkle broccoli, then chicken, then cheese evenly in the pie shell.
Beat eggs, cream, lemon juice, garlic salt and pepper until mixed but not frothy.
Pour into shell.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until center is set.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Spread beans thinly on a large, flat dish (about 14 to 16 inches).
These are available in vegetarian style if you like. Next, mix sour cream with mayonnaise and seasoning.
Spread this like a frosting over the beans.
Now comes the artistic part. Make the top of the plate into a target by creating circles of the following:
center olives, perhaps five or six across, next onions, then tomato and finally avocado.
I've found that it's nice to make a final outer ring of black olive slices that's only one slice deep.
This usually uses up the whole can.

title: steve's best ever biscuits
directions: Mix butter and flour in a large bowl with a fork until mixture is the consistency of "rice".
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Turn onto a well-floured board and roll to a 1-inch thickness.
Cut with a biscuit cutter and bake in a preheated 400° oven until golden brown.

title: oriental honey pork tenderloin with cashews
directions: In a large skillet, place garlic and tenderloin* and cook over medium heat.
Add cashews, honey and water.
Cook until water is reduced.
Add lemon juice and soy sauce.
Mix in Oriental vegetables and let simmer for 3 to 4 minutes.
Do not overcook. Allow vegetables to stay crisp.
Serve over rice.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Use a large round plate (12 to 14-inches).
Layer the ingredients in order of the recipe.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with nachos.

title: lemon ice* * * * *
directions: The shrimp recipe came from Southern Living when we were living in Texas.
The ham and broccoli biscuits are from a neighbor of our first apartment in Iowa.
Lemon Ice is from a friend of my mother's in Iowa.

title: christmas punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in hot water; cool.
Add juices; chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: spicy vegetable dip
directions: Blend ingredients together and chill.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: german meat loaf(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: *I use ground turkey and egg substitute.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Mix the night before.
Bake early next morning.
Together in bowl, combine warm water, yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
In a large bowl, mix milk, sugar, margarine, molasses, salt and 2 cups flour.
Mix until smooth.
Add 1 cup flour and the oats.
Mix.
Add flour to make soft dough.
Knead 10 minutes until smooth.
Add flour as needed.
Cover with plastic, then towel.
Let set 20 minutes.
Grease 2 (8 x 4 x 3-inch) loaf pans; divide dough.
Place in pan.
Brush top with oil.
Cover loosely with plastic.
Refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.
Remove; let stand 10 to 15 minutes before baking.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: quail with grapes and almonds
directions: Salt and pepper quail; roll in flour.
Saute in butter until browned.
Add wine and stock.
Simmer 15 minutes, turning several times.
Add grapes and heat just until the grapes are warmed. Place quail on a hot plate; spoon sauce over.
Arrange grapes around quail.
Sprinkle with almonds that have been browned in a little butter.

title: meat manicotti
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic; drain grease.
Add egg, 2 c. mozzarella cheese, bread and milk; mix well.
Cook manicotti according to package directions.
Stuff shells with meat mixture and place in a 9 x 13 pan.
Pour spaghetti sauce over shells and sprinkle with remaining mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350 degrees for 35-45 minutes.

title: one-eyed egyptian sandwich
directions: Squish out
a flat spot in the middle of bread the size of a half-dollar.
Tear
out
a
hole the size of a quarter in the middle of flat spot.
Melt butter in frying pan and cook 1 side of the
bread in it.
Take it out; put in more butter and put in the other
side of the bread.
Put the egg on top with the yolk in the hole.
Cook it awhile;
turn it over and feed it to a hungry kid.

title: buttermilk chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Place into large bowl. Pour buttermilk over chicken and add as much garlic salt, as desired.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 6 hours.
Remove from the buttermilk and roll in flour and deep fry.

title: hearty lentil-kielbasa stew
directions: Cut sausage in half lengthwise.
Cut into 1/4-inch thick half slices.
In a 4-quart pot with a lid, saute the sausage in the olive oil until lightly browned.
Add the onion, cabbage, celery and carrots.
Cover.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes, stirring once. Add the lentil soup and tomatoes with liquid.
Stir well. Simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Stir in dried parsley and a little garlic powder.
Cover and let sit off heat for 30 minutes.
Add more garlic powder if desired.
Reheat when ready to serve.
This is a great winter dish and easy to prepare.
I also add a few drops of Tabasco sauce to my bowl.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Cook garlic and onion in oil.
Add chicken and brown.
Combine paste, water, salt and pepper; pour over chicken.
Cover and cook over low heat until tender, 60 minutes.
Add mushrooms and wine.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and add milk.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt; place in top of double boiler.
Stir 1/3 of milk and egg mixture into dry ingredients.
Cook until mixture thickens; then add butter and vanilla.
Cool; pour into baked pie shell.
Put beaten egg whites on top and brown.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together well and refrigerate.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick and sausage.
Heat Cheez Whiz in microwave.
Add Cheez Whiz to Bisquick and sausage.
Heat oven to 425°.
Make balls.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Pressure cook or microwave chicken until tender.
Remove chicken from bones while the fowl is warm (easier to do than when it is cold).
Mince into small pieces.
(Pour off broth and use to cook rice in.)
Pressure or boil rice until tender.
Mix and warm chicken soup and milk.
Mix chicken, rice and soup mixture in one bowl.
Serve warm.
Serves 8.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Make alternate layers of potatoes, butter, cheese, flour and salt in buttered baking dish. Add milk and bake, uncovered, in hot 400° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and green pepper and then add all other ingredients and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer until thick and serve.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Combine flour and powdered sugar; add margarine, mixing well. Pat dough out in a 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Combine cream cheese, condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla; mix well and spread on cooled crust. Chill.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix together and pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake for 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Mix whipping cream, pet milk, condensed milk, vanilla, eggs, sugar, and ice cream mix.
Add Butterfingers.
Put in ice cream freezer.
Fill to fill line with milk. Process until frozen.

title: reese's balls
directions: Cream peanut butter and vanilla.
Add sugar and mix with hands. Make into balls.
Insert toothpicks and chill.
Melt chocolate chips and wax in a double boiler.
Dip each ball and place on waxed paper.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Spray 14 inch pizza pan with cooking spray.
With floured hands, press cookie dough into pizza pan to evenly cover the bottom.
Bake dough 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Cool cookie crust in pizza pan on wire rack.
In medium bowl, using a whisk, prepare instant pudding as label directs, but use only 1 cup of milk and add almond extract.
Remove cooled cookie crust to serving platter.
Evenly spread pudding on top of cookie crust.
Arrange fruits in attractive pattern on top of pudding.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix margarine, cheese, salt, red pepper and garlic powder. Add flour and mix well.
Roll into a roll and chill.
Slice and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit and add enough water to make 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Cook with all dry ingredients until thick.
Add all fruit and Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: irish brown bread
directions: Combine white flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut in butter until it is small pieces.
Stir in wheat flour and rolled oats.
Make a well in the center; add buttermilk and molasses.
Stir until thoroughly moistened.
Gather into a ball and place on a floured board.
Knead 5 times and shape into ball.
Pat into a circle.
Using a sharp knife, make a cross on top to allow expansion.
Place on slightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Loaf should be brown and sound hollow.
Brush bread with melted butter.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water mix.

title: captain's bars
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Melt chocolate, add shortening, stir until smooth.
Stir sugar into beaten eggs.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Add flour mixture and stir.
Add milk, vanilla and walnuts; stir.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Remove from pan.
Cut into bars.

title: carrot sticks au gratin
directions: Precook carrot sticks until tender (not quite done).
Place salt in carrots as they cook.
After cooking, arrange slices in bottom of square dish.
Spread diced bell pepper over slices.
Mix orange juice, brown sugar and finally milk.
Pour over peppers and carrot sticks.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over dish.
Cook until top mixture thickens.
Do not get real thick but until mixture soaks into the carrots.
Usually 20 to 30 minutes at 350° will be sufficient.

title: 10-minute strawberry shortcake
directions: Clean and quarter strawberries.
Mix sugar and berries together and let stand for 5 minutes to allow juice to form. Yields:
4 servings.

title: pineapple-chicken salad
directions: Combine cooked chicken, celery and pineapple.
Separately, combine 1/2 cup mayonnaise with dressing mix and 1/4 cup reserved pineapple juice.
Add to chicken mixture and toss to coat.
Great cool dinner on a hot summer day!
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spinach balls
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Chill 1/2 hour. Make small balls.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° on a greased cookie sheet.
Do not allow to brown.
May be frozen and then baked.

title: crunchy taco chip chicken
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange chicken breasts with thicker parts toward outside of dish.
Cover and microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes, until chicken is cooked through.
Remove chicken to plate; keep warm.

title: hawaiian beets
directions: In a saucepan combine brown sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Cut pineapple into small wedges.
Add to saucepan with the pineapple syrup.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add butter or margarine, lemon juice and sliced beets.
Cook over medium heat about 5 minutes or until mixture is heated through. Serves 4 or 5.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Mix in pan and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Boil cranberries in 1 quart water for 20 minutes.
Do not stir. Strain and add red hots, sugar and cloves.
Stir and boil until red hots dissolve, then add remaining water, orange juice and lemonade. Bring to a boil.
Serve hot or cold.

title: scrumptious baked squash
directions: Cook sliced squash in water.
Drain well and mash with potato masher.
Add all remaining ingredients, except 1/2 of the melted butter and the crackers.
Pour mixture into a nongreased loaf baking dish, then pour the rest of the butter and cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until brown.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy cheesy potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes.
When done, drain.
Set aside.
Heat soup; add margarine until melted.
Blend in sour cream, onions and cheese until melted.
Pour mixture over potatoes and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini-pineapple bread
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs, zucchini and oil.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Mix well. Add pineapple and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: new waldorf salad
directions: Toss ingredients together.
In a small bowl, stir salad dressing, yogurt and honey; fold in fruit.
Cover and chill for 2 to 24 hours.

title: stupendous lemon pepper chicken
directions: In bowl combine chicken breasts, lemon juice, the melted margarine, 1 tablespoon lemon pepper and 1 tablespoon seasoned salt.
Let sit 10 minutes.

title: english pea salad
directions: Heat together sugar, vinegar and salad oil.
Pour over drained vegetables.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in a graham cracker crust. Chill for several hours.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and margarine for crust.
Mix condensed milk, cream cheese and lemon juice.
Chill.
Layer crust, condensed milk mixture, cherries (hold out a few for topping) and Dream Whip, as directed.

title: school salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; shake well. Chill and keep refrigerated.
Shake well before using over tossed salad.
Yields 50 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles with oil in salted water for 15 minutes.
Drain. Combine beef, onion, green pepper and seasonings and cook until crumbly in oil.
Add tomato paste and water or tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes.
Blend eggs and cottage cheese.
On baking dish, put thin layer of meat sauce, then cottage cheese, then egg mixture, then Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked cherry dessert
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix and press into 13 x 9-inch pan cake mix, egg and butter. Mix confectioners sugar and cream cheese (softened).
Pour over first mixture and bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Don't peek into oven.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix in blender the first 3 ingredients until smooth; add remaining ingredients.
Chill until very cold.
Serve in hollowed out red cabbage (flatten bottom by slicing off a piece so it will sit straight).
Surround with fresh vegetables on a large platter. Makes 3 cups; 1/4 cup = 66 calories.

title: texas hash browns
directions: Mix all but corn flakes and butter in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until blended.
Stir in potatoes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter.
Stir in corn flakes.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Can prepare ahead and refrigerate.

title: orange julius drink
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend for about 35 to 45 seconds.
This is a cool, refreshing drink and great for any time of year!
Kids love it.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine apples, chicken or tuna, celery and pecans in large bowl.
Mix orange juice, mayonnaise and sour cream to make dressing.
Toss all together with dressing and lettuce.
Use only enough dressing to thoroughly moisten salad.
Use as much broken lettuce as desired.
Serve with crackers for a salad meal.

title: iced tea
directions: Use 10 to 12-cup coffee maker.
Place tea bags in basket and run water through.
Pour into gallon container.
Add sugar and fill to top with tap water.
Add lemon to taste.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together the night before needed. Chill and serve with raw vegetables. Can be served with round rye bread. Hollow out a 6 x 3-inch hole and put in dip. Use vegetables and bread with dip.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1 stick margarine and put in flat dish.
Crush croutons in plastic bag with rolling pin.
Mix crushed croutons, Parmesan cheese and garlic powder in another flat bowl.
Thaw and dry chicken breasts with a paper towel.
Dip each in first the melted butter and then the crouton mixture. Place in a single layer in a baking dish.
Pour a little of the remaining melted butter over the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, uncovered, until golden brown.

title: aunt may's relish
directions: Grind onion, cabbage, green tomatoes, red peppers and green peppers together and cover with salt and let stand for 2 hours. Drain.
Add sugar, celery, mustard seed, turmeric, vinegar and water.
Heat this all to boiling point and boil for 3 minutes. Pack in jars and seal.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Put all together; set in refrigerator for 3 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all the ingredients together well.
Eight rounded teaspoonfuls of tea mixture to 2 quarts of water.

title: no fry doughnuts
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, sugar, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, eggs, shortening and 2 cups flour.
Blend 1/2 minute at low speed.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in remaining flour until smooth.
Cover.
Let rise until double. Punch down, roll (1/2-inch thick).
Cut with doughnut cutter (floured).
Place 2-inches apart on a greased baking sheet.
Brush doughnuts with melted butter.
Cover and let rise for 20 minutes. Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fresh cranberry sauce
directions: Bring sugar and water to rolling boil.
Pour in cranberries, cook about 5 - 10 minutes (they will pop).
Take off heat, add mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Serve warm.

title: old fashioned pot roast
directions: Coat beef with 3 tablespoons flour.
In 8-quart Dutch oven, brown over medium heat in Pam or oil.
Cook well on all sides.
Add tomatoes, spices and 1 cup water.
Heat to boil.
Reduce to low, simmer 2 hours, turn meat occasionally.
Peel potatoes and carrots. Cut into bite-size pieces.
Peel onion, chop fine and chop celery fine.
Add to Dutch oven, simmer 35 minutes more until vegetables are done.
Remove roast to platter.
Arrange vegetables around roast.
In a cup, stir 1/2 cup water and 3 tablespoons flour until blended.
Add to Dutch oven liquid; cook, stirring until thickened. Makes 12 servings.
Contains 395 calories.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients over low heat.
Let stand 15 minutes while you bake a German chocolate cake mix according to directions.
Put 1/2 batter into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; top with chocolate chips, pecans and caramel mixture.
Put rest of cake dough on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
(Best to bake a day ahead so caramel sets.)

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Cool Hershey bar.
Then mix it into Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill good.
Can serve like this or top with Cool Whip.

title: easy brownies
directions: Mix ingredients by hand.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: bierocks
directions: Let frozen dough thaw to room temperature.
