Meanwhile, in skillet, cook ground beef, onion, garlic, salt and lemon pepper until beef is browned.
Add cabbage, Worcestershire and caraway seed.
Cook until cabbage is tender.
Drain off excess liquid.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Add green chilies or Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add a clove of garlic, if you want.
Serve with corn bread.

title: old time bread pudding
directions: Cut toast into cubes and place in greased, 2-quart baking dish.
Combine eggs, 1/4 cup sugar, salt, milk, water, raisins and vanilla in a glass bowl or 4-cup measure.
Microwave at High 1 minute.

title: tuna loaf with vegetables
directions: Combine tuna, potato chips, drained mushrooms, onion, pimento, lemon juice, pepper, egg and white sauce.
Blend and pack in an oiled mold.
Cover mold and place in the bottom of deep-well kettle.
Arrange vegetables around mold.
Add water and cover kettle.
Turn switch to high heat and when steaming freely, turn to low heat and simmer for 45 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Serves 6.

title: carrots au gratin
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter; toss with crumbs, Parmesan cheese and pepper, set aside.
Cook carrots, green pepper and onion in salted water until tender; drain.
Stir in remaining butter.
Top with the crumbs.
Serves 6.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Line bowl with lettuce or spinach leaves.
Combine all ingredients and put in bowl.
Chill.

title: broccoli salad parisienne
directions: Trim broccoli, split and slice into small flowerets and 1-inch strips.
Wash and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients in large glass
bowl.
Add
broccoli.
Toss
to coat well.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: aunt lil's sweet and sour beets
directions: Do not drain beets.
Heat to boiling point.
Mix sugar and stir in cornstarch and when smooth, add to hot beets.
Cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Add butter just before serving.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion until beef is brown. Drain.
Add taco seasoning as per package.
Spread 1/2 cup of salsa in bottom of ungreased square baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch). Mix remaining salsa, sour cream, soup and pimentos.
Layer half of tortilla strips, beef mixture, soup mixture and cheese all on salsa.
Then repeat.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add beaten eggs. Sift dry ingredients which have been mixed together alternately with coffee. Add apples, raisins and nuts. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until done.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until well mixed.
Bake in a tube pan, well-greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave hawaiian chicken
directions: Place chicken in a microwave-safe 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Combine soup, pineapple and curry powder in medium bowl; mix well. Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Cover and microwave on High for 11 minutes.
Rotate 1/2 turn at 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; saute vegetables in butter.
Combine noodles, tuna, mayo, vegetables and salt.
Blend together and heat soup, milk and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted; add to noodle mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered in 425° oven until bubbly, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chili beans
directions: Saute the green pepper, garlic, and chopped onions and add to the browned ground chuck.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 1-2 hours, stirring often.

title: peanut butter party mix
directions: Heat
peanut
butter
and oil in large shallow roasting pan in a 250° oven for 5 to 7 minutes or until soft and shiny. Stir
in salt,
garlic powder and Worcestershire.
Add cereal and peanuts; mix until coated.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towels to cool.
Yields 9 cups.

title: hearty black-eyed peas
directions: In a skillet, combine the first 10 ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover, simmer for 10-15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 2-4. Serve with salad, cornbread and dessert for a complete meal. Increase quantities for required number of servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Saute onion and garlic.
Add canned ingredients.
Then add chicken.
In casserole dish, layer tortilla chips, soup mixture and then Cheddar cheese.
Then another layer of the same.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with more tortilla chips.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Melt 2 sticks margarine with water and 4 tablespoons cocoa. Let come to a boil.
Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Pour first mixture in 2 beaten eggs, sour cream and baking soda.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes in a long cookie sheet pan.

title: cranberry-apple cooler
directions: In large saucepan, combine half of the cranberry juice cocktail and all of the cinnamon and cloves.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Remove and discard cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in remaining cranberry juice cocktail, apple juice concentrate and water.
Chill beverage for several hours or overnight.
Fill with ice cubes.
Garnish with mint leaves.
Makes 5 (12 ounce) servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix confectioners sugar and cream cheese together with a fork. Add creamy peanut butter, Cool Whip and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pilaf
directions: Brown noodles lightly in butter and add rice, broth and a little salt; bring to a boil.
Lower heat and continue to cook until broth is absorbed.

title: milano's cappuccino
directions: Mix liquors together and warm slightly.
Make Espresso and pour in glasses.
Steam milk and add to coffee.
Add liquor mix and stir.
Top with whipped cream.
Place cherry on top and do not eat until the end.

title: sunday dinner chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender; cool enough to cut into pieces. Set aside.
Cook noodles in the chicken broth.
Saute chopped onion and pepper in a small amount of oil.
Cube the cheese and mix all ingredients together.
Put in a baking dish; cover with foil.
Bake 2 hours at 200°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla; mix well. Stir in squash and pineapple, then flour mixture.
Just mix enough to spoon into pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: sweet and sour ribs
directions: Cover ribs with hot water in a large pot.
Cook over low heat with a lid for 2 hours.
In a separate 2-quart pot, combine remaining ingredients. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbling.
Line ribs into a large baking pan. Pour finished sauce over ribs.
Bake for 10 minutes in a 350° oven or microwave for 5 minutes. Cool for 15 minutes before serving. Serve with rice.

title: applesauce raisin cake
directions: Mix flour and spices together.
Cream sugar and shortening until light.
Add applesauce and baking soda mixture; mix well. Add flour and spices.
Mix well.
Add raisins last; bruise well with beaters.
Bake in a tube pan at 325°; after 1 hour keep checking.
This is a heavy batter; takes awhile to bake until done.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar, nuts, margarine and juice, mixing well with hands.
Form small bite size balls,
Roll in coconut.
Chill until firm.
Makes 60 balls.

title: apple dumplings(makes 6 servings)
directions: Make a syrup by combining 1 cup sugar, 3 teaspoons cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg in saucepan. Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Roll pastry dough out until it is about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into six (7-inch) squares.
Peel and halve apples, then remove cores. Combine 1/2 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, nutmeg and fill apple centers with this mixture.
Place an apple in the center of a pastry square.
Dot with 2 tablespoons melted butter and bring the points of pastry over apple to overlap.
Press dough together to seal.
Repeat with remaining apples.
Place 2 inches apart in baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: lazy woman cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients 3 times, then add liquid ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy onion rings
directions: Cut onions into 1/2 inch slices, separate into rings and coat with egg then with bread crumbs.
Place on buttered baking sheets. Broil 4 in. from heat 5 to 6 minutes or until golden brown.

title: toffee
directions: Cook ingredients over low heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture becomes thick and starts to change color, lower heat and cook until very, very thick and almost burned.
Pour on flat pan, like a cookie sheet, and immediately spread 1 cup chocolate chips over it.
As chips melt, spread smoothly with a knife.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: pecan pie #3
directions: Beat eggs with whisk (or fork, no beater). Melt butter (I put butter in Pyrex measuring cup and microwave until melted.) Combine sugar, flour and syrup and whisk until smooth. Add melted butter and beaten eggs to the syrup mixture; mix well, then pour into unbaked pie pastry shell and pour on pecans, without stirring. Place in preheated 350° oven and bake 45 to 50 minutes (to test, insert knife and when it comes out clean, it is done and pastry is slightly brown).

title: no egg chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Place in an 8-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter pudding
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt in a medium pot.
Add peanut butter and mix until crumbly.
Beat egg with a fork.
Put egg and milk in the pot, cook and stir over medium heat until mixture gets thick; then cook and stir 1 minute longer.
Stir in vanilla. Chill before serving.

title: devil dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet about 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool and spread filling
between 2 cookies, forming a sandwich.

title: fried rice
directions: Boil 1 cup of
water; add rice and set aside.
Brown mushrooms; add butter, onions and egg (scramble all).
Add rice to mixture and brown.
Add 1/3 cup water and soy sauce.
Heat 5 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In a large pot, combine chicken, water, peppercorns and bay leaves.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Skin and bone the chicken and cut it into large dices.
There should be about 4 cups.
Skim the fat from the broth, remove and discard the bay leaves and peppercorns and measure 4 cups broth.
Reserve remaining broth for another use.
Combine the broth with remaining ingredients and chicken and turn into a greased 2 1/2-quart round casserole.
Bake the casserole in a 350° oven for about 1 1/4 hours or until the broth has mostly been absorbed.
Serves 6.

title: aunt mattie's cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl. Make a well in dry ingredients and add all wet ingredients; stir well. Do not use a mixer.
Pour into oiled and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Scatter rice in bottom of rectangular pan.
Lay chicken on top and sprinkle dry onion soup mix over chicken.
Mix canned soup and water together.
Pour over all ingredients.
Make sure you do not season. Then cover tightly with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours in 325° oven.
Also may be prepared ahead of time, the night before or the morning it is to be cooked.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Fill the quart jars to within 1/2 inch from the top of jar with the boiling brine.
Cap each jar when filled.
Process 15 minutes in boiling water bath.
Boiling water should cover jars by 1-inch.
Start processing time count when filled jars are placed in rolling boiling water.
Use canner with tight fitting lid. Leave on high heat during processing.
Ready in 3 to 4 weeks.

title: banana muffins
directions: Beat salad dressing and sugar into bananas.
Stir in flour, soda and salt until moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yield:
12 large muffins.

title: scrunch
directions: Put cut up fruit in baking dish.
Mix sugar and cinnamon to taste.
Add to fruit.
Mix butter, sugar, oatmeal and flour together.
Spread over fruit.
Bake at 350° until fruit is tender.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage.
Add sausage and the rest of the ingredients into crock-pot.
Let cheese melt.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in water.
Add frozen juices. Stir until dissolved.
Stir in 7-Up just before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.
Serves 30 plus.

title: ham and egg wrap
directions: Layer scrambled eggs, finely diced ham and shredded Cheddar cheese on a tortilla.
Heat in microwave until cheese melts.
Roll up and eat.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil water.
Mix together brownie mix, water, oil and 1 egg in large bowl until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, one egg and vanilla in small bowl until well blended.
Pour over crust.
Bake 15 minutes; cool.
Top with fruit; drizzle with chocolate.
Garnish with mint leaves if desired.

title: blueberry grenadine pie
directions: Prepare pastry as directed except stir in 1/4 cup cornmeal with the flour.
Continue as directed for baked pie shell.
Place blueberries in pie shell.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, the cornstarch, salt and cinnamon in saucepan.
Stir in water.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in grenadine syrup and lemon juice.
Pour over blueberries.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Beat whipping cream and 1 tablespoon sugar in chilled 1 1/2-quart bowl until stiff.
Cut pie into wedges; top with whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings, 420 calories per serving.

title: french green beans casserole
directions: Prepare French green beans. Cook as directed on package. Sprinkle American cheese on vegetables.
Pour over a mixture of mushroom soup and Pet milk.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes. Take from oven and top with French fried onion rings.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until onions are crisp and golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: veg meat loaf
directions: Saute onion and pepper with margarine, then add rest of ingredients.
Mix small amount of brown sugar and ketchup together in bottom of a loaf pan to make the topping of the loaf.
Add mix on top of this and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hershey's chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add the flour mixture alternating with Hershey's syrup. Add vanilla and mix with mixer for 2 minutes. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes. Ice with Chocolate Frosting.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add water and taco seasoning. Lay crescent rolls in bottom of pie pan (ungreased); press to form a crust.
Sprinkle 1 cup of tortilla chips on top of crust, followed by beef mixture, sour cream, cheese, then remaining chips on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with taco sauce, if desired.

title: hush puppy
directions: Boil chicken.
When done, save broth and make meal and water mixture (runny).
Add to broth.
Cook until thick like pudding. Add onion, chopped up eggs and chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cherry jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the boiling water.
Add pie filling and pineapple and mix well.
Let chill until set.
When set, cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Mix cream cheese, eggs, vanilla and sugar together.
Place one wafer in bottom of foil cupcake wraps.
Fill 3/4 full with mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool and top with filling of choice.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill at least four hours.
Serve in hollowed out bread (onion dill is a great one) with the bread pieces and/or raw vegetables.

title: hot crabmeat appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients, except almonds, until well blended. Spoon into casserole or souffle dish.
Garnish with almonds.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve with fresh veggies or crackers.

title: fresh apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Mix juice, sugar, butter and lemon juice in small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it comes to a boil.
Combine cornstarch and water; stir well.
Add cornstarch to the juice mixture, stirring until this becomes thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat; cover and chill.
After chilling, stir in mayonnaise.

title: sweet smell of christmas(not meant for drinking)
directions: Mix and simmer in an open kettle, adding water as it evaporates.
Makes a nice aroma for your home during the holidays.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Melt butter; mix with sugar, milk, coconut, nuts and vanilla. Shape into balls and chill 1 hour.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Dip each chilled ball in this.
Use a toothpick to dip them.

title: corn-egg scramble
directions: Fry bacon in 10-inch skillet until crispy; drain off fat. Beat eggs; stir in corn.
Pour over bacon pieces in skillet.
Cook until eggs are thickened throughout but still moist.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: basic cookie dough(excellent for holiday baking and parties)
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift in baking powder and flour (sufficient amount of flour should be added so dough can be rolled out).
Roll out dough using plenty of flour on counter top and on rolling pin.
Cut out cookies and bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Cover bottom of pan or baking dish with rice.
Place chicken pieces on rice.
Mix soups together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cover dish with foil.

title: cherry delight
directions: Put in layers in order listed.
Do not grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: caramel pie
directions: Brown the 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Heat egg yolks.
Add milk, sugar and flour.
When sugar is browned and bubbly, add egg mixture.
Stir until thick.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Mix together and pour into crust.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make graham cracker crust in bottom of pan.
Beat eggs, butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar for 10 minutes and pour on crust.
Top with bananas.
Add pineapple (drained).
Cover with Dream Whip.
Garnish with cherries and pecans.

title: cream puffs
directions: Mix together the last 3 ingredients ahead of time. Cover and store in the refrigerator.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding and set aside.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and butter.
Add to pudding mix and then fold in Cool Whip.
Layer; start and finish with crushed cookies.

title: cheesy sausage muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center.
Combine eggs and milk; add sausage mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased miniature muffin pans, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately.

title: chili sauce(for hot dogs)
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour, covered.

title: beer(guiness-style stout)
directions: Use 4-gallon pot or large. Place flaked and roasted barley in a straining bag and add to 2 gallons of water.
Hold at 150° for 1/2 hour; remove bag and barley.
Add malt extract and stir until dissolved.
Bring to a boil and add hop pellets.
Boil for another hour.
Transfer to a 6-gallon fermenter and add water to total 5 gallons.
Cook to 75°.
Sprinkle yeast on top, close fermenter and shake for 1 minute.
Ferment for 10 days to 2 weeks. Siphon into bottling bucket, add corn sugar and bottle.
Leave in a cool dark place for 1-2 weeks and drink up! Keeps up to one year.

title: potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the warm water, then add and mix shortening, salt, eggs and mashed potatoes.
Add 2 cups flour at a time.
Turn into greased bowl until double in size.
Punch down.
Make rolls. Let rise 1 to 2 hours.
Bake at 450° until brown.
Brush tops with butter.
Serve.

title: chili con carne
directions: Cook hamburger on stove, mixing with a fork and draining the fat off.
Put mango, celery and onions in sauce; let simmer for 1 hour.
Add the tomatoes and tomato sauce; let it simmer.
Add the drained hamburger and chili powder; let simmer.
Add the kidney beans 15 minutes before done.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets and slip off the skins.
Mix ingredients for syrup altogether until sugar and salt are dissolved. Pour over beets. Pack in jars and seal.
Yields about 10 pints.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ring-a-lings
directions: Kolache dough:
Dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon of sugar in lukewarm water.
Heat milk to 150° to scald; remove from heat and add 1/2 cup butter to melt.
In bowl, beat eggs with salt, 1/2 cup sugar and orange (or lemon rind).
When milk is lukewarm (110° to 120°), add to egg mixture and mix in yeast mixture.
Add enough flour to make soft dough, not sticky and not too stiff.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Stir with wooden spoon.
Repeat 2 more times at 15 minute intervals.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix bananas until all mashed.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Spray bottom and sides of pan (bread pan) with cooking spray.
Pour mixture in pan and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain. Stir in butter, cheese and eggs. Put in the bottom of baking dish. Brown meat and drain. Add all other ingredients, except cottage cheese. Simmer for 10 or 15 minutes. Put cottage cheese on top of spaghetti in dish. Add the meat mixture to top of cottage cheese. Chill for 2 hours or let set in the refrigerator overnight. Bake, covered, for 1 hour. Uncover and sprinkle with 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, barely cover squash with water and cook until tender but not mushy.
Drain thoroughly in colander.
Set aside.

title: honey bun bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients as for pie crust.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons honey over and spread.
Bring water and margarine to a boil.
Add flour and salt all at once. Stir until a stiff ball forms.
Remove from heat and add 3 eggs, one at a time, and beat after each until smooth and glossy.
Stir in 1/2 cup honey and 1 teaspoon almond extract.
Pour and spread on crust.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped nuts on top.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Cool and then drizzle with icing made of sugar, almond extract and milk.

title: best ever cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add flour and eggs; beat well. Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown on top.
Makes 2 small pies or 1 large pie.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Brown chicken in 4 tablespoons margarine.
Take chicken out. Add pepper and onion to skillet.
Add rice, broth, salt and chili powder.
Bring to a boil and add 1 cup tomatoes.
Place chicken on top and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell peppers in margarine.
In bowl, mix both cans of corn, eggs and corn bread mix.
Stir all ingredients together and pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until firm and lightly brown on top.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese into chunks and melt.
Add can of tomatoes.
Mix until well blended.
Serve warm.
Crock-pot works well for serving.

title: fish dinner casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion and cook until soft. Remove pan from heat; stir in flour and then milk.
Return to heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened. Arrange fish and shrimp in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with parsley and mushrooms.
Pour half of the sauce over fish.
Top with layer of sliced potatoes and pour remaining sauce over all. Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: sour cream crescent rolls
directions: Scald sour cream. Stir in sugar, salt and melted margarine. Pour warm water in large bowl.
Sprinkle yeast over water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm cream mix, eggs and flour.
Mix until blended.
Cover tightly.

title: quick fudge pie
directions: Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Good topped with ice cream.

title: bean soup from the sea of galilee
directions: Chop onion and fry lightly in oil just golden brown.
Transfer to a large pot, along with the oil.
Add beef broth, beans, tomato paste, minced garlic, pepper, salt and parsley.
Add 2 cans of water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook for 20 minutes. Serve hot.
Serve with pita bread dipped in it.
This makes a hearty soup.

title: hush puppies
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Mix until mixture is a stiff consistency.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into deep fryer or pan about half full of hot oil.
Cook until Hush Puppies float and turn a golden brown.

title: perfect divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water and salt.
Stir until the sugar dissolves.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and boil 2 minutes. Uncover and cook to a soft ball stage or to 238°.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not too dry.
Slowly pour syrup over egg whites.
Beat until candy is cool and holds shape.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Allow to cool.

title: old-fashioned bread dressing
directions: Cook celery and onion in oleo over low heat, stirring occasionally until onion is tender but not brown.
Blend in dried bread and seasonings; toss lightly.
Add more seasonings if desired.
Pour broth or milk or water over mixture.
Makes enough to stuff a 14 to 18 pound turkey.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Keep in airtight container and keep refrigerated.
Will keep up to a week.
Great if made the day before you serve it.

title: speedy little devils
directions: Combine cake mix and butter.
Save 1 cup of this for topping. Pat the rest into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with peanut butter and then Marshmallow Creme.
Crumble remaining mixture over the top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: clam dip
directions: Rub mixing bowl well with cut garlic and discard.
Drain clams, reserving broth.
Blend ingredients well, adding reserved broth as needed for desired consistency.
(Add gradually, since 1/4 cup is usually more than enough.) Makes about 2 cups.
This is also good with sherry used for part of the liquid.

title: pineapple fizz
directions: Combine all ingredients and freeze in ice cube tray.
When ready to serve, place 3 or 4 cubes in a tall glass and fill with Fresca, Vernor's 1-Cal or your choice of flavored no-cal soda or club soda.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.
(For holidays, use colored marshmallows and red candied cherries.)

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
Mix in taco seasoning and water.
Simmer and cool.
Mix lettuce, cheese, tomatoes, and olives with hamburger mixture in a large bowl.
Just before serving add chips and enough French dressing to moisten.

title: linguini
directions: Cook linguini until tender.
Rinse with cold water.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Great for picnics!

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together veg-all, mayonnaise, cheese and butter pour into casserole.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: cinnamon-oatmeal pancakes
directions: Beat egg with hand beater in medium bowl until fluffy.
Beat in remaining ingredients except margarine until smooth.
For thinner pancakes, stir in additional tablespoon of milk.
Heat griddle or skillet over medium heat.
Grease griddle with margarine if necessary.

title: doozits
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir in peanut butter and syrup. Mix well.
May have to use hands!
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls. Shake or roll in powdered sugar.

title: pepper cube steak
directions: Place steak on greased cookie sheet.
Brown under broiler. Place in greased cake pan.
Sprinkle with pepper and seasoned salt.
Place onion and green peppers on top.
Pour a little water on bottom.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: skillet peanut butter fudge
directions: If
you
have
an electric skillet set control at 280°. If using regular skillet combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk. Bring
mixture
to	a
boil.
Boil	5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn
off
heat.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla;
stir
until
marshmallows and peanut butter are melted and
blended.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch square pan. Cool.
Cut into squares.
About 2 pounds.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and save broth.
Do not use skin.
Cut chicken small and put in bottom of buttered casserole dish.
Mix the celery soup, chicken soup (no water) and 1 cup sour cream together.
Put over chicken.
Put the stuffing over soups.
Mix 1 cup chicken broth and the butter (melted).
Pour over stuffing. Heat.

title: the next best thing to robert redford dessert
directions: Mix together flour, butter and pecans until crumb-like.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until golden brown (350°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 of the topping.
Whip.
Spread over cool crust.
For the top layer, mix pudding mixes with milk until thickened.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread remaining topping over top and sprinkle with grated chocolate bar.
Refrigerate until served. Serves 16.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except croutons.
Put mixture in a lightly greased casserole.
Top with croutons and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Sift flour once.
Measure and add dry ingredients, then sift 3 times.
Cream butter thoroughly, gradually adding sugar.
Cream well.
Add egg, nuts and raisins.
Stir well.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream.
Drop by teaspoonful on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: country chicken and stuffing
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
In a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish, combine soup, sour cream and chicken.
Top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 7 to 8.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325° to 350°.
Cream together sugar and butter. Mix ingredients together in order listed.
Can be rolled out or dropped.
Bake until slightly brown.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Fry hamburg; drain fat.
Put in crock-pot.
Add potatoes, carrots, corn, peas, green beans and pack of onion soup mix.
Cook on low.

title: chipped corned beef rolls
directions: Lay beef flat on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate.
Combine remaining ingredients.
If necessary, add a little milk for spreading consistency.
Lay 2 slices of beef side by side, overlapping a little.
Spread mixture over; roll together.
Refrigerate again (about an hour).
Before serving, slice and insert picks.

title: butternut squash soup
directions: Heat oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add onions and garlic with a little bit of salt and fry until brown. Add curry powder, mixing it with the onions until the spice has heated and gives off a spicy fragrance. Put in squash and potatoes, and mildly braise them. Add just enough vegetable stock so that the squash and potatoes are submerged in the stock.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until crumbly.
Press into 9-inch pan using 1/2 of crumbs. Top with rhubarb.
In a small saucepan combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; boil 3 minutes. Mixture will be thick and clear.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: judy's dressin'
directions: Debone boiled chicken or hen.
Mix cornbread with chicken broth.
Leave it pretty moist (not dry).
Add canned soup, chopped celery, bell pepper, green onion and regular onion.
Add eggs and spices and deboned chicken.
Bake slow couple of hours until brown on top.

title: sausage swirls
directions: Let sit until room temperature. Mix together and divide into two balls

title: wonderful stuffed potatoes
directions: Prick potatoes with fork.
Bake at 425° for 60 minutes, or until fork is easily inserted.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise. Carefully scoop out potatoes, leaving about 1/2 inch of pulp inside shell.
Mash pulp in large bowl.
Mix in by hand the remaining ingredients, except Parmesan cheese.
Spoon mixture into potato shells.
Sprinkle top with 1/4 teaspoon Parmesan cheese. Place on baking sheet and return to oven.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until tops are golden brown.

title: filoses or malasadas(sweet doughnuts)
directions: Heat the cinnamon in the milk.
When it reaches the boiling point, remove from heat and allow it to cool to lukewarm temperature.
Remove the cinnamon sticks.
Moisten the yeast with lukewarm water.
Add the yeast, salt, sugar and melted butter to the warm milk.
Gradually add the flour, stirring continuously to prevent lumps from forming.
Add the eggs and continue stirring to form a soft dough.
Cover and place the dough in a
warm place for two to three hours until it doubles in size.
Drop by tablespoon into deep fryer or oil heated to 350°.
Fry until the pieces are evenly browned.
Remove and drain them on paper towels.
Roll the filoses in honey and sugar (or just sugar) and serve warm.
Yields 24 doughnuts.

title: chicken muenster
directions: Marinate chicken in beaten eggs 6 to 8 hours or overnight. Drain chicken and coat with bread crumbs. Brown in oil in skillet. Put chicken in casserole pan. Top with mushrooms and cheese. Dissolve 1 chicken bouillon cube in cup of water. Pour over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, milk, eggs and chips in large bowl.
Mix by hand until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed. Do not overbake.
Cool 15 minutes in pan before removing.

title: diabetic oatmeal cookies
directions: Whip dry milk with ice water for 4 to 5 minutes or until stiff peaks form.
Boil raisins in water for 2 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Combine margarine, brown sugar, egg and vanilla; beat for 1 minute at medium speed.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add liquid from raisins.
Add to egg mixture and beat for 2 minutes at low speed.
Fold in rolled oats and raisins.
Fold in whipped dry milk.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.
Each equals 1/2 bread plus 1/2 fat exchange.

title: quick cheese bread
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add grated cheese.
Beat together the eggs, milk and oil; add them to the dry ingredients and blend delicately.
Grease a bread loaf tin and pour mixture into it.
Bake for 55 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mincemeat diamonds
directions: Combine hot water and raisins.
Combine all ingredients and mix.
Add raisins and water, nuts and mincemeat last.
Spread on greased cookie sheet and bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Frost, if desired, and cut in squares.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 7 minutes at 400°.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw and drain the spinach.
Mix with other ingredients in order listed.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Store in plastic bag after they are frozen.
Bake from freezer at 375° for 17 to 20 minutes.
Makes 65.

title: crab-filled mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; discard stems.
Steam mushroom caps in steamer for 3 minutes; drain.
Drain and chop crab meat. Combine crab meat, bread crumbs, sour cream, melted margarine, green pepper, sherry, mustard and hot pepper sauce in bowl.
Mix well.
Stuff each mushroom cap with mixture.
Place in 10 x 15-inch baking dish.
Chill, covered, for several hours to 24 hours.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes or until heated through.

title: millie's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine first 6 ingredients.
In a 2-quart ovenproof dish, spray Pam to coat. Place meat mixture inside and shape into loaf.
Pour undiluted soup on top of meat mixture.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk to make a stiff dough.
Roll out on floured board 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into 2-inch strips.
Drop into boiling chicken broth. Cook until dumplngs are tender.
(Cook, covered, then uncover.)

title: chicken liver special
directions: In an iron skillet, fry liver slightly.
Do not overfry.
(Mix flour, salt, pepper and garlic salt in a bowl).
Roll chicken livers until covered; then fry.
Add onion until tender (chopped). After hot and onions are tender, add 1 can drained mushrooms. Heat until hot; sprinkle flour into mixture and stir as if you're making gravy.
Add Mrs. Dash.
While hot, stir in hot water until smooth and thick.
Add more water, if too thick.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Serve on rice or toast, or by itself.
Delicious!

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugars together.
Beat in eggs, flour, salt, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix in chocolate chips, oatmeal and raisins. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 8 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
You will need pastry for a 9-inch pie and pricked so it won't puff.
Bake until light brown, set aside to cool.
Reduce oven to 375°.

title: snack
directions: Mix soup crackers and oil.
Add dressing and dill weed.
Mix well, tossing and refrigerate at least 1 1/2 hours.
Keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: chocolate rice krispies treats with peanut butter
directions: Melt margarine in a large pot.
Mix in marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Melt.
Take off heat.
Add peanut butter chips. Add Rice Krispies to desired texture.
Put in a 9-inch pan and let cool.

title: aunt juanita's relish
directions: Wash and drain vegetables.
Scald, core and peel ripe tomatoes; core, but do not peel, green tomatoes.
Chop vegetables and mix all ingredients and cook until about as thick as chili sauce.
Taste and add more seasonings if desired.
Pour boiling hot relish in hot, dry jars and seal with hot lids.

title: meat loaf #1
directions: Mix all ingredients
and top with catsup.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: turkey breast in lemon sauce
directions: Lightly sprinkle turkey breast with salt and pepper.
Place in shallow roasting pan.
Mix butter and lemonade concentrate.
Pour evenly over turkey.
Cover with foil loosely to allow circulation. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: kentucky butter cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Blend eggs into butter/sugar mixture one at a time.
Combine buttermilk and vanilla and combine alternately with dry ingredients.
Blend well after each addition.

title: low-sodium chicken salad
directions: In a big bowl, mix chicken, celery, parsley and onions. Combine dry mustard, pepper, lemon juice and mayonnaise, mixing well.
Add to chicken mixture and stir until well mixed.
Chill. Serves 6; approximately 153 mg sodium.

title: sugar-free punch
directions: (Use formula to make as much as you wish.)
Refrigerate juice and ginger ale, and add ginger ale just before serving to give the punch sparkle.
You can float thin slices of lemon, lime or other fruit on top.

title: sweet 'n tangy barbecue dip
directions: Heat until jelly melts and blends with barbecue sauce.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Bring to a boil.
Add vegetable mixture and simmer 30 minutes.
Pack into hot, sterilized pint jars.
Seal.
Yields 6 pints.
Excellent to use wherever sweet pickle relish is used.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender except the second half cup of oil.
This must be added last, slowly while blending.
Makes 2 cups.
Goes well with spinach salad.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add strawberries.
Break apart with fork.
Add pineapple.
Put half in mold; refrigerate and let set about 1/2 hour.
Leave rest on counter.
Spread sour cream over it when it's set.
Then put rest of jello on top of that and refrigerate.

title: spoon dumplings
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together flour and salt.
Make well in center.
Mix eggs and milk together and pour into well.
Mix well with fork.
Tilt bowl over large pot of boiling salt water and with a sharp knife, cut off small pieces of batter into water. Cook until dumplings puff and rise to top of water (about 5 minutes).
Remove and drain in colander.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw spinach.
Drain and squeeze out all excess moisture. Blend in other ingredients.
Shape into small balls (approximately 40).
Refrigerate or freeze.
Bake on a lightly greased baking sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with Spicy Mustard Sauce.

title: low-fat biscuits
directions: Into
mixing
bowl, put flour and baking powder and mix together.
Pour
oil and buttermilk into cup and add gradually into
flour
mixture.
Blend
with fingertips until moistened. (Add
small
amounts of milk/oil mixture to flour until all is used.)
Put
onto
floured
wax
paper.
Pat out with hand for desired
thickness.
Cut
with floured cutter.
Bake on cookie sheet
or
pan that has been greased with canola oil.
Bake at 450°
for
to 10 minutes, until brown as desired.
Makes 10 large biscuits.

title: shrimp fettuccine
directions: Cook garlic in butter and olive oil.
Add vegetables.
Cook and stir about 5 minutes.
Stir in shrimp, seasonings and wine. Cook and stir on high 1 minute or until shrimp is thoroughly heated.
Serve over hot fettuccine.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Fry bacon crisp. Cool and crumble. Set aside.
Steam chopped onions and chopped celery until tender. Set aside.
Lightly sprinkle bottom of a baking pan with garlic salt.
Place halibut fillets in pan.
Sprinkle again with garlic salt, white pepper and Johnnie's seafood seasoning.
Top each fillet with onion/celery mix and bacon crumbles.
Pour evaporated milk over each fillet to completely moisten each fillet.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until fish flakes and is no longer translucent.
Serve with slice of lemon on top.

title: gator's slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and carrot.
Add salt; let stand 1 hour.
Heat vinegar, water, sugar and seeds.
Let come to a boil; cool. Squeeze juice out of cabbage, then add vinegar mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Keep refrigerated.

title: easy fruit salad for a crowd
directions: Add all ingredients together and refrigerate before serving.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased and floured baking dish.

title: pine bark candy(oven: 400~)
directions: Line a cookie sheet with aluminum foil (and sides).
Completely cover bottom with saltine crackers in one layer.
Melt the butter in a saucepan.
Add brown sugar.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour sugar mixture over crackers.
Spread well to cover all surfaces.
Bake 7 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately spread on the chocolate chips.
Spread evenly with spoon or knife (they will melt). Refrigerate for an hour or until chocolate is firm.
Peel off foil and break into pieces.
(Freezes well.)

title: raisin cookies
directions: Combine raisins and water in a small saucepan; bring to boil and cook for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool.
Do not drain. Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Mix.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Easy to remove. Enjoy!

title: penocha pecans(appetizer)
directions: Cook to a soft boil.
Stir in the pecans until well coated and cool.
Separate each nut from the others.

title: italian salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar and shake well.
Chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in oleo until very tender.
Cook frozen broccoli until very tender.
Add remaining ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 10 to 20 minutes.
(Add whole can of mushroom soup, another package of broccoli and another cup of rice to make larger casserole.)

title: sour cream apple crisp
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Beat egg slightly. Add sour cream and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients and stir well. Add sliced apples and stir well to coat all pieces.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Place casserole in a pan of water in a 350° oven.
Bake for 35 minutes.
In the meantime, make topping.

title: hash brown potato dish
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potatoes.
Mix thawed potatoes into mixture.
Mix 2 cups corn flake crumbs with 1/2 cup soft oleo; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 400°, uncovered, for 40 minutes. Can be frozen for later dinners.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add liquids.
Beat with mixer for at least 5 minutes, adding flour as you beat until it is too stiff for beater to turn easily.
Remove beater and add more flour, using a spoon, until it is firm.
Flour board and place dough on it.
Knead enough to form a smooth ball and roll to about 1/2-inch thickness and cut into biscuits.
Dip each biscuit in melted margarine.
Fold in half and let rise until doubled.
Bake in 450° oven.
Makes about 30 to 35 rolls.

title: divinity
directions: Boil together the
sugar,
syrup
and
hot water.
When this forms a soft ball
dropped	in cold water, pour 1/4 of it on egg whites.
Return
the
remaining
syrup
to the fire and cook until the mixture forms
a stiff hard ball in cold water. Then pour over the first mixture.	Add nuts and vanilla.
Beat well and pour into buttered dish.

title: mandarin chicken
directions: Rinse, pat and dry chicken. Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken.
Cook 2-3 minutes on both sides.
Drain oranges and save juice. Set oranges aside.
Mix orange juice and remaining ingredients.
Stir well and pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add oranges and simmer an additional 5 minutes or until tender.
Serve over rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: monster cookies(great for girl scouts or boy scouts)
directions: Mix in order given.
Use your hands to mix or a heavy spoon! Make big cookies or make batter into shapes.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes (time depending on oven).

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in covered casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.
Small can of chopped mushrooms may be added, if desired.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes.
Mix with sour cream, mayonnaise, cheese and lemon juice.
Sprinkle top with parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350 degrees until it bubbles. Serve with crackers or chips. Also good on baked potatoes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all together until soft dough and drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Melt 1/4 cup butter and garlic powder to taste, then brush on cooked biscuits.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine.
Pour into a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 325° until brown, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients all together. Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon all together. Add to mixture. Add oats, nuts and vanilla. Bake in 350° to 375° oven on ungreased cookie sheet until lightly browned, 10 to 12 minutes. Do not overcook.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Line bottom of container (10 x 13-inch) with graham crackers. Mix milk with pudding and beat until set.
Fold Cool Whip into the pudding mixture.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over graham crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers and rest of pudding mixture.
Top with one more layer of graham crackers, covering pudding mixture completely.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, spread milk chocolate icing over graham crackers.

title: raisin pie
directions: Combine lemon juice and rind, orange juice and rind, sugar, raisins and 1 1/4 cups water and heat to boiling.
Mix flour and remaining 1/2 cup water to a smooth paste and add to mixture gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook 5 minutes.

title: tea biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Work shortening into flour.
Add milk until you get a nice soft dough.
Do not overmix.
Cut with cookie cutter.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown meat in oil. Add onions and cook until tender. Add seasonings, soup, tomatoes and rice. Simmer 5 minutes. Pour in long, flat casserole. Garnish with cheese and olives. Broil until cheese is melted. Serves 6 to 8.

title: upside-down meat loaf
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together and pour into roasting pan. Combine and mix remaining ingredients together thoroughly.
Press into pan over ketchup-sugar mixture.
After baked, turn out upside down onto platter, slice and serve.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine milk, Cool Whip and lemon juice until well mixed. Fold in crushed strawberries.
Pour in baked shells and chill.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, over high heat, heat potatoes, with enough water to cover, to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes, until potatoes are fork-tender; drain.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add liquids and eggs, one at a time, whole.
Mix by hand.
Don't beat.
Put in a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown and toothpick comes out clean when inserted.

title: cheese balls
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Mix together all ingredients. Sprinkle with cayenne pepper and salt.
Let chill.
Roll into balls and roll in chopped pecans or parsley until well coated.

title: butterfly lamb with rosemary
directions: Place lamb in shallow pan.
Combine oil, lemon juice, rosemary, pepper and bay leaf.
Blend well and rub mixture all over the lamb.
Cover and let stand for 2 hours or longer.
Put in a cool place.
Turn meat occasionally.
Prepare grill.
Place lamb on grill and grill to desired degree of doneness.
Turn meat several times as it cooks.
Cooking time will depend on distance of meat from heat.
It should vary from about 20 minutes for rare meat to 40 minutes for medium well done.
Let stand for 20 minutes, covered with foil.
Serve sliced.

title: beef and eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant in cubes and cook until tender with the celery (about 10 minutes).
Drain well in colander.
Brown beef in oil with onion and green pepper.
Drain off any excess fat.
Add flour and seasonings and tomatoes and simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir all together with cheese and bake in casserole at 350°, uncovered, for 30 to 45 minutes.
Add additional cheese on top.
This is good made ahead.
Serve with green salad and French bread.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: english trifle
directions: Cream sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Fold in flour.
Gently add milk.
Microwave 6 minutes.
Cool.
Place sponge in base of a large glass bowl.
Sprinkle on sherry (be generous).
Drain fruit and place on top of sponge.
Make up and pour on jello.
Chill until set.
Make up custard.
Cool slightly and pour over jello.
Chill until set.
Top with whipped cream.

title: gail's olive salad
directions: Drain all ingredients.
Put in salad bowl.
Use Zesty Italian salad dressing or dressing of your choice.

title: sausage noodle surprise
directions: You will also need some toothpicks.

title: chocolate nut drops
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, chocolate, eggs and vanilla together. Then add dry ingredients and milk.
Add nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.
Cover with icing.
(May add a few drops of food coloring to vanilla frosting; great for kids parties.)

title: sally's poppy seed bread
directions: Blend all ingredients. Beat 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cheese custard
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into prepared pie shell and bake at 350°
until done.

title: pasta-in-a-pot
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add Ragu, tomato sauce and meat.
Mix well and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook shell macaroni; drain.
Put half of the macaroni in a large pot or casserole.
Cover with half of the meat sauce, half of the sour cream and top with Provolone cheese.
Repeat with remaining macaroni, meat sauce and sour cream. Top with Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake until browned.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix salmon, bread crumbs, eggs, 1/2 cup milk, onion, paprika, salt and pepper.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peppered pork
directions: Roll pork in pepper to coat.
Place in flameproof roasting pan.
Roast in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, until cooked through and internal temperature registers 160° on instant red thermometer.

title: boston pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with liquid.
Turn into pans lined with tinfoil for easy removal.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: harvard beets
directions: Remove the skins from beets; trim and dice.
In saucepan combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Blend in vinegar and jelly. Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until thickened and smooth.
Add butter and beets.
Simmer 10 minutes stirring occasionally.
Garnish with orange peel.
Serves 6.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook Rice until form holds. Add Milk and cook until thick. Mix into Egg the Sugar and Vanilla. Add Raisins. Combine all mixtures in a double boiler. Cook 5 minutes to reheat. Sprinkle with Cinnamon or Nutmeg.

title: state fair doughnuts
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix milk, sugar, oil and eggs and add to dry mix.
Add all ingredients together and beat thoroughly.
Place dough in a greased bowl.
Cover and chill. Knead dough and roll out and cut.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Fry in hot grease until brown.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook ground beef until well done and crumbly.
Place cooked ground beef in the bottom of a greased baking dish.
Drain carrots and peas.
Pour over ground beef. Cover all of this with a layer of mashed potatoes.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes, or until potatoes are golden brown.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Place in a greased casserole dish. Prepare white sauce from butter, flour, milk, salt and pepper by mixing over medium heat.
Add chopped onion and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour.
Uncover and continue baking until golden brown.

title: no foolin' fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in saucepan.
Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling exactly 5 minutes on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter chips until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and let cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares. Yields about 3 pounds.
Do not refrigerate.

title: mt. vernon cherry nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, cherries and nuts last.
Blend until moistened.
Bake at 350° in greased loaf pan for 1 hour.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening, eggs and potatoes.
Mix in flour with hand until dough is easy to handle.
Knead on lightly floured board until smooth and elastic.
Place greased side up in greased bowl.
Cover with damp cloth, place in fridge 2 hours.
Shape dough into crescent rolls. (Divide dough into 2 circles and cut into triangles and roll into crescent rolls.)
May also shape dough into 2-inch balls, place in greased muffin cups.
Cut each ball in half and then in quarters. Cover and let dough rise until double (2 to 3 hours).
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: cake doughnuts
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and Crisco.
Add milk.
Mix together the flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add to first mixture; stir until smooth.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness on a floured surface.
Dough will be soft.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter. Fry doughnuts in oil heated to 365°.
Turn and fry on both sides to golden brown.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
If desired, while still warm, sprinkle with powdered sugar or granulated sugar.
Cinnamon may be added for added flavor.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix together in casserole dish and top with Pepperidge Farm dressing and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until heated through and bubbly.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: pesto
directions: In a mortar and pestle, or in food processor, mash together the pine nuts, basil and garlic.
Add cheese and butter; blend. Dribble in the olive oil, mixing until you have achieved a paste. Add pepper.

title: cornmeal mush
directions: Mix cornmeal with cold water.
Stir into boiling water with salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Cover and cook over a defuser (if you have one) or very low heat until very thick.

title: spinach dip
directions: Take sour cream, vegetable mix, water chestnuts and 1/2 cup mayo and mix together.
Let sit while you defrost spinach.
After defrosting spinach, drain water by soaking it up with paper towel, then add spinach to the rest of mix and stir up.
Let the whole mix sit in fridge for 2 to 3 hours to let herbs moisten.
Take Hawaiian bread and cut out the top of bread.
Put mix inside the middle and use the bread to dip.
You can use any other type of bread to use as dip also.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Combine all and bake in a 350° oven, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift together flour and 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat eggs and salt until frothy.
Add cream of tartar to whites; beat until stiff but not dry.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar at low speed, scraping sides of bowl often.
At low speed add vanilla and flour and sugar mixture until blended.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Invert pan until cake is cold.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise.
Place cut side down in microwave-safe 2-quart baking dish and cover.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes until nearly tender.
Scoop out pulp, leaving a 1/4-inch thick shell.
Finely chop pulp and set both shells and pulp aside.

title: ribbon fantasy fudge
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, 6 tablespoons margarine and 1/3 cup milk in a heavy pot.
Bring to a full boil and continue boiling for 4 minutes or until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add 1/2 jar marshmallow cream and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Repeat with remaining ingredients, using peanut butter instead of chocolate chips.
Pour over first layer.

title: nutty sweet potato bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy in large mixing bowl. Stir in eggs, potatoes and milk.
Blend in remaining ingredients except nuts.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes or until done.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: With grease from bacon, fry onion and rice until onions are tender.
Put in baking pan with cabbage.
Brown ground meat on stove.
Strain and put in pan.
On stove, heat sauce and water. Put in pan.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until rice is tender.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix instant vanilla pudding with 3 cups milk until thick. Refrigerate for 20 minutes (or until thickened).
Blend in Cool Whip.
Line dish (2-quart casserole) with graham crackers. Pour mixture on top.
Place another layer of graham crackers.
Melt oleo.
Add powdered sugar, vanilla and cocoa.
Mix and add enough milk to spread easily. Pour on graham crackers.
Leave in refrigerator 2 to 4 days.

title: pork pies
directions: In a large skillet, combine pork and hamburg, onion and spices.
Add enough water to cover and simmer for 3 hours, mashing with a fork for the first 1/2 hour.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Melt in double boiler or microwave.
Serve warm over chips.

title: seasoning fries
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Cook fries in hot oil until fries are brown. Toss seasoning on fries. Serve hot.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Stir until creamy and pecans are coated.
Turn onto foil and separate.

title: almond crescent
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake on top shelf of oven at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: sherrill's divinity
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, salt, corn syrup and water.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Bring to a boil.
Meanwhile, beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
When syrup mixture reaches 230° on candy thermometer, pour slowly over egg whites, beating constantly until the mixture begins to lose its gloss and holds its shape.
Add vanilla and working quickly, drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Top immediately with a pecan half. Yields 4 dozen.

title: chili con carne
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until done. Break up beef with fork while cooking. Drain off grease. Combine balance of ingredients in pot. Add cooked ground beef. Simmer 30 minutes. Water may be added to reach desired consistency. Top with desired shredded cheese (melt on individual serving or entire pot). Great as a dip.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Cream cheese and sugar until creamy. Add crushed pineapple and fold in cool whip. Pour into a baked pie shell or graham cracker crust and chill.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat.
Mixture scorches easily.
Remove and stir in chocolate bits until melted. Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until blended. Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cool 2 hours.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: icicle pickles
directions: To 1 quart of cucumbers, put 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon salt and not quite a pint of vinegar.
Finish filling the jar with water.
Seal and shake the jar until sugar and water are well mixed.
Put in hot water bath until the cucumbers change color. They do not have to boil.

title: pecan pie
directions: Make pastry for one-crust pie; line pie pan.
Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter and corn syrup together. Mix in pecan halves.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes, or until set and pastry is nicely browned.
Cool. Serve cold or slightly warm.

title: grandma delphia's dog food
directions: Mix together all Chexs, pretzels and peanuts.
To oil and butter, mixed together, add salts and Worcestershire sauce. Slowly pour over cereal mix, stirring as you pour.
Bake in oven at 250° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring frequently.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until fluffy.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Spread on 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: fruit candy
directions: Cut pineapple and cherries into small pieces.
Place together in large bowl.
Cook together sugar, syrup, salt and half and half until hard soft ball stage.
Beat until it starts to thicken.
Add slowly to nuts and fruit.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet.
Pat down with buttered hands.
Cover with waxed paper and place overnight to dry.
Cut into squares.

title: bacon wraps
directions: Cut uncooked bacon in half.
Cut crust off bread and cut bread slices in half.
Spread undiluted soup on top of bread slices. Roll bread.
Place half piece of bacon around each rolled up bread and secure with toothpick.
Place on broiler pan and bake for 2 hours at 225°.

title: little pizzas
directions: Mix frist 7 ingredients all together and put on baguette bread. Put under broiler for about 3 minutes.
If you want it hotter, you can add a couple of jalapenos.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil to soft ball stage sugar and milk (medium Heat). Stir constantly to keep from scorching. Add marshmallow creme, peanut butter and nuts. Pour into buttered pan. Very good. Easy to make.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter, shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Mix well.
Add soda to flour and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Add milk.
Use teaspoon to make ball of dough.
Press dough with glass bottom dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400°.
Bakes fast and cookies should be removed from cookie sheet immediately.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar and the shortening. Cream until light. Add eggs; beat well. Combine 2 cups flour, soda and salt.
Combine buttermilk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Add pecans and apples into batter.
Pour into loaf pan. Bake at 350°.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cheesie onion hors d'oeuvres
directions: *Blend 1 envelope onion soup with 1/2 pound butter or margarine.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: apple cobbler(or peach, cherry, pineapple)
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put 2 cans apple filling in pan; spread evenly.
Spread dry cake mix evenly over the pie filling. Put 1 stick butter on each end of cake.
Pour milk evenly over mixture.
Put in oven for 2 hours at 300°.
Let cool and serve.

title: chimechangas(about 1 dozen beef and bean filling)
directions: Heat salad oil in frypan.
Add ground beef, stirring to break up.
Cook until lightly browned.
Add onion, garlic and green pepper.
Cook, stirring, until onion is transparent.
Stir in salt, cumin, chili powder, cayenne and refried beans.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium-low heat until hot.
Fold in cheese and set aside to cool.
Place 1/4 cup filling near center of tortilla.
Fold tortilla around filling, tucking in sides. Fasten with wooden pick.
Deep fry at 370°.
Turn as needed, until browned.
Remove with tongs; drain on paper towels.
Serve with sour cream, guacamole, tomato and green chili relish.

title: waffles
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Mix all the other ingredients and fold in the egg whites.

title: karo orange ham glaze
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, combine Karo corn syrup, orange peel, orange juice and nutmeg. Bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 5 minutes.

title: waioli tea room carrot bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon together.
Make a well in the dry ingredients mixture (in mixing bowl) and add nuts, oil, vanilla, sugar, carrots and optional raisins or coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased 8 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Cool before slicing to prevent crumbling.

title: vegetable toss up
directions: In large bowl, layer the greens, cauliflower, zucchini, tomatoes and the onion.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzel sticks, margarine and sugar and spread into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes; don't overcook.
Whip the cream cheese and 1 cup sugar and fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix jello, water and frozen strawberries.
Let cool.
Pour over cream cheese layer and congeal.

title: caesar salad
directions: Crush garlic; add to oil, egg, lemon juice, mustard, salt and pepper in jar with tight fitting lid.
Shake to combine.
Chill.

title: fiesta casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and seasonings until crumbly.
In a round casserole, alternate layers of tortillas, meat sauce, olives and cheese.
Pour tomato sauce over top.
Add water.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: sesame cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well until fluffy.
Mix flour and baking powder together. Gradually add the flour mixture to the creamed mixture, also adding the milk.
Roll in the palm of your hand to about the size of your little finger, then roll in sesame seed.
Bake for 15 minutes in 375° oven on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chicken swiss
directions: Cut chicken breasts in two.
Lay slice of Swiss cheese on each one.
Place single layer in baking dish. Mix cream of chicken soup with white wine and pour over cheese and chicken. Spread layer of mushrooms on top.
Cover with 2 cups of stuffing mix and drizzle melted butter or margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and sugar.
Mix well. Make a well in center and add eggs and oil.
Stir only until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in strawberries and pecans. Spoon batter into 2 lightly greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tested done.
Let stand overnight.
Can be wrapped and frozen.

title: chicken macaroni and cheese salad
directions: Mix until moist with mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste. Chill before serving.

title: apple pizza
directions: Put pie crust in 14-inch pizza pan.
Slice apples thin over crust.
Mix dry ingredients together with enough milk to make a paste. Drizzle over sliced apples and bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Preheat grill or frying pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour batter into hot greased griddle and bake until bubbles appear. Turn only once. Brown other side.
Makes about ten 5-inch pancakes.
Blueberries and bananas may be added for variety.

title: lobster and shrimp salad
directions: Remove the lobster meat from the shell and cut into bite-size pieces.
Coarsely chop the eggs, onion and pepper.
Mix with the celery and parsley.
Mix the oil, vinegar and mustard.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Combine the lobster with the eggs and onion mixture.
Add the shrimp and mix well.
Pour the dressing over the salad and toss thoroughly.
Spoon the dressing over the salad and toss thoroughly.
Spoon onto a bed of lettuce leaves and garnish with chopped dill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Melt butter to liquid form, add sugar, brown sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, salt, vanilla, baking powder and mix well.
Add flour a little at a time until completely mixed in, then add chocolate chips.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: mrs. parrish's egg custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Beat eggs and sugar together.
Scald milk and butter.
Pour custard into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg (use 10-inch pie shell).
Bake 13 to 14 minutes (no longer).

title: kielbasa in a crock-pot
directions: Cut kielbasa into 2-inch pieces and place in crock-pot.
Rinse sauerkraut and place over meat.
Sprinkle with pepper; add bay leaf and apples.
Saute onions in margarine and pour over apple layer.
Stir in 1/2 cup water.
Place potatoes over the mixture; pour additional melted margarine over potatoes.
Cover and cook on high for 5 hours.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Place margarine and peanut butter in a large glass mixing bowl.
Microwave on High for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Add the 10x sugar and vanilla.
Stir quickly until well mixed.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Cool and cut when set.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off fat.
In a large pan, mix hamburger, beans, tomatoes, tomato sauce and onion soup mix.
Stir together; bring to boil.
Still hot, pour into a baking dish.
Add cheese on top, then cornbread mixed as on the box using 1/2 cup milk.
Batter will be thin.
Pour over cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven until cornbread is done, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut squares
directions: Melt butter and mix with powdered sugar and peanut butter. Put in a thin layer on large buttered cookie sheet.

title: layered salad
directions: In large see-through bowl, layer vegetables as desired, intermingling lettuce.
Top with dressing.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs; pour in oil.
Mix at medium speed until no visible trace of oil remains.
Mix 3 minutes more.
Add flour, soda, spices and salt; mix well.
Add pumpkin and mix at slower speed.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: garden salsa
directions: Drop tomatoes in boiling water for 5 seconds.
Remove and peel skin off.
Crush and place tomatoes in pot and boil.
Add peppers, garlic, onion and adobo.
Sift flour over boiling tomatoes while stirring, until thick.
Add salt to taste, then allow to cool.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: cavettina
directions: Mix all together (except Mozzarella cheese). Put in baking dish. Cover with Mozzarella cheese and bake until browned and bubbling.

title: vegetarian dip
directions: Mix ingredients well. Serve with little tomatoes, fresh broccoli, carrot sticks, celery sticks, fresh mushroom slices or fresh cauliflower.

title: tangy slaw
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil.
Boil for about 1 minute. Pour over cabbage mixture; toss several times, cover and refrigerate overnight or at least for 6 hours.
Will keep for at least a week if kept in refrigerator in covered container.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mix salt and chopped onion with hamburger.
Press into a pie plate to form a pie shell.
Fill with stuffing.
Cover with undiluted mushroom soup and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6. Great with baked potatoes.

title: ham and tortilla rollups
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Spread on flour tortilla. Lay ham on top cheese mixture.
Roll up, wrap and refrigerate for 4 - 6 hours before serving.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, beating well after each. Add flour, vanilla and salt. Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Combine egg and buttermilk and stir into dry ingredients.
Stir only enough to moisten.
Drop into hot deep fat.
Fry until golden brown.
Especially good with deep fried fish.

title: sugarless cherry chews
directions: Beat butter until light and fluffy.
Blend in cottage cheese and sour cream.
Stir in flour and salt until thoroughly mixed. Chill dough if it's too soft to handle.
Using rounded teaspoons of dough, shape into balls.
Flatten center with fingers and place whole cherry or fruit filling in indentation.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 400 degree oven for 12 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Remove and cool completely.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Combine and pour into paper cups.
Place in muffin tin. Freeze.
Peel off paper and place on lettuce leaf to serve.

title: tropical salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium bowl.
Season with salt and pepper.
Can be prepared 3 hours ahead.
Chill.
This is wonderful with swordfish and a well chilled bottle of a dry white wine.

title: creamy cheesecake
directions: Mix butter and 1 cup sugar with graham cracker crumbs.
Press into tins firmly by hand.
Warm cream cheese to room temperature. Beat with 1 cup granulated sugar and eggs until frothy.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla and lemon rind.
Pour into pie tins.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender; drain. Salt to taste. Scald milk with margarine.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Pour into prepared casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon-sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine; slowly add sugar and continue creaming.
Add eggs one at a time.
Combine sour cream and milk. Combine baking powder and flour.
Add flour and the sour cream mixed with milk alternately.
Add flavorings last.
Bake at 325° for approximately one hour and fifteen minutes in a tube pan.

title: fried corn
directions: Combine corn, salt, pepper and green pepper.
Add oil.
Cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: kifli(austrian)
directions: Beat sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time. Add sifted flour and lemon juice.
Put into greased and floured pan, 13 x 9-inches.
Sprinkle with ground nuts and sugar mixture. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: apricot raisin pie with crumb topping
directions: Take all except apricots and cook until mixture thickens, stirring occasionally.
Add drained apricots and pour in pastry lined pan.
Put sweet crumbs on top and bake at 425° until crust is brown.

title: old leathergut chili
directions: Brown meats and drain.
Cook for 3 hours; cool for 12 hours, then serve.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese and mix together with other ingredients.
Roll in chili powder.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: hershey fudge cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs and flour; stir in Hershey's syrup and vanilla.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: melt in your mouth blueberry cake
directions: Sift flour, powder and salt.
Beat egg whites.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fold in egg whites, lemon juice and blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour into small round pan or loaf pan.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until done.

title: easy red punch
directions: Mix together.
(Be sure ingredients are cold.)
Make attractive molds by freezing 1 can Hawaiian Punch in different Cool Whip containers.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Beginning with beans, layer ingredients in a casserole dish. Serve with dip-size Fritos or tortilla chips.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour beans and corn over top.
Sprinkle 1 cup of cheese over meat mixture.
Prepare cornbread mix as per package directions.
Pour mixed cornbread down center of baking dish and top with remaining cup of grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: In a large bowl, beat together applesauce, egg, oil and honey. Set aside.
In a medium bowl, combine flours, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add this to the applesauce mixture, stirring to moisten the dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins; divide the batter and pour into greased muffin cups.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: soft peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat together wet ingredients and sugars.
Sift together dry ingredients and beat them into the wet ingredients by hand.
Roll tablespoonfuls of dough into balls.
Place 3 inches apart on nonstick sprayed cookie sheets.
Flatten to 1/2-inch thick with fork, making a "plus" on each cookie.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Cool on pans 1 minute and transfer to wire racks to cool.

title: lazy day brown stew
directions: Mix all together including green bean juice.
Cover tightly and cook at 300° for 4 to 4 1/2 hours.

title: company-over chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with 1/2 strip of bacon.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch dish in two rows.
Top with shredded beef.
Mix sour cream and soup together and spread over chicken.
