Bake at 375° for 2 1/2 hours.
"O so good."

title: dark cocoa pie
directions: Line a deep pie pan with pie crust.
Bake quickly 10 to 15 minutes
in hot oven.
Scald the milk.
Sift cocoa, flour, sugar and
salt.	Gradually
add	scalded
milk, mixing well. Cook, stirring
constantly until thick.
Slightly beat yolks. Add
a little
of the thick mixture to yolks, then add all to the	cooked mixture.
Cook
a	while
longer,	stirring.
Add butter
and vanilla.
Pour
into
baked pie shell.
Let cool. Beat
egg whites
with
tablespoons of sugar for meringue. Brown.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt shortening in a heavy pot over high heat.
Add flour and stir until light brown.
Lower heat.
Add shrimp.
Cook 5 minutes or until pink.
Add garlic, onion, parsley and bell pepper.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Turn up heat; gradually add water and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; simmer, covered, for 25 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: apricot pecan salad
directions: Place pineapple, including juice, in a 4 cup measure.
Heat on high in microwave for 3 minutes or until bubbly hot.
Stir in jello until dissolved. Cut cream cheese in large chunks.
Add to pineapple mixture.
Microwave on medium until cream cheese is completely softened, stirring halfway through. Stir in apricots. Cool to room temperature.
Fold in 1/4 cup nuts and Cool Whip together.
Pour into 8-inch square dish.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts. Refrigerate until set.

title: banana bread(low calorie)
directions: Mix together in order and bake in a large pan 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese "croutons"
directions: Melt butter over low heat in medium skillet.
Add shredded wheat biscuits.
Heat for 5 minutes, constantly turning biscuits with a spoon.
Remove from heat.
Add the cheese, tossing gently to coat.
Serve warm or cool, floating on soups, tossed with a green salad or use as nibblers.
Store in tightly covered jar in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: hot potato casserole
directions: Pour melted margarine in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Salt and pepper potatoes.
Mix last 5 ingredients together, except cheese, and cook 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with cheese as soon as you take it from the oven.

title: old fashioned cooked cheese(for sandwiches)
directions: Add no salt.
Drain cottage cheese in strainer for a day (about 8 hours).
Turn into bowl and sprinkle the baking soda over cheese.
Let stand overnight on cabinet counter at room temperature.
Put oleo or cream in heavy saucepan.
Add the cheese mixture and caraway and cook very slowly over low heat until cheese is congealed and melted.
Pour into bowl to set.
Use for sandwiches.
Good with French bread.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Blend cottage cheese and dry milk until smooth and chill to thicken.
Mix apples and lemon juice.
Add celery, walnuts and grapes.
Stir in thickened cottage cheese mixture and serve. Makes 4 servings.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and pepper; add all other ingredients.
Bake at 300°, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh cranberry muffins
directions: Grease 12 count muffin pan.
In small bowl, sprinkle cranberry halves with 3 tablespoons sugar.
Set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add cranberries, walnuts and orange peel; blend thoroughly.
Combine egg, orange juice, oleo and milk.
Mix just until moistened.
Spoon into pan; fill cups 2/3 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 425°.
Cool in pan 5 minutes before removing.
Serve hot.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Break up tortillas into bite size pieces.
Add chicken and onion.
Cook soup in saucepan, along with milk and chilies for 15 minutes on low.
Add soup to chicken and add cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: rice and beans
directions: Boil rice and chicken broth for 15 minutes.
Rinse beans and add to rice until done.
Serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water; add cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Let set.
Spread with Cool Whip, if desired.
It is advised to use a 9 x 10-inch or a 9 x 12-inch dish.

title: wild rice dressing
directions: Wash rice and soak overnight; drain well.
Bring water to boil; add salt and rice.
Drain if necessary.
Heat butter in skillet, add onion, almonds and mushrooms; saute 3 minutes.
Blend in parsley, cloves and seasoned salt.
Mix well.
Makes approximately 4 cups.
Delicious with game or domestic fowl, or use as meat accompaniment.

title: potatoes salad
directions: Boil whole red potatoes.
Allow to cool.
Peel and chop into fairly large pieces.
Chop eggs, celery and onions and add to potatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add mayonnaise or dressing.

title: chicken cheese chowder
directions: Cook bacon, drain and reserve drippings. Crumble bacon.
Put 2 tablespoons reserved drippings in saucepan.
Add onion and green pepper. Cook until tender. Add milk, soup, chicken, pimientos, salt and half the bacon.
Heat through.
Add cheese.
Stir to melt.

title: frosting for chocolate cake
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add cocoa; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add gradually the milk and powdered sugar. Beat with electric mixer until smooth and thick enough to spread.

title: papaya - mango sauce
directions: Slice fruit into large saucepan.
Mix cornstarch with sugar; sprinkle over fruit.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until thick (at least 20 minutes).

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 400° oven in iron skillet until done.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Press into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice, soup and water together and put in a large baking pan.
Lay chicken on soup mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: raisin cake
directions: Cook at 275° until done (about 1 hour and 45 minutes).
Let margarine get room temperature and cream it with sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and then add cream and flour. Stir in raisins with spoon.

title: meat ball stroganoff
directions: With fork, combine meat, crumbs, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and parsley.
Shape into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Saute in 2 tablespoons hot oleo until brown.
Remove meat balls and reserve.

Add 2 tablespoons more oleo to skillet, then saute onion and mushrooms with paprika, about 5 minutes or until tender. Sprinkle flour over mushroom mixture; stir, then while stirring, slowly add beef bouillon, 3/4 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and 1/2 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce.
Return meat balls to sauce and simmer, covered, about 10 minutes.
Just before serving, add sour cream and heat through.
Serve over rice or spaghetti.

title: salsa
directions: Put tomatoes and onion in blender.
Surge until onion is coarsely chopped.
Add spices and peppers.
Surge again.

title: adelle payne's chicken spectacular
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly at 350°.

title: pull apart bread
directions: Preheat
oven
Roll dough in little balls and roll in
brown
sugar,
nuts
and cinnamon.
Place in loaf or Bundt pan and let rise 45 minutes.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Spray with pan or grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix together all ingredients.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Put in a casserole.
Cover with pie crust and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes (approximately).

title: lemon angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add salt and vinegar.
Continue beating until stiff.
Gradually add sugar (about 2 tablespoons at a time), beating thoroughly after each addition.
Continue beating until all sugar is dissolved and mixture is very stiff.
Spread in well-greased and floured 9-inch pie pan, making edges slightly higher than center.
Bake in slow oven, 275° for 1 1/4 hours. Cool.

title: dash diet mexican bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Spread rice in a shallow 3-quart casserole. Top with chicken. In a bowl, combine tomatoes, beans, corn, peppers, seasoning and garlic; pour over chicken. Top with cheese and jalapeo pepper. Bake 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and flour.
Stir in other ingredients. Pour into 2 medium uncooked pie shells. Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey soup
directions: Debone leftover turkey and cut into small pieces.
Pour water into pot.
Add all ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Add more water, if needed.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Mix bread crumbs, eggs, milk, wheat and white bread, celery, onions, bell pepper, sage, oregano, hen or turkey broth and chicken soup in a large bowl until the mixture is smooth.
Add water to mixture to keep dressing from being thick and having no lumps in mixture.
The mixture should look like uncooked corn bread.
Season with pepper and little or no salt.
Pour mixture in a buttered dish or large baking pan.
Set oven at 350° and bake until dressing is golden brown.

title: chili
directions: Brown onions in small amount of fat.
Add other ingredients. Cook about 2 hours slowly.
If too thick, add more tomato juice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water.
Drain and mix in rest of ingredients.
Pour into shallow baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs or crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: five hour stew
directions: Brown beef.
In a large casserole, combine rest of ingredients.
Recipe can be doubled.
Bake for 5 hours at 275°, covered.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apricot salad
directions: Boil pineapple in juices with sugar.
Mix in jello and put aside to cool.
Chop celery and nuts.
Fold cream cheese into pineapple mixture. Add celery and nuts.
Whip chilled evaporated milk and fold into pineapple mixture.
Refrigerate until set (overnight or at least a few hours).

title: rosy cinnamon peaches
directions: Combine peaches with syrup, cinnamon candies, lemon juice and food coloring.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight or longer. Stir occasionally to mix red hots while dissolving during the day. Peaches should have a rosy red color to them with cinnamon taste. Serves 10.

title: pizzelles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake on hot iron.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and salt; add scalded milk and egg yolks. Cook until thick.
Caramelize 1/2 cup sugar and add 1/4 cup butter. Mix well into milk mixture.
Add vanilla; let cool.
Pour into baked pie shell and put meringue of 3 egg whites on top.
Brown at 350° for 15 minutes or more.

title: aunt frida's five minute cookies
directions: Boil in a pan a bit after the shortening melts the brown sugar, milk and margarine.
Add rolled oats, coconut, cocoa, vanilla and dash of salt.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper. Cool.

title: sausage pie
directions: Brown sausage; add potatoes, gravy and onion and set aside.

title: citrus cooler
directions: Combine juices and extracts in a large pitcher.
Refrigerate until cold.
Stir in sparkling water. Serve over ice.

title: rice and chicken(servings:  4)
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces, carrot into strips and slice mushrooms into strips.
Put in pan.
Add 1 tablespoon of sake, soy sauce and 2 tablespoons of mushroom water.
Cook until water has evaporated.
Boil string beans lightly in salted water and cut into strips.
Cook rice in 2 3/4 cups of water, 2 tablespoons of soy sauce and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add sake, soy sauce and mushroom water, chicken and vegetables.
Let boil for 30 seconds; turn down and simmer until water has almost evaporated (20 minutes).
Just before turning off, turn up heat for a few seconds.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Stir.
Place on dish.

title: cheese biscuits(for parties)
directions: Grate cheese and let come to room temperature along with margarine.
Cream together.
Sift flour with spices.
Mix with cheese.
Mix until smooth.
Add Rice Krispies.
Roll in small balls and flatten.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown or 10 to 12 minutes.

title: rhubarb(one crust pie)
directions: Combine sugar, flour, egg yolks and salt.
Add rhubarb. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of flour over bottom of crust.
Pour in rhubarb mixture.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 10 minutes. Then turn to 350° and bake 30 minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add 4 tablespoons of sugar and beat again. Put over pie when done and brown at 325°.

title: german potato salad
directions: Scrub and cook potatoes; when tender, peel and dice.
Add celery, hard-boiled eggs and onion; toss lightly.
Fry bacon until crisp and brown.
To the beaten eggs, add sugar, salt, pepper and mustard; add to the mixture of vinegar and water.
Mix well.
Pour egg mixture in hot bacon fat; stir until mixture thickens (about 10 minutes).
Pour over potato mixture; toss lightly and chill several hours before serving.

title: apple macaroon
directions: Place sliced apples in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Mix sugar, eggs and melted margarine. Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Add milk, enough to make smooth.
Spoon over apples.
Bake 50 minutes at 375°.

title: pepper relish
directions: Put peppers and onions through grinder and coarsely grind. Do not save the juice.
Pour boiling water over this mixture and let stand for 3 minutes and drain.
Repeat this one more time. Add to the vinegar, sugar and salt and boil exactly 15 minutes. Wonderful as an accompaniment for fish, chicken, beef, etc.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix all ingredients chopped together.
Cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Put in hot sterilized pint jars.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Undercook the broccoli, drain and place in casserole dish. Melt cheese and margarine.
Add rest of ingredients, except crumbs, and pour over broccoli.
Top with crumbs (can use corn flake crumbs).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar and put into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°. Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar (1 cup) and Cool Whip and put on top of pretzel mix.
Make sure edges are sealed to keep crust from becoming soggy.
Dissolve jello in water and stir in strawberries.
Cool 10 minutes in refrigerator.
Pour over cream cheese second layer and chill until firm.

title: taco salad
directions: Cut up lettuce.
Cut tomatoes in small pieces.
Slice onion. Mix lettuce, tomato, onion, olives and Cheddar cheese.
Crumble Doritos and add to salad.
Add warm (but not hot) ground beef. Add dressing and mix.
Serve immediately.

title: grandma's homemade vegetable soup
directions: Brown boiling beef in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add to 2 quarts of water.
Bring to boil.
Add bouillon cubes and dissolve.
Cut up carrots, celery and onions into thin slices.
Add to soup mixture. While this starts to cook, cut up potatoes into cubes and slice cabbage into thin strips.
Add potatoes, cabbage and barley to soup.
Cook about 20 minutes.
Add peas, corn, tomatoes and beans. Cook until ingredients are tender.
More water may be added if needed.
Serve with homemade rolls.

title: iced green tomato pickles
directions: Soak sliced tomatoes in lime water for 24 hours, drain.
Soak in fresh water for 4 hours, changing water every hour.
Drain well.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 package of the 3 ounce size package of strawberry jello.
Place berries into a baked pie shell and pour filling over.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Trim fat from pork chops.
Fry out fat in a large skillet. Brown chops slowly in fat; remove from skillet.
Pour out excess fat.
Spread rice over bottom of skillet; add water.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt.
Arrange chops over rice; sprinkle with remaining salt.

title: calzones
directions: In 9 x 13 baking dish sprayed lightly with cooking spray, spread 1 pizza crust to cover bottom and pinch up sides.
In bowl mix cheeses, pepperoni, olives and seasoning.
Spread over crust. Cover mixture with second crust and pinch sides together with bottom crust.
Brush top with beaten egg.
Make multiple slices on top crust for air ventilation.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or so. Try different cheeses, spinach, mushrooms, etc.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice green tomatoes.
Pour 1/2 cup of milk into shallow bowl. Mix salt and pepper into flour.
Dip slice of tomato into milk, then dredge in the flour mixture.
Put into hot oil in frying pan and brown on both sides.
Serve immediately.

title: cranberry wild rice
directions: Cook rice according to package.
Stir in cranberries.
Cook until berries begin to pop.
Add celery, cashews, orange rind and sugar.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Is very good with fowl.

title: chocolate-pecan pie
directions: Combine milk, butter and chocolate morsels in a small saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly until chocolate melts.
Remove from heat.
Combine eggs, sugar, flour, salt, vanilla and pecans; stir in chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot pasta chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken and cut in julienne strips.
Saute mushrooms and shallots a few minutes.
Add tomatoes, parsley, chicken, wine and yogurt.
Serve over pasta.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to package directions.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with crushed potato chips. Bake in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Place all ingredients, except cheese, in blender and blend until all are chopped fine.
Remove from blender and add Parmesan cheese.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches with 1 cup sugar.
Let stand.
Put butter in a 2-quart casserole and place in the oven to melt.
Combine remaining sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir!
Spoon peaches on top of batter. Sprinkle blueberries over all.
Do not stir!
Put in oven.

title: batter for corn dogs
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and corn meal.
Add beaten egg and milk.
Use one pound of wieners and fry.

title: oriental skillet supper
directions: In heavy skillet, quickly cook green pepper and celery in hot oil until crisp-tender.
Remove and set aside.
Add meat to hot skillet and brown quickly.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together. Refrigerate until chilled and serve.

title: heath bars
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and butter in saucepan; boil for 2 minutes. Have crackers on cookie sheet. Pour the boiled mixture. Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Take off cookie sheet. Place on wax paper. Have your chocolate chips and paraffin melted. Place 1 spoon of chocolate on each cracker. A double boiler is good to melt the chocolate.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk and margarine; pour into baking dish. Spoon fruit over top of batter (crust will rise above the fruit to the top).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: tijuana torte
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, sauce, chilies and taco mix.
Combine and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: white bean soup
directions: Wash and soak beans 3 or 4 hours.
Cook beans for 1/2 hour and add all other ingredients.
Simmer 2 or 3 hours, or until beans are done.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix the boiling water and jello.
Add the crushed pineapple and the pie filling.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine; add graham cracker crumbs and press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients, but chicken and pour over chicken pieces. Bake 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: orange barbecued pork chops
directions: In small bowl, stir together barbecue sauce and orange juice until well blended.
Grill pork chops 6 inches from source of heat, turning frequently (30 minutes).
Brush with sauce.
Grill, brushing with sauce and turning frequently, 15 to 30 minutes longer or until chops are tender.
Heat remaining sauce and serve hot with pork chops.
Makes 4 servings.

title: italian coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half of batter into pan.
In separate bowl, mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour over batter.
Pour remaining batter over filling.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Shut off oven.
Leave in for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: uncle wendell's meat sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender or food processor. Blend or process on high until well mixed. This is very good on ham, turkey, or beef sandwiches. It is also good as a dip for cheese or pretzels. Will keep in refrigerator several weeks.

title: hungry boy casserole
directions: In skillet, heat margarine and beef.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 2 quart casserole dish.
Garnish with bacon slices.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or microwave on High 15 to 20 minutes if in a hurry.

title: pickled eggs
directions: In a bag bring to boil the ingredients for 10 minutes.
Put 3 bay leaves in jar with 1 teaspoon celery seed and ingredients.
In 5 to 6 weeks they will be pickled.

title: country cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in strips or wedges.
Cook in heavy saucepan with all the seasonings.
Fry onions and bacon together and pour over cabbage.
Use bacon drippings, too.
Cover and cook until tender, about 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: low-fat, sugar-free cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, yogurt, dry vanilla pudding mix and lemon juice.
Pour into crust which has been chilled.
Add strawberries just before serving.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate mocha cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light or fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat until fluffy. Sift dry ingredients and cream alternately with milk. Beat 1 minute. Bake at 300° in 3 (9-inch) cake pans that have been greased and floured for about 25 minutes. Cool.

title: hollywood hash
directions: Saute onions.
Add ground beef to onions; brown.
Add bacon, peas and tomato soup.
Cook and drain noodles; add to other ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 11-inch casserole dish and add desired salt and pepper.
Bake at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: beef in wine sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together. Put in covered baking dish.
Bake 3 hours at 325°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: salmon stew
directions: Fry
diced
fat meat until brown.
Add potato and onions and fry
until	brown.	Add water, cover and simmer 20 minutes. In large saucepan combine margarine and flour until mixed well. Add sweet
milk.
When	milk is hot, add all other ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes.

title: molded nippy salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Fold in remaining ingredients. Chill until partially set.
Continue chilling until firm.
Good served with ham.

title: mark twain's favorite mince cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine brandy and cream.
Add flour mixture, alternating with brandy mixture.
In a small bowl combine crumbled mincemeat and 2 tablespoons flour. Mix until mincemeat is well separated.
Fold into batter.
Spoon batter into a greased 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Allow to cool in pan 10 minutes, then turn out onto wax paper.
It is said this cake is good sliced and toasted and served with coffee.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli according to package directions.
As you wait, mix other ingredients (cheese, onion, soup and milk) in a bowl.
When cooked, drain and mix rice and broccoli in bowl with other ingredients.
Spray a casserole dish or disposable baking pan with a nonstick spray and bake at 350° until it's a touch brown and bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as instructed on box as soon as cake comes out of the oven.
Make holes in the cake with a knife and space them about 1-inch apart.
Have holes go about 3/4 of the way through the cake.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over cake, then pour cream of coconut over cake.
Top with nuts and coconut.

title: pecan squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Blend all ingredients except powdered sugar until just moistened.
Spread mixture into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares (sprinkle with powdered sugar).
Yields 24.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Brown ground beef.
Saute chopped onion. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Season to taste.
Let simmer to tender.

title: pecan logs
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Shape into small logs and freeze.
Combine next 4 ingredients and cook until soft ball stage is reached.
Dip logs into syrup.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: chocolate raisin pie
directions: Place baking chips, raisins, cream and butter in a heavy saucepan.
Stir over low heat until chips and butter are melted. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.

title: roughneck rolls
directions: Combine warm water and sugar in a bowl; add yeast and let stand. Let yeast come to top of water, then add shortening. Add flour and salt; mix well and place in greased bowl. Let dough rise to twice the original size, then roll out on floured board to 3/4 inch thickness. Cut rolls and place in greased pan; let rise. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown. Butter tops and serve. Makes 18 rolls.

title: mississippi pudding pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, then refrigerate to cool.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: *Can substitute lightly seasoned croutons for chips, if desired.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Grease 10-inch quiche dish or pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake at 400° until knife inserted in center comes out clean
(35 to 40 minutes). Cool 5 minutes.

title: water chestnut meatballs
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together well, then add the sausage and chopped water chestnuts.
Form into balls.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix well and pour in shell, cook at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let cool and pour 1 can cherry pie filling on top.
Chill. Top with drops of whipped cream.

title: grape torte
directions: Cook together in a double boiler until thick enough to spread: grape juice, tapioca, sugar and orange juice.
Spread over angel food cake.
Let stand overnight.
Cover with whipped cream.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Slice one roll cookies on bottom of sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan. Pat to make solid sheet.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Beat until smooth and fluffy.
Spread on cookie dough.
Slice other roll of cookies and place on cheese mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting in bars.

title: quick hot rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Spoon into well-greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked chicken pieces
directions: Salt and pepper chicken after washing.
Mix milk and eggs. Soak chicken in mixture.
Roll in corn flakes to coat.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: roasted asparagus with balsamic browned butter
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange asparagus in single layer on baking sheet; coat with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake for approximately 12 minutes or until tender.
Melt butter in small skillet over medium heat; cook for 3 minutes or until lightly browned, shaking pan occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in soy sauce and balsamic vinegar.
Drizzle over asparagus, tossing well to coat.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix sugar, brown sugar, evaporated milk, and butter in a sauce pan.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Remove from heat, beat until smooth.
Pour into greased pan and let cool.

title: spiced peach salad
directions: Drain peaches, reserving syrup.
Chop peaches coarsely.
Place syrup, vinegar, sugar and spice in a small pan.
Bring to a boil. Simmer, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cold water.
Pour into serving dish or mold.
Refrigerate until set. Yields 4 servings.
Has 110 calories, 0 g. of fat.

title: honey mounds
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients, then add vanilla and mix well. Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: my favorite dessert
directions: Fix jello on the quick chill method; set until firm.
Add frozen ice cream.
Blend with mixer; beat until smooth.
Serve in fancy dessert dishes with an elegant cookie.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add with buttermilk to dry mixture.
Mix well.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Add more flour if necessary and roll to 1/4-inch.
Cut and then dip in butter. Fold to make pocket book rolls.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Slice potatoes crosswise.
Place in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Slice onions and break into rings and place on top of potatoes.
Spread mustard, salt and pepper on both sides of pork chops.
Place on top of potatoes.
Pour milk over all until chops appear to float on top but are not covered.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Just before serving, top with grated Cheddar cheese. Return to oven to melt cheese.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Make gravy from onion and mushroom soups, from directions on package in a large pan.
Mix meat, eggs, bell pepper, parsley, celery seed, garlic, cheese, black pepper and crackers. Roll into balls.
Roll in flour.
Drop in hot grease and brown on all sides. Remove from frying pan, place in gravy and simmer for one hour, stir often enough to prevent sticking to pan.

title: cheesy egg casserole
directions: Combine flour, salt and butter in a large bowl.
Add cottage cheese, monterey jack cheese, eggs and green chilies.
Mix well. Pour into a lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2 baking dish.
Garnish with green pepper rings and pimento.
Bake, uncovered at 375° for 30 minutes.
6 to 8 servings.
May be prepared preceding night.

title: spareribs barbecued in soulful sauce
directions: Wipe ribs with clean, damp cloth; cut into pieces for individual servings.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika; set aside.
Place all other ingredients, except ribs, in a large frying pan.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes; cool.
Place ribs in a large, shallow flat dish; marinate well with sauce on both sides. Cover; store in refrigerator for several hours.
Cook until well done, basting occasionally.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream white sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then at 325° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
2 large or 4 small loaf pans. (I use Teflon pans, greased lightly, with no flour.)

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cheese; add chives, Worcestershire sauce and catsup until pink.
Add shrimp last and let stand overnight.

title: old style butter pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Mix on low speed.
Cream the butter until soft.
Add the sugar while the mixer is running.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well after each.
Add flour and salt.
Mix until smooth. Add vanilla and almond extract with milk.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake 75 to 90 minutes at 325° or until done.

title: italian beef skillet
directions: In large skillet, brown beef and drain. Drain tomatoes; save juice. Add water to juice to make 2 1/4 cups liquid.
Add liquid, rice, garlic salt, oregano and onion to beef.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender. Fold in tomatoes and heat through.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well.
Let set overnight before serving.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: vegie bars
directions: Spread crescent rolls in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake as directed. Blend and cream the mayonnaise, cream cheese, garlic powder, dill weed and dry onion. Spread on top of cool crust. Spread fresh vegetables and shredded cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: beef and cabbage soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain in colander to remove fat.
In large pot add tomato juice, water, Ro-Tel, cabbage, onions and ground beef.
Bring to a boil and add bouillon cubes.
Lower heat and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Season to taste.

title: angel yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, set aside.
Combine flour, sugar and baking soda.
Cut in shortening until the size of peas.
Mix buttermilk with yeast water; add to flour mixture; stir with fork until moistened.
Turn onto floured surface, sprinkle with flour. Knead 4 to 5 times.
Roll 1/2 inch thick.
Cut into biscuits with 2-inch cutter.
Place close together on lightly greased baking sheet.
Let rise 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Brush with melted butter or margarine.
Makes 24 to 30 biscuits.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix hamburg with beaten egg. Add rice, grated onion, salt and pepper.
Soften cabbage in hot water.
Mix tomato sauce, sugar, vinegar and water. Take leaf of cabbage and add meat mixture. Make rolls.
Tuck cabbage ends in.
Place in liquid and cook about 3/4 hour.

title: squash patties
directions: Grate squash fine.
Mix in eggs, cornbread mix, some onions, pepper and salt.
A little flour may be necessary.
Then by spoon, put in slightly hot grease and fry until browned on both sides.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on package.
Add 3 ounces of sour cream and Cool Whip; mix well.
Add bananas and wafers. Top with Cool Whip.

title: russian tea
directions: Blend well together.
Store in covered jar.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients until thick.
Seal in sterilized jars. Scald tomatoes; dip in cold water.
Slip off skins.
Chop and puree in blender.
May increase quantity of ingredients as desired.

title: paska bread(easter bread)
directions: Pour hot milk over sugar and shortening.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Crumble yeast in water and sugar.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Sift flour in large bowl.
Add salt and beaten eggs. Add milk and yeast mixture.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Let rise in warm place 2 hours.
(Cover.)
Punch down, cover and let go for 1 hour.
Flour board.
Divide set in enamel pot.
Let rise for 10 minutes; brush with milk.
Prick with fork.
Set in oven at 325° 10 minutes at 350° (40 minutes).

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use 3 heaping teaspoons mix or to suit your taste to 1 cup boiling water.
This is a different version than the usual mix of this type.
It keeps well if stored in an airtight container.
It is good to have on hand during the holidays when unexpected guests call.

title: tasty spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill.
Serve with vegetables or chips.
Makes 3 cups.

title: homemade yeast rolls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add flour and mix well.
(Will have a few lumps.)
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 17 minutes.
May refrigerate unused (covered) dough and bake later.
Yield: Approximately 48 rolls.

title: berried treasures
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, egg and seasoning.
Wet hands and form balls the size of walnuts.
Place in a 2-quart casserole. Combine cranberry sauce with chili sauce and pour over meatballs. Cover and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Baste after 1 hour.
Cover again and bake an additional 30 minutes. Can be made the day before to improve flavor.
Serve warm with toothpicks.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add to milk.
Mix sugar, cocoa and flour well until no lumps.
Add to warm milk and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and salt.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine peanut butter, margarine, sugar and Rice Krispies. Mix well and form into 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place in refrigerator until ready to dip.
Melt chocolates and paraffin in double boiler over medium heat.
Dip peanut butter balls into chocolate and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: oatmeal rollslincoln, nebraska
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients and let cool until lukewarm.

title: honey salad dressing
directions: Beat egg yolks, then pour in the hot honey.
Cook for a moment, beating continuously, then fold the salad oil, lemon juice, the cream (beaten stiff) and the seasonings! Mm good!

title: 7-cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: miniature meatball kabobs
directions: Combine ingredients in a medium size mixing bowl.
Shape meat into 1-inch balls.
Heat 1/2-inch of oil in a frypan.
Cook meatballs over low heat until done as desired.
Serve on wooden picks with an olive.
Makes 24 meatballs.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with a medium chopped onion.
Add salt and pepper and chili powder.
Cook well and add cream of mushroom soup and tomato soup.
Simmer 5 minutes and pour over cooked macaroni. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 450° about 10 minutes or until ingredients are heated through and sauce bubbles.

title: chicken with lemon sauce
directions: Place the bread crumbs in a shallow dish; set aside.
Brush the chicken pieces with 1/4 cup of the mayonnaise.
Dip in the bread crumbs to coat.

In a large skillet, melt 2 tablespoons of the margarine over medium heat; add the chicken and cook for 15 minutes, turning occasionally, or until golden and done. Remove to a serving platter and keep warm.

title: easy garden vegetable casserole
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Chop and brown in butter the onion and celery.
Add the green beans, corn, celery soup, sour cream and cheese.
Mix.
Top with crackers and drizzle with butter.
Cook until it bubbles, then reduce heat to 325° and let brown.

title: chicken bog
directions: Start with 28 cups of water in a large pot (this will result in 26 cups of broth). Chop onions and celery. Add to water. Add salt and pepper. Bring to boil and then add raw chicken on bone. Cook until chicken is done. Remove from heat. Brown sausage in separate pan and drain. Slice smoked sausage. Remove chicken from bone and return to stock. Add pork sausage, smoked sausage and Texas Pete. Bring to a boil. Add rice; reduce heat and stir occasionally to prevent from sticking. Cook, covered, until rice is done.

title: guacamole dip
directions: In bowl, mash avocados and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in chopped tomato, pepper, lime juice and cilantro.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: pat's cheese cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Pat in bottom of 11 x 13-inch pan.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: supreme beef casserole
directions: Melt shortening in skillet.
Add beef, breaking into pieces with fork and cook until lightly brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir into meat the tomatoes and tomato sauce, adding salt, sugar and garlic. Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add the flour, baking powder, vanilla and bananas.
Preheat the oven to 325° and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with crackers.

title: deep-south date-nut loaf
directions: In a large bowl, place dates and pecans.
Do not cut or chop. Place in bowl whole.
Sift flour; add baking powder and salt.
Pour over dates and nuts.
Mix thoroughly until dates and nuts are well floured.
Beat yolks until lemon colored, then add vanilla and sugar.
Stir into first mixture.
Mix well.
(I use my well scrubbed hands for this operation!)
Beat egg whites until they stand in peaks.
Fold gently into other mixture.
Grease a loaf pan generously; place inside thick, clean, brown wrapping paper.
Leave enough of the paper so that it overlaps the top of the loaf pan. Butter lining paper.
Spoon date-nut mixture into pan.
Fold the brown paper lightly over top of loaf.
(Heavy-duty aluminum foil could be used instead of the brown wrapping paper.)
Bake in 300° oven for 1/2 hour, then 225° for 1 1/2 hours, or until a knife plunged into loaf comes out clean.
During the last half hour of baking, uncover the top so that it may brown.
Do cook slowly.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli in bite size pieces.
Crumble bacon.
Mix dressing into other ingredients and chill before serving.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream
shortening. Add sugar and eggs. Add milk, apples nuts and
raisins. Sift dry ingredients; add to mixture. Bake in greased loaf pan at
for
45	minutes to 1 hour. Cool before slicing.

title: hot mushroom turnovers
directions: Mix together cream cheese, butter and flour.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Cook mushrooms, butter and onions until tender.
Mix in salt, thyme, sour cream and flour.
Roll dough out.
Cut into 3-inch circles.
Place filling on one side.
Fold over and seal. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple; mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill before serving.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Stir well the first 5 ingredients.
Add to scalded milk and stir well.
Pour into 9-inch pastry lined pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven down to 325° and bake for 25 minutes.
Test with knife.

title: chuck wagon mac
directions: Salt beef and brown.
Prepare dinner as directed.
Combine with beef.
Add corn and tomato paste.
Add water and stir. Place in 3-quart casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mossledge quick rolls
directions: Crumble yeast in mixing bowl; add salt, sugar, water and beaten egg.
Stir in 2 cups flour; stir until smooth.
Stir in melted Spry or shortening; add rest of flour.
Mix well.
Let rise once, then shape like Parker House rolls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Mix together.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until browned on top.

title: hawaiian wedding punch
directions: Heat 2 cups water with the sugar until sugar dissolves.
Add the juices, the remaining water and the banana puree.
Divide mixture into 2 large plastic bowls.
Cover tightly and freeze.
To serve, defrost 1 of the punch bases into punch bowl.
Add half the 7-Up and 1/2 the club soda.
Break up punch base until mushy and icy in bowl.

title: denise holland salsa
directions: Put all ingredients in food processor until blended.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients.
In large saucepan, combine milk, butter and marshmallows.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Pour over pecan mixture and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in the coconut, washing your hands frequently.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form a sweet potato ball around a large marshmallow.
Roll each ball in crushed corn flakes.
Bake in 425° oven until marshmallows begin to ooze.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes on medium heat.
Stir often.

title: dried beef roll-ups
directions: Blend cream cheese and horseradish.
Spread mixture on slices of beef.
Roll up beef into logs and refrigerate.
Before serving, cut each log into fourths.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix hamburger, onions, rice, tomato soup and tomato paste. Cook cabbage leaves; put mixture in leaves and roll up with toothpicks.
Pour tomato sauce over rolls.
Cook in pressure cooker for 25 minutes.

title: overnight casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except potato chips and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Cover with crushed potato chips and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12 easily.

title: taco sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Process until all ingredients are chopped fine.

title: one-skillet spaghetti
directions: Cook and stir hamburger and onions in 10-inch skillet or Dutch oven until hamburger is light brown; drain.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid, green pepper, water, mushrooms, salt, sugar, chili powder and spaghetti.
Break up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally until spaghetti is tender, about 30 minutes.
Add more water during cooking if necessary.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Combine green pepper, onion, celery, rice, eggs and chicken. Blend bouillon cubes in mayonnaise; add to rice mixture.
Season to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: make-ahead salad
directions: Prepare vegetables for salad.
Layer them in bowl except eggs. Mix mayonnaise with sugar and spread over vegetables.
Top with cheese.
Refrigerate 8 to 24 hours.
Toss before serving.
Garnish with eggs.

title: honey oatmeal bread
directions: Bring 5 cups water to boil; add oatmeal.
Cool slightly. Dissolve yeast in 2 cups lukewarm water and sugar.
Mix together with remaining ingredients for 10 minutes.
Let rise; punch down. Let rise again.
Put in pans.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer in crock-pot.

title: quick supper salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite size pieces.
Add macaroni, eggs and tuna.
Combine vinegar, salt and mayo; pour over salad.
Toss to mix.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until thick.
Mix with oleo, flour, 1/3 cup cocoa, vanilla, coconut and nuts thoroughly.
Combine with eggs and sugar.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Immediately after removing from oven, spread cream over it.
Cook 1 stick oleo, milk and 1/3 cup cocoa until smooth.
Add powdered sugar and nuts.
Spread over warm cake.

title: beet pickles
directions: Wash beets and cut tops off to 1 1/2 inches.
Leave roots on until cooked.
Boil until skin comes off easy.
Then cut roots and remaining tops off and peel the skin.
Slice beets.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, butter and egg together; pat out into an ungreased 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Then mix confectioners sugar, egg and cream cheese and pour into pan on top of the other mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: mamaw's sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and egg together.
Scald soda in 2 or 3 tablespoons boiling water before putting in milk.
Add to sugar, shortening and egg.
Mix with enough flour to make a stiff dough so you can roll easily to desired thickness.
Put in any flavor desired.
Use 1/2 teaspoon salt if using plain flour.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: asparagus supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain asparagus, but reserve 1/2 cup of liquid.
Place asparagus in greased casserole.
Combine soup with reserved liquid; pour over asparagus.
Sprinkle with almonds; top with cracker crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix yeast in water.
Add sugar, oil, egg, salt and flour.
Mix well until blended and put into refrigerator.
Let rise 3 hours. When ready to eat, place by spoonfuls into well-greased muffin tins.
Don't punch down.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Will last in refrigerator about 1 week.

title: rye bread
directions: Combine 1 c. scalded milk, 1 Tbsp salt, 2 Tbsp shortening, 3 Tbsp dark molasses.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften 1 cake compressed or 1 pkg dry yeast in 1 c. lukewarm water for 5 minutes.
Add to the above.
Blend in 2 c unsifted pure rye flour, 4 1/2 c. all purpose white flour a little at a time.
Turn on floured board and knead until smooth.
Be sure to get all white flour worked in dough until very stiff.
Place dough in greased bowl.
Cover, let rise in a warm place till double in bulk.
Punch down, let rise again.
Turn out on floured board and knead for 1 minute.
Mold into 2 balls, let stand covered 15 minutes.
Then shape into long loaves or may be baked in round pans.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
For glass, bake at 350°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Wash and clean chicken.
Brown in hot fat in skillet.
Remove to deep kettle.
Add enough water to cover; salt and cook until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove meat from bone.
Strain fat off of broth and add enough water to make 2 quarts.
In skillet that chicken was browned in, cook onion and green pepper with paprika until browned.
Add to broth; add chicken.
Heat to boiling; add spaghetti and cook uncovered 15 to 20 minutes or until spaghetti is tender and most liquid is absorbed.
Do not drain.
Add olives and 1 cup cheese.
Heat in oven until very hot.
Serve with remaining cheese sprinkled on top.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: apple-anna bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream together the shortening and sugar; add the eggs, stirring well.
Mix together the flour, baking soda and baking powder and add to the creamed mixture alternately with the bananas.
Add the vanilla, stirring well.
Fold in the apples. Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: haystacks
directions: Cook ground chuck and onion in a skillet until done. Drain well. Place back in skillet. Add 1 cup water and seasoning mix. Heat and mix well; cook dry. Crush Doritos and place handful in plate. Top with meat mixture, then tomatoes, lettuce and cheese. Top with dressing. Fast meal. Kids love it!

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Pour melted butter on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle evenly the crumbs, nuts, chocolate bits, then coconut.
Pour condensed milk evenly over coconut.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned in a 350° oven.
Cool in pan 15 minutes, then cut.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix together and press with fingers into pie plate.
Bake in preheated oven (450°) on upper shelf for 15 minutes.
Makes 1 large pie shell.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple (do not boil).
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: favorite green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans in colander before mixing ingredients. Combine green beans, milk, soup, pepper, cheese and 1/2 can of French fried onions.
Mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions. Bake 5 minutes longer.
Serve.

title: oatmeal flat bread(havremel flat brod)
directions: Cream sugar and melted butter together.
Add salt.
Add soda to buttermilk, then add to creamed mixture alternately with flour. Add oats.
Divide mixture into 2 log shapes.
Divide as you work in 1/3 cup portions and shape each into round ball.
Press down and roll on pastry cloth with pin covered with pastry sleeve. Roll paper thin.
Use lefse stick and roll dough on stick; lift and unroll on cookie sheet.
Either cut with pastry cutter into squares before baking, or bake and then break into pieces.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Mix with other ingredients as you would biscuits. Roll and cut on floured board. Bake at 400° until golden brown. Makes 15 rolls.

title: crunchy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add cornflakes, oatmeal, coconut and vanilla.
Drop by spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: old fashioned cornmeal pie
directions: In large bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add corn syrup, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in cornmeal and flour.
Pour into pastry shells.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Reduce heat to 300°.
Bake 20 minutes longer or until pie tests done.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and bake in a 2-quart long baking dish at 350° until brown.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: banana milk
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth

title: broccoli with cheese casserole
directions: Trim off large leaves of broccoli; remove tough ends of lower stalks.
Wash thoroughly; cut into 1-inch pieces.
Bring water to a boil in a large saucepan.
Add broccoli and salt.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until tender.
Drain liquid and set broccoli aside.
Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in margarine in saucepan until tender.
Combine broccoli, sauteed vegetables and water chestnuts in a large bowl; set aside.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until it forms soft ball in water. Remove from stove and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream. Beat together until thick and pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan to cool.

title: diabetic coconut pie
directions: Coconut should be fresh because of the sugar.
The day before if needs to be ground and Sweet 'N Low added to taste.
Store in tight container overnight at least.
Prepare pie and topping as you would for any other pie.
High in fat so have small pieces!

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients; spread evenly in shallow baking pan.

Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle 2/3 of the crumbs in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine egg whites, sugar, berries and lemon juice in a large bowl; with electric beater, beat at high speed to stiff peaks, about 10 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon over crumbs; top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze at least 6 hours or overnight.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar in a small bowl.
Toss remaining ingredients in a serving bowl.
Stir in dressing.
Serve chilled.
Serves 8.

title: oriental chicken and pineapple stir-fry
directions: Pour reserved pineapple juice into small bowl.
Add cornstarch; use fork to mix well.
Add garlic, scallions, ginger, soy sauce, steak sauce and honey; mix well.
Let mixture stand for 10 minutes.
Place chicken strips into casserole dish.
Add sauce and stir.
Cover dish with waxed paper.
Set microwave on High and cook for 3 minutes.
Stir, cover again and cook on High for 3 more minutes.
Add pineapple.
Stir, cover and cook on High for 3 more minutes.
Let covered dish stand for 5 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Layer 1/2 of each item in a 2-quart greased casserole.
Then repeat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain green and yellow beans.
Rinse kidney beans.
Slice onion and green pepper very thin.
Mix sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour into dish with beans, onion and pepper.
Let set overnight.

title: diabetic banana-raisin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients carefully.
Spray pan with Pam.
Bake in loaf, tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry pancakes(low calorie)
directions: In blender, combine Bisquick, butter, egg, milk and cinnamon. Process until smooth.
Stir in strawberries.
Spray a nonstick skillet with Pam and heat over medium heat.
Yields 3 pancakes.

title: recipe for a good w.m.u.
directions: Cream together Leadership Training and Desire.
Add Tithes and Offerings which have been combined with Energy and Bible Study. Stir gently.
Add Vivacious Girls and Service Flour and mix well. Sift together General Meetings, Dedicated Life, Aspiration, Inspiration and Enthusiasm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew whole chicken or parts, salt, onion and celery.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing.
Combine cold, cut up chicken, peas, cream of mushroom soup and sour cream.
Place chicken mixture in casserole dish with stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chocoholic's dream cake
directions: In a large bowl, sift flour and sugar together.
Mix well. In a saucepan, bring to a boil the oleo, Crisco, cocoa and cold milk.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
(For an extra moist cake, add syrup to the boiled mixture.)
Mix well.
Add buttermilk, soda, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well; pour into a 15 x 11 x 1-inch sheet cake pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Combine chicken, soups, 1/2 cup milk and sour cream and chicken.
Simmer.
Combine Bisquick mix, cornmeal, 3/4 cup milk, egg and cheese.
Pour chicken mixture into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
With spoon, drop batter mixture on the chicken.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
The crust should be browned.

title: flank steak
directions: Mix and marinate steak 3 to 4 hours in refrigerator or overnight.
Grill steak.

title: german oven pancake
directions: In blender, combine eggs, milk and melted butter.
Add flour and salt.
Pour into well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°.
Drizzle with butter and sprinkle with sugar. Especially good served with sausage.

title: fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; cook over medium gas flame, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring until small amount forms a soft ball in cold water (234°).
Turn off flame.
Stir in 2 tablespoons butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cool without stirring.
When cool, beat until creamy.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in pan and cut into squares.

title: diet cookies
directions: Mix well and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake until done at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Use 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Do not mix.
Layer ingredients in pan in order given.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip, ice cream or plain.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Beat egg, then add milk.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then roll in cracker crumbs.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spray pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Arrange chicken in pan so they do not touch.
Drizzle chicken with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: the very best brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine the melted butter, sugar and cocoa.
Add the eggs, one at a time, blending after each addition.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix just until combined.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch glass dish and bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until the top is firm to the touch.
Do not overbake or the brownies will be dry.
Allow to stand 15 minutes, then cut into 32 squares.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly, except Ragu sauce. Form into 2 small loaves or 1 large loaf.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with the Ragu sauce.
(You might also use some of the new Italian style tomato soups, mixed with 1 can of water.) Bake, covered, for 1 1/4 hours.
Uncover; bake for an additional 15 minutes.
Slice and serve with sauce, if preferred.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Work the flour, sugar and margarine together as you would a pie dough, into coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of crumbs.
Mix the molasses, boiling water and baking soda and combine with remaining crumbs.
Mix well.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into an oblong cake pan which has been greased and floured.
Sprinkle the remaining crumbs over the cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: supreme stuffed potatoes(ala bill alison)
directions: Bake potatoes in hot oven (425°) for 45 minutes or until tender.
Cut into halves and scoop out insides; mash.
Add remaining ingredients; beat until fluffy, seasoning to taste with salt, pepper and paprika.
Fill potato shells and bake until lightly browned.

title: easy hot german potato salad
directions: Forty minutes before serving, in large skillet over medium-high heat, fry bacon crisp.
Drain on paper towels. Crumble bacon into bits and set aside.
Discard bacon drippings. In skillet, empty potato slices and seasoned sauce mix from package of scalloped potatoes.
Stir in 3 cups of boiling water, onion flakes and sugar.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally, then stir in vinegar and bacon bits.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate oaties
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil and cook 4 minutes.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over oatmeal and mix (fast). Drop by spoon on wax paper.

title: blueberry strata pie
directions: Drain fruits, reserving syrups.
Blend cream cheese and next 3 ingredients.
Reserve 2 tablespoons pineapple.
Stir remainder into cheese mixture.
Spread over bottom of crust.
Chill.
Blend 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Combine reserved syrups, measure 1 1/2 cups, blend into cornstarch mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir in blueberries and lemon juice; cool.
Pour over cheese layer; chill.
Top with whipped cream and reserved pineapple.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over chicken or other meat to be grilled.
Marinate overnight for best results.

title: cheese and pineapple salad
directions: Thicken pineapple juice with flour, sugar and egg.
Mix all ingredients together and cool.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet; drain.
Add salt and pepper. Stir in ketchup and tomato sauce.
Heat well.
Place into 1 1/2-quart dish.
Cut cheese into strips and lay on top of meat. Place biscuits on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 450°.

title: frothy fruit frappe
directions: Combine raspberries, banana, peaches, pineapple juice and sugar.
Divide among four 8 ounce glasses.
Chill.
For each glass, add a scoop of vanilla ice cream and muddle.
Tip glass and slowly pour lemon-lime carbonated beverage down side.
Add second scoop of ice cream.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine in electric blender until thick and smooth (approximately 30 seconds).
Makes 6 cups.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix ingredients by hand sugar, oil and egg; sifting dry ingredients and mixing adding milk.
Blend blueberries in carefully.
Grease muffin tins (no papers) or 8-inch square pan. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Combine rice, salt, butter and water in heavy saucepan. Cook until
rice
is
tender. Drain well.
Add drained crushed pineapple and nuts to rice and set aside.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Mix with pineapple juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.	Remove	from fridge and beat well with a rotary beater.
Whip
chilled
milk
until
stiff.
Fold into gelatin mixture;
add
to
rice
mixture.
Place
in
a large bowl and chill until firm.
Serves 12.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Place fruit cocktail into
x
13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over this.
Dribble
melted
oleo
over top.
Bake 30 minutes. Put chopped pecans and
coconut over top and bake 30 minutes longer.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add sweet potatoes and roll into biscuits.
Cook at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Can be frozen before cooked.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
In another bowl mix remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients and stir with spoon, do not over beat.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 325 degrees, then 10-15 minutes more at 350 degrees.

title: tuna and shells
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain well. Combine with remaining ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Chill until serving time.
Yields 6 servings.

title: baked apples
directions: Wash and core apples. Starting at stem end, peel 1/3 of the way down. Arrange in shallow baking dish. Mix sugar and cinnamon. Add water to the dish and broil for 5 minutes. Baste frequently with pan syrup.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in shortening, then add milk.
Handle lightly.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cherrio treats
directions: Melt margarine; add marshmallows and melt together.
Add vanilla and peanut butter until well blended.
Add Cheerios.
Drop by tablespoons on waxed paper.
Cool.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Blend soup and chiles in blender.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and spread some of the sauce to coat pan.
Brown meat.
Heat enchilada sauce in small frypan.
Dip tortillas, one at a time, in sauce to soften.
Place in pan.
Spoon in beef, cheese and some onions.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Continue until all tortillas are used.
Pour rest of sauce over enchiladas.
Top with cheese and olives.

title: mexican dip(microwave)
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on bottom of 8 x 8-inch glass dish.
Pour and spread no bean chili on top of cream cheese. Spread shredded Cheddar cheese on top of no bean chili.

title: gee gee's chicken pie
directions: Lay chicken in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Combine chicken broth and chicken soup.
Pour over chicken.
Combine margarine, pepper, flour, and milk.
Mix thoroughly and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: dilly beans
directions: You will need four 1 pint Mason jars and hot water canner.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in cookie press using star tip.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 10 minutes.

title: fast and easy casserole(low cholesterol)
directions: Saute onions
and green pepper in pan sprayed with Pam. Brown beef.
Add	soups and vegetables.
Crush noodles and add to mixture.
(They
do not need cooking.) Add seasonings.
Put in casserole that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bacon strips may be placed across
top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. May be baked
in
microwave
on High for 30 minutes.
Test for doneness. May require more time or less.

title: norton hospital parmesan chicken
directions: Remove excess fat from chicken.
Dip in Butter Buds sprinkles. In a dish, combine Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs, parsley, oregano and basil.
Mix together.
Roll chicken breasts in bread crumb mixture, coating all sides well.
Place in an ovenproof casserole.
Bake uncovered in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, or until internal temperature reaches 160°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: non-alcoholic fruit cake
directions: Cream together the butter or margarine and 2 cups sugar.
Beat well and add the eggs and salt.
Sift together 5 cups flour, baking powder and allspice. Add slowly to creamed mixture along with orange juice. Add broken walnuts.

title: asparagus ham appetizers
directions: Spread each ham slice with approximately 1 tablespoon cream cheese.
Place 1 or 2 asparagus spears lengthwise on each ham slice.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Wrap and chill until serving. To serve, cut each roll into 4 pieces.
Makes 48 appetizers.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut into biscuits.
Place on well-greased cookie sheet. Let rise 5 minutes.
Bake at 475° until golden brown.

title: black magic cake
directions: Make chocolate cake using package directions.
Grease and flour the sides and bottom of 11 x 7-inch cookie sheet (with 1/2 to 1-inch sides).
Pour batter in cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: chicken-almond casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large casserole dish or 7 x 11-inch pan and let remain in refrigerator overnight.
Top with buttered crumbs or cheese and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: tarte a la bouillie(sweet dough pie)
directions: Cream sugar and butter well, add eggs, mix well.
Add vanilla.
Mix all dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.

title: hollywood squares
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Press into large cookie sheet with sides (15 x 9-inch).
Melt the chocolate chips; spread over top.
Cut into squares while chocolate is warm. Chill before serving.

title: cheese krispies for teatime
directions: Cream margarine and cheese.
Sift flour, salt, paprika and sugar together.
Add to cream mixture and mix well.
Add cereal. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto baking sheet.
Mash flat.
Bake at 320° to 350° until golden brown.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: russian tea cakes(like wedding cookies)
directions: Mix butter, corn syrup and vanilla well.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add chopped nuts.
Mix all ingredients real well.
Chill dough.
Roll into small balls and place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 10 minutes or until set but do not burn, then reduce temperature to 225° and bake 20 to 30 minutes longer.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and shape into small balls and drop into hot fat. Cook until done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add pumpkin and eggs.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add water, raisins and walnuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: luby's fruit salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: honey glazed chicken
directions: Combine egg yolk with all the other ingredients except the chicken.
Place in a 2 x 9 x 13-inch baking pan with chicken and marinate for 2 to 4 hours in refrigerator, turning occasionally. Place chicken in shallow baking pan in a single layer.
Spoon some marinade over chicken pieces and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until deep brown in color.

title: calico bean pot
directions: Mix all ingredients together in crock-pot and cook slowly for 4 hours.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice with sugar, milk, salt and vanilla (and raisins, cinnamon and nutmeg) in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours (90 minutes), stirring when a crust forms on top.
Add cream after the 90 minutes, but do not stir.
Bake another 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Pudding will get creamy while standing.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Then add all other ingredients.
Cook in tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Cook this all together and can and seal.

title: rice krispie treats(microwave)
directions: Mix margarine and marshmallows together and microwave until melted in a large bowl.
Add Rice Krispies; quickly stir together. Flatten out into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
When almost cooled, cut into squares.

title: deviled ham and cheese ball
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients except nuts and radish slices.
Chill until slightly firm.
Form into desired shape and garnish with radish slices and pecan halves.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serve with assorted crackers. Especially good with Stoned Wheat Thin crackers.
Yields 1 large cheese ball (approximately 3 1/3 cups of mixture).

title: creole jambalaya
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine ham, sausages and onions.
Over medium heat, saute 8 minutes, or until onions are soft.
Stir in rice.
Add green pepper, scallions, the boiling water, parsley, garlic, salt, thyme, paprika and bay leaf; mix well.
Bring to boiling; boil 5 minutes.
Over low heat, cook jambalaya, covered, 20 to 25 minutes, or until rice is tender, adding shrimp the last 8 minutes.
With large fork, fluff rice and evenly distribute ingredients.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Let cool.
Dissolve lemon jello in hot water.
Cool until it starts to set.
Combine with marshmallow mixture.
Whip cream and fold into mixture.

title: barbecue chicken legs
directions: Wash chicken under cool water and pat dry.
Combine ingredients and mix well.
Place chicken in a shallow pan and pour sauce over.
Marinate for 2 hours.
Prepare grill.
Place chicken at medium height and turn often.

title: pioneer mix biscuits
directions: Mix biscuit mix, oleo and sour cream.
Add club soda last. Mix well.
Turn out on board or counter and knead just until it can be cut with glass or cutter.
Bake at 450° for 11 to 13 minutes.

title: carob pie
directions: For crust, use 1/2 cup ground pecan meal, 1/2 cup coconut flakes and 1/2 cup crushed cornflakes with just enough margarine to press mixture in pie dish to make crust.

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: Follow directions of potatoes in bowl.
Set aside.

title: caramel chex mix
directions: Mix and divide first 6 ingredients into 2 large paper grocery bags.
Bring to a boil the rest of ingredients, except vanilla, and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Pour into the grocery bags and toss until well coated. Fold the top down of the bag and heat in microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and shake the bag, cook another 1 1/2 minutes, then repeat the process again.
Do the same with the other bag.
I spread this mixture out onto the counter to cool.
If you don't have a microwave, heat in 200° oven on large cookie sheets for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: cookie sticks
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the oil, sugars, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add to sugar mixture.
Divide dough in half.
On a greased baking sheet, shape each portion into 15 x 3-inch rectangle, about 3-inches apart. Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over dough; press lightly.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 7 minutes.
(Bake 8 to 9 minutes for crispier cookies.)
Cool for 5 minutes.
Cut with a serrated knife into 1-inch strips; remove to wire racks to cool.
Yield:
about 3 dozen.

title: dip for fresh fruit
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Cook on low heat until boils.
Add cream cheese and put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put 3 teaspoons oil into the skillet to heat while preparing.
Mix meat, soda and onion.
Add egg, milk and corn; stir well.
Add peppers and cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes.
The last 5 minutes, spoon salsa around edge of bread. Continue baking until done.
May be served with barbecue.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Break up and separate the cold cooked rice.
Dice meat, seafood and vegetables.
Keep the fresh and frozen vegetables separate from the canned.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a wok or other large deep pan.
Add scallions; stir-fry a few time.
Add fresh and/or frozen vegetables and stir-fry to soften slightly. Add canned vegetables and cooked meat; stir-fry until heated through and blended.
Remove all ingredients from pan.
Heat remaining oil to smoking.
Add rice and heat completely.
Return vegetables and meat; fold into rice and blend well.
Reheat, then quickly blend in soy sauce, salt, sugar and sherry.
Fold in beaten eggs and turn off heat as eggs begin to set.
Serve hot.

title: little pizzas
directions: Separate rolls and place them flat on a cookie sheet.
Spread 1 tablespoon sauce onto each roll.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hearty vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown meat with onion in a large pot. Cook until onion is tender and drain. Stir in remaining ingredients. Salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: four layer delight
directions: Melt margarine, then stir in flour, powdered sugar and nuts; spread thin in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Cool completely.

title: pineapple crush
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; cover and process on liquefy until slushy.
Double or triple recipe according to need.
Yields 3 cups.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients, except seed.
Whisk oil, milk, eggs and extract until smooth.
Add dry ingredients and stir until evenly moist.
Don't overstir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in large tins or 20 minutes in small tins.
Always use paper liners.

title: pull apart bread
directions: Mix yeast and warm milk.
Mix butter, egg, sugar, salt and flour.
Add apple.
Let rise.
Then remove from bowl and knead. Roll into balls.
Dip in butter.
Place in greased angel food cake pan.
After each layer, place cinnamon sugar and pecans.
Then more balls, etc.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Drizzle while warm with a mixture of powdered sugar and milk.

title: raisin pie(has clear filling)
directions: Mix raisins, sugar and flour thoroughly.
Slowly stir in boiling water, butter and salt.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Pour mixture into baked pie shell.

title: united nations sandwich
directions: Layer in the order listed.

title: lentil soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until light golden color. Add water
and
all ingredients except tomatoes, linguine and cheese. Bring
to boil and simmer 1 hour or until lentils are tender.
Add tomatoes and cooked linguine.
Serve with cheese. Serves 4 regular size people or 6 midgets.

title: italian cookies
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Wet hands and form round balls, then flatten.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes. Do not let them brown. Frost and dip into candy sprinkles.

title: green bean casserole
directions: First spread a layer of green beans, then a layer of corn and for third layer, use water chestnuts. Combine next 4 ingredients and spread over water chestnuts to form fourth layer.
Sprinkle cheese over chestnuts, crushed crackers and margarine.
Bake at 300° for about 25 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour, milk, salt and pepper in a bowl. Dip sliced tomatoes in mixture and fry in fat until well browned.

title: fat-free pasta primavera
directions: Spray frying pan with Pam.
Saute first 5 ingredients 4 to 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Meanwhile, spread flour in another large skillet.
Add can of evaporated skim milk and stir.
Do not boil as milk will separate.
Add salt, pepper and fresh basil. When liquid reaches a nice sauce consistency, add sauteed vegetables and serve over hot cooked pasta.
Sprinkle lightly with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: kim's old-fashioned chip cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder and nutmeg. Alternate flour and milk with creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up slices of bread and place in greased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Brown and drain sausage.
Spoon sausage over bread. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: egg casserole
directions: Place in baking dish according to amount of mixture.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Nice for company breakfast.

title: patti's dad's salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients except Blue cheese in blender container; cover and blend until smooth.
Remove dressing from container; stir in Blue cheese.
Cover; chill.
Garnish with additional Blue cheese, if desired.
Serve over your favorite tossed vegetable salad.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender and chill.
Peel and grate into a large bowl.
In saucepan, put butter and cheese and heat until melted.
Remove from heat and add the sour cream, onion and salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes and stir.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish, dot with butter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange slice candy
directions: Cut candy into very small pieces. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Spread in 2 well-greased 9 x 9 x 2 pans. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. Cut into 1 x 3-inch bars and roll in powdered sugar.

title: pudding eclair
directions: Layer bottom of a
