9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix vanilla pudding, 1/2 cup of sugar and 2 cups milk until well mixed.
Add Cool Whip and stir well.
Spoon half of this mixture over layer of graham crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers and then spoon the remainder of vanilla pudding mixture on top.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Mix chocolate pudding and 2 cups of milk and spread over crackers.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate cake roll
directions: Sift powdered sugar, flour, salt, cocoa and cream of tartar together 3 times.
Beat egg whites with additional cream of tartar until stiff; set aside.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon-colored; beat in vanilla and water.
Add sifted dry ingredients and beat until well blended.
Fold in beaten egg whites with wire whisk.
Bake in greased, waxed paper-lined jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch) at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
When done, loosen edges of cake with knife and invert on dish towel which has been sprinkled with powdered sugar.

Peel off waxed paper and roll cake, along with towel, from narrow end like a jelly roll. When cool, gently unroll and remove from towel, back onto jelly roll pan to spread with sweetened whipped cream.
Reroll (without towel) and fasten edges with toothpicks if necessary.
Chill in refrigerator before serving.
Cut in slices to serve.
Freezes well.

title: sweet graham cookies
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar, molasses and nuts. Line grahams on cookie sheet. Spoon sugar mixture on cookies. Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: copper pennies(serves 12)
directions: Mix these ingredients together.
Pour into casserole
and mix with vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight for flavor.

title: brooklyn beer cheese appetizers
directions: In a deep bowl, crush the garlic with back of a spoon.
Beat in the Worcestershire, hot pepper sauce, mustard and salt.
Stirring constantly, pour in the beer in a slow stream.
Beat in the cheese, 1 cup at a time, until the mix is smooth.
Pack the cheese into a 2-cup mold or crock.
Cover it with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 24 to 48 hours before serving.
Serve with crackers and more Brooklyn lager.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender.
Drain well and layer with Velveeta.
Place crackers and margarine on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted (30 minutes).

title: original banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in egg yolks, one at a time with enough milk to mix well.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Layer wafers, bananas and custard to make three layers of each.

title: cheese manicotti
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tomato sauce and pasta shells. Boil shells for 6 minutes; stuff with cheese mixture.
Pour 1/2 jar of sauce in a baking dish.
Arrange pasta in dish; top with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream butter.
Slowly beat in sugar.
Add vanilla and pineapple.

title: fresh creamed corn casserole
directions: Grate corn well and mix with small amount of water and sugar. Put oil in iron skillet and heat well. Add corn mixture and butter. Cook until corn begins to thicken.
(Water may need to be added, depending on amount of starch in corn.)
Stir constantly. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook until thick and pour into greased casserole.
Top with slices of butter and bake in oven for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for Magic Shell.
Place mixed ingredients in chocolate crusts and top with Magic Shell topping. Freeze.

title: breezy brownies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine and add eggs and salt.
Beat well. Add syrup and flour.
Grease and flour 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch cookie sheet.
Bake 22 minutes at 350°.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and mix with melted margarine.
Press into 13 x 9-inch cake pan for crust.
Stir together creme de menthe with Marshmallow Creme.
Fold in the whipped heavy cream.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle a few cookie crumbs on top.
Freeze.

title: chicketti
directions: Cook spaghetti in water just until done (do not overcook). Place chicken, soup, broth, onion, parsley, salt and pepper and half the Cheddar cheese in casserole.
Mix in drained spaghetti and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.
Best if made early in day and kept in refrigerator until ready to bake.
Great way to use leftover holiday turkey.

title: delicious meat and cheese enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and add onion (let cool).
Add shredded cheese with meat after cooled.
Mix all other ingredients in saucepan on low heat.
Fill tortillas with 3 tablespoons of meat and cheese.
Put in deep dish pan.
Pour sauce over tortillas.
Cover for 15 minutes.
Uncover 10 minutes on 350°.

title: dumplings
directions: Bring 2 cups water to a boil in saucepan.
Stir in margarine until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add flour and salt; mix well. Knead lightly on floured surface.
Roll 1/4 at a time to 1/8-inch thickness on lightly floured surface.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: beef ball
directions: Mix together everything and form a ball then roll in dried beef on the out side.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Cut fruit into small pieces.
Mix ingredients all together. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco together until fluffy.
Blend in other ingredients slowly.
Add one egg at a time.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: baked ham
directions: Use country ham, not Smithfield ham, but good for any standard ham.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Serve with French fries and celery sticks with Blue cheese dressing.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook shells.
Combine egg, bread crumbs, parsley, onion and salt.
Add meat and cheese.
Mix well.
Stuff shells.
Arrange stuffed shells in casserole dish.
Cover with spaghetti sauce. Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Serve with French bread.

title: butterfinger pie
directions: Blend the crushed Butterfingers with the cream cheese and Cool Whip in large mixing bowl.
Spread into pie crust.
Chill several hours in refrigerator.
Slice.

title: prune bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash jelly
directions: Boil squash and sugar for 20 minutes.
Add pineapple and lemon juice and boil for another 5 minutes.
Pour jello mix into the boiling mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into hot jars and refrigerate until used up.

title: black bean salsa pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta shells and corn according to directions on package. In a measuring cup, combine lime juice, olive oil, cumin, cayenne pepper, salt and sugar. Stir well. In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Toss well. Chill before serving. Serves 12.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, jello and cornstarch.
Heat 1 cup of water in saucepan and pour sugar mixture in the water, stirring as you pour.
When mixture is thick and smooth, remove from heat and cool completely.
Line baked pie shell with strawberries and pour cooked mixture over berries.
Chill and cover with Cool Whip.

title: cornmeal butter wafer
directions: Combine first two ingredients and beat until light and well blended.
Add yolks and mix well.
Then stir in rest of ingredients, blending thoroughly.
Chill dough until firm.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese, taco seasoning, sour cream and mayonnaise in a bowl until blended well, then spread the dip in a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Layer with lettuce, onions, tomatoes, cheese and black olives.
Serve with the taco chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses.
Add remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Mix well; shape into ball.
Roll in nuts.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Serve with crackers.

title: creole seasoning blend
directions: Italian Butter:
Combine 2 tablespoons butter or margarine (softened), 3 tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese, 1/4 teaspoon Italian seasoning and dash of garlic powder.

title: new orleans chicken tureen
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Brown chicken in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Bone chicken and serve with rice (cook in electric skillet).
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak into thin slices.
Marinate in soy sauce for 15 to 20 minutes (add meat tenderizer if needed).
Put steak into a frypan with 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil.
Brown.
Add green peppers; cook until peppers are tender.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: peas, butter beans, ham hock and baby okra
directions: In a large pot combine the ham hocks with enough water to cover.
Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for about 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.	Pick over peas and beans; wash thoroughly.
Stir in all except okra.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: no fail cream cheese mints
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together; add food coloring and flavoring.
Form desired shapes.
(Candy mixture may be refrigerated before shaping.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and put in greased casserole dish. Cut up margarine and spread on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately one hour.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Pour cherry pie filling in 9 x 13 dish. Pour cake mix evenly over pie filling. Slice butter into several pieces and place all over top. (Optional: Nuts can be sprinkled on top, if desired.) Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until top is golden brown.

title: fried rice
directions: Melt margarine in nonstick pan. Scramble egg in mixture with onions, peas and carrots.
Add cold cooked rice.
Dilute soy sauce with the water.
Pour over mixture.
Cook until heated completely.

title: cran-orange drink
directions: Combine cranberry juice, lemon juice and sugar.
Mix well. Chill.
Just before serving, add orange soda.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and oleo.
Add eggs and beat some more.
Add vanilla, soda, salt and baking powder.
Blend in flour.
Add nuts and chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Brown onion, bell pepper and garlic in butter.
Cook spaghetti in water used to cook chicken.
Put all ingredients in large casserole dish with tomato sauce, soup, pimento and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cheese, reserving some for top.
Cook 45 minutes at 350° until brown.

title: italian coleslaw
directions: Place cabbage in bowl in layers, alternating with onion.
Top with sugar.
Boil the remaining ingredients.
Pour over cabbage while hot.
Cover; let stand 4 to 6 hours in refrigerator.
Then mix and serve.
Even better after 2 or 3 days and will keep 2 or 3 weeks.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Combine mixtures and eggs.
Add 4 cups flour.
Beat thoroughly and then add rest of the flour.
Do not knead! Cover and put into fridge overnight. Pinch into small rolls.
Place in greased pans.
Let rise in a warm place about an hour or until double in bulk.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: bubble pizza
directions: Brown meat.
Pour off fat.
Add sauce and let simmer until hot (2-3 minutes).
Cut biscuits into quarters (layer in glass casserole dish).
Pour meat mixture over biscuits.
Mix cheeses. Use half over sauce.
Sprinkle with a little Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Take out of oven, add rest of the cheese. Bake for 2-3 minutes more.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and make out into balls the size of a walnut. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: squash dressing
directions: Stir all together and cook at 350° in a buttered casserole for 40 minutes.

title: chicken soup with dumplings
directions: Rinse chicken and place in a large cooking pot 3/4 full of water.
Cut onions to desired size.
Place in water with chicken. Add salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, then simmer on medium for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove chicken and let cool to touch.
Strip meat and place back in soup.
Let simmer on low.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning and place in serving dish. Top with chopped lettuce, diced tomatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: yurda(cheesecake cookies)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; stir in butter.
Reserve 1/3 cup crumbs.
Press remaining crumbs in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Shred vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand 1 hour. Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Boil for 3 minutes; cool.
Stir well into cabbage.
Let stand 3 minutes. Freeze in containers.

title: christmas holly punch
directions: Mix together the juices, water and grenadine; add ginger ale. Pour over ice in punch bowl.
Float lemon or orange slices on punch.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: oursler barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients; simmer for about 1 hour.
May add cooked meat to sauce and simmer an additional 20 minutes or use sauce to brush on cooked meat.
Adjust ingredients to your taste.

title: fry bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Sprinkle work surface with flour.
Roll out dough and cut into strips of desired width.
Fry in hot oil (about 1 inch deep in skillet) until golden brown on both sides.
Serve with jam.

title: cheese-vegetable soup
directions: Boil first four ingredients for 20 minutes.
Then add potatoes and vegetables.
Cook 30 minutes longer.
Add soup and cheese. Cook until cheese is melted.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat well.
Bake in prepared tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: binky's vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, adding sugar while beating. Dissolve gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add 1/2 cup hot water to gelatine.
Add Knox gelatine mixture to sugar and egg whites.
Add whipping cream and vanilla extract.
Fill to full line of ice cream maker with milk.
Can also add fruit or 6 Heath bars, ground.

title: aunt ruth's peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine milk, butter and powdered sugar in a large saucepan. Boil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream. Stir until smooth.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch or similar size pan. Cool in refrigerator until hard.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
Combine the next 5 ingredients; simmer until ready to eat.
Top with cheese, sour cream and chips on top of soup.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Mix meat, flour, salt and pepper. Form into 1/4-inch patties. Dip into beaten eggs, then into cracker crumbs. Fry for 7 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and form into
loaves and place in pan.
Put 1/2 can Hunt's tomato sauce,
can water, 2 tablespoons dark syrup or brown sugar,
tablespoons prepared mustard and 2 tablespoons vinegar over meat loaf.
Bake
hour
and 10 minutes at 350°. Baste several times.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add onion, green pepper and salt. After these have cooked a little, add cooked spaghetti, soups, water, mushrooms, and garlic powder.
Pour into a 3 qt. casserole and top with shredded sharp cheese.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter bites
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients. Roll into 48 balls. Place on ungreased baking sheets. Flatten with a fork. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool on wire racks. Enjoy!

title: spinach-cheese squares(low-fat)
directions: Cook onion in nonstick pan until soft.
Add 1 1/2 cups of the milk and heat.
Mix the cornstarch with the remaining 1/2 cup of milk and add to the hot mixture, stirring until thick and smooth. Break up the cheese and add it.
Slowly add the hot sauce to the beaten eggs, stirring constantly.
Add the spinach; season with salt and pepper and mix.
Pour into an 8-inch square dish and set it in a shallow pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Serves 6, 112 calories per serving.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Boil 8 minutes the milk, butter and sugar.
Take off stove and add marshmallows, beating until melted.
Add coconut and nuts. Cut cake layers in half with thread so you will have 4 layers. Spread mixture between layers.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Add butter.
Eat and enjoy!

title: ham ball appetizer
directions: Mix ingredients well and roll in pecans. Serve with crackers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add the sugar to the cranberries, let stand for 2 hours or overnight.
Add the rest of the ingredients, mix and refrigerate. Makes a large quantity.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until done; drain.
Then put in casserole dish. Mix together egg, mushroom soup, mayo, onion and grated cheese. Pour over broccoli.
Crumble crackers and mix with melted butter. Cover broccoli with crackers.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: baked "stuffed" shrimp
directions: Melt butter.
Mix cooking sherry into cream of mushroom soup. Peel and devein shrimp.
Dip shrimp in melted butter, then in soup mixture. Roll in bread crumbs.
Place on a cookie sheet in a single layer.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: lentil-potato soup
directions: Cook dry lentils for one hour.
While the lentils are cooking, add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook until the lentils are tender.
Mash slightly.
One cup of canned milk can be added if desired.

title: chocolate cloud dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix butter, flour and 3/4 cup walnuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Bake at 350° until slightly browned (approximately 20 minutes).

title: turk-getti
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Add all except 1/2 cup cheese.
Toss lightly. Use 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: krupnik(polish version of "fire water")
directions: Mix the honey, water, vanilla, spices and lemon rind.
Bring to soft boil; simmer for about 5 minutes, covered.
Take off the stove and add the vodka.
Heat it, but do not bring it to boil.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli and rice according to directions.
Saute the onions and celery in salad oil.
Cook cream soup, milk and Cheez Whiz until cheese is melted.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered at 350° for 35 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cream of lima bean soup(great hot or cold)
directions: Simmer limas for 30 minutes or more, until very soft (baby limas cook faster).
Drain, saving the liquid.
Strain or puree; return puree to saucepan.
Add 1 cup (more or less) of the bean liquid, 1 cup milk (more or less), the bouillon, savory and crushed garlic.
Simmer all of this for 15 minutes; stir and watch (milk burns and sticks).
Add the sour cream, blending.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: crescent wrapped gouda
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut cheese in half crosswise to form 2 circles; remove wax.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal. Place 2 rectangles on top of each other; press each stack into a 6-inch square.
Place cheese in center of each square.
Pull corners of dough to top center of cheese.
Press dough tightly; twist dough in center to seal. Press seams to seal.
Brush with egg.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 18 to 22 minutes until golden.
Cool 10 minutes.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: broccoli-chicken-cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli about 10 minutes, until almost tender.
Drain and arrange in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with chicken; set aside.

title: fudge popsicles
directions: Combine pie mix, sugar and milk in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until it comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat. Cool for 5 minutes.
Pour into shallow pan.
Freeze until it freezes around edges, about 30 minutes.
Stir until smooth, but not melted.
Spoon into paper cups.
Put a wooden stick into center.
Freeze until firm.
Makes 7.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil zucchini in small amount of water until tender.
In saucepan, saute carrots and onion in margarine. Stir in soup and sour cream.
Add zucchini and 1 1/2 cups of the croutons.
Spoon into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine remaining croutons and melted margarine; sprinkle over top.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: salami
directions: Knead all ingredients together.
Put in covered bowl and refrigerate. Every day, knead for 5 minutes.
Cover and put back in refrigerator.
On the fourth day, knead and form into 2 to 4 rolls.
Bake 9 hours at 200° or at 160°.
Bake on rack so grease drops off.
Broiler pan works fine.
When you remove from oven, drain on paper towels while cooling.
Makes 4 rolls.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Slice eggplant in thin slices and sprinkle with salt.
Mix tomato, onion, green pepper, olives and salt and pepper to taste. Add rosemary and mix well.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add remaining items and simmer.

title: chicken and sausage pie
directions: Melt butter and add mushrooms. Saute until soft, then add all other ingredients and bring to a slow boil. Turn off and set aside.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: First put tomato sauce in pan with olive oil, crushed garlic and red wine.
Add tomato paste, oregano, Italian seasoning, onion salt and bay leaf.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Pour hot water over jello and dissolve.
Add strawberries and pineapple (drained partly), add mashed bananas and mix well. Pour half of mixture in mold and let jell.
Then add small carton sour cream, then add remainder of mixture on top and chill.
Will keep for several days.

title: easy barbecue chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Place in frying pan.
Mix Coke, catsup and mustard; pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes to an hour.

title: chicken broccoli dish
directions: In a greased casserole, layer chicken (torn in bite size pieces).
Cut up dried beef and layer on chicken, then broccoli. Mix soups and mayonnaise; pour over ingredients.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: pecan squash
directions: Cook squash in salted water 10 minutes.
Drain.
Combine mayonnaise, cheese, eggs, seasoning, and onion with squash.
Pour into baking dish.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut in Crisco until it crumbles.
Mix egg and milk together and add to flour mixture.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Let set or stand 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut in strips and drop in boiling chicken broth.
Add 2 to 4 tablespoons butter.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: old pa. dutch pie crust
directions: Mix water, egg and vinegar in small dish; beat well.
Place in freezer to get cold.
Cut in flour, salt and shortening; mix all ingredients.
Roll out dough.
Makes 3 crusts.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, condensed milk and lemon juice.
Add all other ingredients and pour into cool pie shells.
Best if made a few days in advance.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together with squash.
Grease a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until browned on top. Yield:
8 servings.

title: spinach and cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine and set aside spinach and cheese.
Combine rest of ingredients and add the spinach and cheese mix.
Blend well.
Stir into butter in pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes. Cut into 1-inch squares.
Serve warm.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: In saucepan, combine butter, brown sugar and corn syrup.
Stir well and bring to boil over medium heat.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk.
Simmer, stirring constantly, until the mixture forms a soft ball (234° to 238°) when dropped in cold water.
Takes just a few minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over popped corn and stir well until all kernels are coated.
Butter hands lightly; shape into 3 1/2-inch balls.
Makes 15 balls.

title: french toast
directions: Beat egg and add enough cream to coat both sides of bread. Put a little butter in pan and melt.
Then dip bread in mix and put in pan.
Fry until golden brown, then turn and fry until golden brown on that side.
Use topping of your choice.
My favorite is cinnamon and sugar.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream; spread on plate.
Add remaining ingredients.
Top with sauce and shredded cheese. Amounts for each ingredient can vary depending upon how much you want to make.

title: connecticut beef supper
directions: Brown meat and onions in oil; pour off oil.
Drain mushrooms (reserve liquid).
Add water to reserved mushroom liquid to make 1 cup.
Stir mushrooms and liquid into beef mixture.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 2 hours, until meat is tender.

title: rolls
directions: Mix hot water, salt, shortening and sugar in a large bowl. Cool.
Add yeast mixture, then the eggs and half of the flour. Beat well.
Add rest of flour.
Store in the refrigerator and use as needed.

title: chunky chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Soften butter; add flour and baking soda. Mix well. Add brown sugar, the white sugar and egg; mix. Add vanilla, then add chocolate chips. Drop dough onto cookie sheet. Leave 2 inches between each cookie. Bake the cookies for 8 to 10 minutes or until the cookies are golden brown.

title: cheesers
directions: Lay tortillas flat on cookie sheet.
Layer chosen ingredients on each tortilla, beginning with meat, if any.
Top with cheese. Put cookie sheets into oven and bake for 10 minutes at 350° or until cheese is bubbling.
Remove from oven and serve immediately.

title: spicy hot tea
directions: Bring
quart water to a boil, pour over tea bags and steep 5
minutes.
Combine
1 quart
water, sugar and spices, bring
to a
boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.	Combine spice mixture,
tea
and	juice.	Boil the remaining 3 quarts water
and add
to mixture.
Strain.	Serve with lemon slices studded with whole cloves.
Makes about 6 quarts.
Refrigerate unused portion and reheat as wanted.

title: fudge
directions: Put sugar, Dr. Pepper, grated chocolate and corn syrup in a heavy saucepan.
Cook very slowly, stirring constantly, until sugar and chocolate are thoroughly dissolved.
Continue cooking, on low-medium heat, until temperature of 236° or soft ball stage is reached.
Set off heat and cool at room temperature to lukewarm, 110°.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat until the candy loses its shiny look.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour into slightly buttered pans.
When cold, cut into squares.
Yields approximately 2 1/2 to 3 pounds or 36 pieces 1/2-inch thick and 2-inches square.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown and drain first 5 ingredients.
Cook noodles and drain. Mix all ingredients together except cheese and pour into casserole pans (8 1/2 x 11-inch or about).
Makes 2 or 3 pans.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: corn meal mush
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add cold water and mix.
Add butter and hot water.
Boil 5 minutes, then turn heat on low. Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and pour in 6 x 9 1/2-inch cake pan.
When cold, slice and fry or eat it hot with brown sugar and milk.

title: almost raspberry jam
directions: In large kettle, combine tomatoes and sugar; simmer for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved, about 1 minute, stirring occasionally to prevent floating fruit.
Pour into jars or plastic containers. Cool; top with lids.
Refrigerate up to 3 weeks.
Yields 7 cups.

title: curry ripe olive sandwich
directions: Mix thoroughly in a bowl all ingredients except muffins. Toast backs of muffins split in half lengthwise.
Pile mixture high on other side.
Mixture is piled high because it flattens as cheese melts.
Place under broiler until puffy and brown.
This is an excellent main dish for lunch.
Serves 6.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen canapes on Melba toast rounds.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Alternate layers of cabbage, pepper, carrot, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Boil the oil, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Do not stir.
Will keep in refrigerator 2 weeks.

title: "the thing"
directions: Well grease a 9-inch tube pan.
Roll each ball into shortening, then sugar, then nuts and put a layer into tube pan, so they barely touch.
Sprinkle 1/2 the raisins on top, then put another layer of balls.
Sprinkle rest of raisins on top.
Cover and let rise until light, about 45 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. Break or cut into pieces for serving.

title: lemon bread
directions: When bread is finished, prick with a fork and pour the lemon-sugar mixture over it while it is still hot.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate bits a little and add milk.
Stir until well melted.
Stir in 1 cup flour.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and add 1 cup chopped pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for exactly 8 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Put cream in blender container and blend until stiff.
Add bananas, a few pieces at a time, and process until bananas are well chopped.
Scrape mixture from sides of container occasionally.
Add mayonnaise and salt and run until well blended.
Add marshmallows, a few at a time, and blend.
Add pecans and fruit and blend until just mixed.
Pour into freezer tray and freeze.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except rhubarb.
Slowly stir in rhubarb.
Put mixture in prebaked pie shell and top with lattice crust.
Brush lattice crust with milk.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: s & s special taverns
directions: Brown hamburger.
Pour off grease.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well and heat until bubbly.
Can be eaten then or put in crock-pot on low and eaten later.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Blend in vanilla and chocolate.
Sift flour with soda and salt; add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture, beating after each addition until smooth.
Fold in beaten whites.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Whip cream until stiff.
In another bowl, beat cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold cheese mix into cream.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: beef tips
directions: Brown stew meat.
Place all ingredients into casserole dish, cover with foil, then with tight lid.
Bake at 275° for about 2 hours.
Turn off oven and leave another 1/2 hour, if desired. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix; spread mixture in a 12 x 8-inch pan.
Layer the remaining ingredients in the order given; chill.
For dipping, use large size Fritos.

title: keolu salad dressing
directions: Place ingredients in a blender; blend well.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Combine pudding, jello and water in pan; bring to a boil. Then cool and chill.
After it thickens, fold in Cool Whip, oranges and mini marshmallows.
Chill well.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs. Blend remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place 1 inch of water and broccoli in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 to 8 minutes or just until crisp-tender. Drain and place in a greased 2 qt. baking dish. In a bowl, combine the soup, mayonnaise, cheese and lemon juice. Pour over broccoli. Sprinkle with crushed crackers. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through. Yield: 6 to 8 serving.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter or margarine and sugar in large bowl until creamy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and blend until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Turn mixture into pie shell.
Bake until center is set and top is golden, about 50 minutes.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine
all ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in saucepan. Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat. Mix rest of ingredients. Drop on wax paper by teaspoon. Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: korean potato and hot dogs
directions: Cube potatoes and hot dogs; dice onions.
Mix everything together in a soup pot.
Cook on medium heat, stirring often, until potatoes are soft.
Add more soy sauce if the mixture gets too dry.

title: hickory smoked brisket
directions: Sprinkle beef with all salts and garlic powder.
Place in baking dish.
Pour liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce over the meat and cover with foil.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight, turning once.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 4 to 4 1/2 hours or until tender.
Pour out about 3/4 of brisket juice, then pour commercial barbecue sauce over beef and bake, uncovered, an additional 30 minutes.
Let stand about 10 to 15 minutes before cutting and then serve.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Coat beef with mixture and brown in hot shortening.
Add seasonings, tomatoes and broth to meat. Cover and simmer over low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.
Stir in vegetables except peas.
Cover and cook about 30 minutes.
Add peas; cover and cook about 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings and very good over rice.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Melt oleo; mix oleo, flour and nuts.
Pat in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, then cool.
Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until soft.
Mix ingredients until all powdered sugar is blended into Cool Whip and cheese.
Top with a can of cherry pie filling.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream the butter.
Add the sugar and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in the flour then the pecans; mix well.
Chill 15 minutes.
Roll the dough into small balls the size of a marble. Place on a greased cookie sheet, spacing them an inch apart.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until delicately brown.
Roll in sugar while warm (not hot) then again when the cookies have cooled.

title: debi's chicken fettucini
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Use broth from chicken and cook with fettucini.
Saute onion, celery and butter.
Add mushrooms, Velveeta cheese, cream of chicken soup and cream of mushroom soup. Add this to cooked chicken and fettucini.

title: italian seasoned chicken
directions: In a large strainer rinse vegetables with warm water to help thaw.
Place vegetables in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix bread crumbs and cheese in a large bowl.
Rinse chicken and pat dry. Cover all sides of chicken with Miracle Whip.
Roll chicken in bread crumb mixture.
Fold in half and secure with a toothpick. Arrange chicken pieces with the thickest portions toward the edge of casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and cover and microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: shrimp pizza(appetizer)
directions: Mix horseradish, Ricotta cheese, chives and onion; spread on pizza dough.
Arrange shrimp on top of Ricotta cheese mixture; sprinkle on bacon and peppers.
Top with cheese and red peppers to taste.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes or until crust is done. Leave crust in square shape and cut into bite-size pieces.

title: best corn muffins
directions: Mix everything by hand in large bowl.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 23 minutes until light brown.

title: oven steak
directions: Place steak on aluminum foil and sprinkle with onion soup mix on top.
Wrap well and place in 250° oven for 2 1/2 or 3 hours.

title: anticuchos
directions: Wash beef hearts well, removing all nerves and fat.
Cut into 1-inch cubes.
Place in enamel bowl, along with all other ingredients.
Marinate for 24 to 48 hours.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: About 3 1/2 hours before serving, in large saucepot or 6-quart Dutch oven, place chicken, giblets, Bouquet Garni, 4 teaspoons salt and hot water to cover chicken.
Over high heat, heat mixture to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 1 1/4 hours or until chicken is fork-tender.
Discard Bouquet Garni.
With slotted spoon, remove chicken to large bowl; cool.
Remove and discard chicken bones and skin.
Cut meat and giblets into bite size pieces.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Cook vegetables.
Save a little water.
Mix cream cheese and cream of chicken soup; add to vegetables with the half and half or evaporated milk.
Add the parsley and butter and heat through. Add bacon on top.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: ukrainian borscht
directions: Saute diced onions and carrots in butter until tender.
Add tomato paste, then flour.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer bean dip on plate, then guacamole, next sour cream, black olives and cheese.
Refrigerate.
Serve with Doritos.

title: baked apple and cheese dessert
directions: Arrange sliced apples in a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar and lemon juice.
Mix together in bowl the flour, salt, remaining brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. Mix in grated cheese.
Spoon this mixture over apples and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can serve warm with cream.

title: parmesan fried chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Dip chicken into dressing, then coat with bread and cheese mixture.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
